2964
2965void CursorVisitor::EnqueueWorkList(VisitorWorkList &WL, const Stmt *S) {
2966 EnqueueVisitor(WL, MakeCXCursor(S, StmtParent, TU,RegionOfInterest)).Visit(S);
2967}
2968
2969bool CursorVisitor::IsInRegionOfInterest(CXCursor C) {
2970 if (RegionOfInterest.isValid()) {
2971 SourceRange Range = getRawCursorExtent(C);
2972 if (Range.isInvalid() || CompareRegionOfInterest(Range))
2973 return false;
2974 }
2975 return true;
2976}
2977
2978bool CursorVisitor::RunVisitorWorkList(VisitorWorkList &WL) {
2979 while (!WL.empty()) {
2980 // Dequeue the worklist item.
2981 VisitorJob LI = WL.pop_back_val();
2982
2983 // Set the Parent field, then back to its old value once we're done.
2984 SetParentRAII SetParent(Parent, StmtParent, LI.getParent());
2985
2986 switch (LI.getKind()) {
2987 case VisitorJob::DeclVisitKind: {
2988 const Decl *D = cast<DeclVisit>(&LI)->get();
2989 if (!D)
2990 continue;
2991
2992 // For now, perform default visitation for Decls.
2993 if (Visit(MakeCXCursor(D, TU, RegionOfInterest,
2994 cast<DeclVisit>(&LI)->isFirst())))
2995 return true;
2996
2997 continue;
2998 }
2999 case VisitorJob::ExplicitTemplateArgsVisitKind: {
3000 for (const TemplateArgumentLoc &Arg :
3001 *cast<ExplicitTemplateArgsVisit>(&LI)) {
3002 if (VisitTemplateArgumentLoc(Arg))
3003 return true;
3004 }
3005 continue;
3006 }
3007 case VisitorJob::TypeLocVisitKind: {
3008 // Perform default visitation for TypeLocs.
3009 if (Visit(cast<TypeLocVisit>(&LI)->get()))
3010 return true;
3011 continue;
3012 }
3013 case VisitorJob::LabelRefVisitKind: {
3014 const LabelDecl *LS = cast<LabelRefVisit>(&LI)->get();
3015 if (LabelStmt *stmt = LS->getStmt()) {
3016 if (Visit(MakeCursorLabelRef(stmt, cast<LabelRefVisit>(&LI)->getLoc(),
3017 TU))) {
3018 return true;
3019 }
3020 }
3021 continue;
3022 }
3023
3024 case VisitorJob::NestedNameSpecifierLocVisitKind: {
3025 NestedNameSpecifierLocVisit *V = cast<NestedNameSpecifierLocVisit>(&LI);
3026 if (VisitNestedNameSpecifierLoc(V->get()))
3027 return true;
3028 continue;
3029 }
3030
3031 case VisitorJob::DeclarationNameInfoVisitKind: {
3032 if (VisitDeclarationNameInfo(cast<DeclarationNameInfoVisit>(&LI)
3033 ->get()))
3034 return true;
3035 continue;
3036 }
3037 case VisitorJob::MemberRefVisitKind: {
3038 MemberRefVisit *V = cast<MemberRefVisit>(&LI);
3039 if (Visit(MakeCursorMemberRef(V->get(), V->getLoc(), TU)))
3040 return true;
3041 continue;
3042 }
3043 case VisitorJob::StmtVisitKind: {
3044 const Stmt *S = cast<StmtVisit>(&LI)->get();
3045 if (!S)
3046 continue;
3047
3048 // Update the current cursor.
3049 CXCursor Cursor = MakeCXCursor(S, StmtParent, TU, RegionOfInterest);
3050 if (!IsInRegionOfInterest(Cursor))
3051 continue;
3052 switch (Visitor(Cursor, Parent, ClientData)) {
3053 case CXChildVisit_Break: return true;
3054 case CXChildVisit_Continue: break;
3055 case CXChildVisit_Recurse:
3056 if (PostChildrenVisitor)
3057 WL.push_back(PostChildrenVisit(nullptr, Cursor));
3058 EnqueueWorkList(WL, S);
3059 break;
3060 }
3061 continue;
3062 }
3063 case VisitorJob::MemberExprPartsKind: {
3064 // Handle the other pieces in the MemberExpr besides the base.
3065 const MemberExpr *M = cast<MemberExprParts>(&LI)->get();
3066
3067 // Visit the nested-name-specifier
3068 if (NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc = M->getQualifierLoc())
3069 if (VisitNestedNameSpecifierLoc(QualifierLoc))
3070 return true;
3071
3072 // Visit the declaration name.
3073 if (VisitDeclarationNameInfo(M->getMemberNameInfo()))
3074 return true;
3075
3076 // Visit the explicitly-specified template arguments, if any.
3077 if (M->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()) {
3078 for (const TemplateArgumentLoc *Arg = M->getTemplateArgs(),
3079 *ArgEnd = Arg + M->getNumTemplateArgs();
3080 Arg != ArgEnd; ++Arg) {
3081 if (VisitTemplateArgumentLoc(*Arg))
3082 return true;
3083 }
3084 }
3085 continue;
3086 }
3087 case VisitorJob::DeclRefExprPartsKind: {
3088 const DeclRefExpr *DR = cast<DeclRefExprParts>(&LI)->get();
3089 // Visit nested-name-specifier, if present.
3090 if (NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc = DR->getQualifierLoc())
3091 if (VisitNestedNameSpecifierLoc(QualifierLoc))
3092 return true;
3093 // Visit declaration name.
3094 if (VisitDeclarationNameInfo(DR->getNameInfo()))
3095 return true;
3096 continue;
3097 }
3098 case VisitorJob::OverloadExprPartsKind: {
3099 const OverloadExpr *O = cast<OverloadExprParts>(&LI)->get();
3100 // Visit the nested-name-specifier.
3101 if (NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc = O->getQualifierLoc())
3102 if (VisitNestedNameSpecifierLoc(QualifierLoc))
3103 return true;
3104 // Visit the declaration name.
3105 if (VisitDeclarationNameInfo(O->getNameInfo()))
3106 return true;
3107 // Visit the overloaded declaration reference.
3108 if (Visit(MakeCursorOverloadedDeclRef(O, TU)))
3109 return true;
3110 continue;
3111 }
3112 case VisitorJob::SizeOfPackExprPartsKind: {
3113 const SizeOfPackExpr *E = cast<SizeOfPackExprParts>(&LI)->get();
3114 NamedDecl *Pack = E->getPack();
3115 if (isa<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(Pack)) {
3116 if (Visit(MakeCursorTypeRef(cast<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(Pack),
3117 E->getPackLoc(), TU)))
3118 return true;
3119
3120 continue;
3121 }
3122
3123 if (isa<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(Pack)) {
3124 if (Visit(MakeCursorTemplateRef(cast<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(Pack),
3125 E->getPackLoc(), TU)))
3126 return true;
3127
3128 continue;
3129 }
3130
3131 // Non-type template parameter packs and function parameter packs are
3132 // treated like DeclRefExpr cursors.
3133 continue;
3134 }
3135
3136 case VisitorJob::LambdaExprPartsKind: {
3137 // Visit non-init captures.
3138 const LambdaExpr *E = cast<LambdaExprParts>(&LI)->get();
3139 for (LambdaExpr::capture_iterator C = E->explicit_capture_begin(),
3140 CEnd = E->explicit_capture_end();
3141 C != CEnd; ++C) {
3142 if (!C->capturesVariable())
3143 continue;
3144
3145 if (Visit(MakeCursorVariableRef(C->getCapturedVar(),
3146 C->getLocation(),
3147 TU)))
3148 return true;
3149 }
3150 // Visit init captures
3151 for (auto InitExpr : E->capture_inits()) {
3152 if (Visit(InitExpr))
3153 return true;
3154 }
3155
3156 TypeLoc TL = E->getCallOperator()->getTypeSourceInfo()->getTypeLoc();
3157 // Visit parameters and return type, if present.
3158 if (FunctionTypeLoc Proto = TL.getAs<FunctionProtoTypeLoc>()) {
3159 if (E->hasExplicitParameters()) {
3160 // Visit parameters.
3161 for (unsigned I = 0, N = Proto.getNumParams(); I != N; ++I)
3162 if (Visit(MakeCXCursor(Proto.getParam(I), TU)))
3163 return true;
3164 }
3165 if (E->hasExplicitResultType()) {
3166 // Visit result type.
3167 if (Visit(Proto.getReturnLoc()))
3168 return true;
3169 }
3170 }
3171 break;
3172 }
3173
3174 case VisitorJob::PostChildrenVisitKind:
3175 if (PostChildrenVisitor(Parent, ClientData))
3176 return true;
3177 break;
3178 }
3179 }
3180 return false;
3181}
3182
3183bool CursorVisitor::Visit(const Stmt *S) {
3184 VisitorWorkList *WL = nullptr;
3185 if (!WorkListFreeList.empty()) {
3186 WL = WorkListFreeList.back();
3187 WL->clear();
3188 WorkListFreeList.pop_back();
3189 }
3190 else {
3191 WL = new VisitorWorkList();
3192 WorkListCache.push_back(WL);
3193 }
3194 EnqueueWorkList(*WL, S);
3195 bool result = RunVisitorWorkList(*WL);
3196 WorkListFreeList.push_back(WL);
3197 return result;
3198}
3199
3200namespace {
3201typedef SmallVector<SourceRange, 4> RefNamePieces;
3202RefNamePieces buildPieces(unsigned NameFlags, bool IsMemberRefExpr,
3203 const DeclarationNameInfo &NI, SourceRange QLoc,
3204 const SourceRange *TemplateArgsLoc = nullptr) {
3205 const bool WantQualifier = NameFlags & CXNameRange_WantQualifier;
3206 const bool WantTemplateArgs = NameFlags & CXNameRange_WantTemplateArgs;
3207 const bool WantSinglePiece = NameFlags & CXNameRange_WantSinglePiece;
3208
3209 const DeclarationName::NameKind Kind = NI.getName().getNameKind();
3210
3211 RefNamePieces Pieces;
3212
3213 if (WantQualifier && QLoc.isValid())
3214 Pieces.push_back(QLoc);
3215
3216 if (Kind != DeclarationName::CXXOperatorName || IsMemberRefExpr)
3217 Pieces.push_back(NI.getLoc());
3218
3219 if (WantTemplateArgs && TemplateArgsLoc && TemplateArgsLoc->isValid())
3220 Pieces.push_back(*TemplateArgsLoc);
3221
3222 if (Kind == DeclarationName::CXXOperatorName) {
3223 Pieces.push_back(SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(
3224 NI.getInfo().CXXOperatorName.BeginOpNameLoc));
3225 Pieces.push_back(SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(
3226 NI.getInfo().CXXOperatorName.EndOpNameLoc));
3227 }
3228
3229 if (WantSinglePiece) {
3230 SourceRange R(Pieces.front().getBegin(), Pieces.back().getEnd());
3231 Pieces.clear();
3232 Pieces.push_back(R);
3233 }
3234
3235 return Pieces;
3236}
3237}

3239//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3240// Misc. API hooks.
3241//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3242
3243static void fatal_error_handler(void *user_data, const std::string& reason,
3244 bool gen_crash_diag) {
3245 // Write the result out to stderr avoiding errs() because raw_ostreams can
3246 // call report_fatal_error.
3247 fprintf(stderr, "LIBCLANG FATAL ERROR: %s\n", reason.c_str());
3248 ::abort();
3249}
3250
3251namespace {
3252struct RegisterFatalErrorHandler {
3253 RegisterFatalErrorHandler() {
3254 llvm::install_fatal_error_handler(fatal_error_handler, nullptr);
3255 }
3256};
3257}
3258
3259static llvm::ManagedStatic<RegisterFatalErrorHandler> RegisterFatalErrorHandlerOnce;
3260
3261CXIndex clang_createIndex(int excludeDeclarationsFromPCH,
3262 int displayDiagnostics) {
3263 // We use crash recovery to make some of our APIs more reliable, implicitly
3264 // enable it.
3265 if (!getenv("LIBCLANG_DISABLE_CRASH_RECOVERY"))
3266 llvm::CrashRecoveryContext::Enable();
3267
3268 // Look through the managed static to trigger construction of the managed
3269 // static which registers our fatal error handler. This ensures it is only
3270 // registered once.
3271 (void)*RegisterFatalErrorHandlerOnce;
3272
3273 // Initialize targets for clang module support.
3274 llvm::InitializeAllTargets();
3275 llvm::InitializeAllTargetMCs();
3276 llvm::InitializeAllAsmPrinters();
3277 llvm::InitializeAllAsmParsers();
3278
3279 CIndexer *CIdxr = new CIndexer();
3280
3281 if (excludeDeclarationsFromPCH)
3282 CIdxr->setOnlyLocalDecls();
3283 if (displayDiagnostics)
3284 CIdxr->setDisplayDiagnostics();
3285
3286 if (getenv("LIBCLANG_BGPRIO_INDEX"))
3287 CIdxr->setCXGlobalOptFlags(CIdxr->getCXGlobalOptFlags() |
3288 CXGlobalOpt_ThreadBackgroundPriorityForIndexing);
3289 if (getenv("LIBCLANG_BGPRIO_EDIT"))
3290 CIdxr->setCXGlobalOptFlags(CIdxr->getCXGlobalOptFlags() |
3291 CXGlobalOpt_ThreadBackgroundPriorityForEditing);
3292
3293 return CIdxr;
3294}
3295

3297 if (CIdx)
3298 delete static_cast<CIndexer *>(CIdx);
3299}

3324
3325CXTranslationUnit clang_createTranslationUnit(CXIndex CIdx,
3326 const char *ast_filename) {
3327 CXTranslationUnit TU;
3328 enum CXErrorCode Result =
3329 clang_createTranslationUnit2(CIdx, ast_filename, &TU);
3330 (void)Result;
3331 assert((TU && Result == CXError_Success) ||
3332 (!TU && Result != CXError_Success));
3333 return TU;
3334}
3335
3336enum CXErrorCode clang_createTranslationUnit2(CXIndex CIdx,
3337 const char *ast_filename,
3338 CXTranslationUnit *out_TU) {
3339 if (out_TU)
3340 *out_TU = nullptr;
3341
3342 if (!CIdx || !ast_filename || !out_TU)
3343 return CXError_InvalidArguments;
3344
3345 LOG_FUNC_SECTION {
3346 *Log << ast_filename;
3347 }
3348
3349 CIndexer *CXXIdx = static_cast<CIndexer *>(CIdx);
3350 FileSystemOptions FileSystemOpts;
3351
3352 IntrusiveRefCntPtr<DiagnosticsEngine> Diags =
3353 CompilerInstance::createDiagnostics(new DiagnosticOptions());
3354 std::unique_ptr<ASTUnit> AU = ASTUnit::LoadFromASTFile(
3355 ast_filename, CXXIdx->getPCHContainerOperations()->getRawReader(),
3356 ASTUnit::LoadEverything, Diags,
3357 FileSystemOpts, /*UseDebugInfo=*/false,
3358 CXXIdx->getOnlyLocalDecls(), None,
3359 CaptureDiagsKind::All,
3360 /*AllowPCHWithCompilerErrors=*/true,
3361 /*UserFilesAreVolatile=*/true);
3362 *out_TU = MakeCXTranslationUnit(CXXIdx, std::move(AU));
3363 return *out_TU ? CXError_Success : CXError_Failure;
3364}
3365
3366unsigned clang_defaultEditingTranslationUnitOptions() {
3367 return CXTranslationUnit_PrecompiledPreamble |
3368 CXTranslationUnit_CacheCompletionResults;
3369}
3370
3371CXTranslationUnit
3372clang_createTranslationUnitFromSourceFile(CXIndex CIdx,
3373 const char *source_filename,
3374 int num_command_line_args,
3375 const char * const *command_line_args,
3376 unsigned num_unsaved_files,
3377 struct CXUnsavedFile *unsaved_files) {
3378 unsigned Options = CXTranslationUnit_DetailedPreprocessingRecord;
3379 return clang_parseTranslationUnit(CIdx, source_filename,
3380 command_line_args, num_command_line_args,
3381 unsaved_files, num_unsaved_files,
3382 Options);
3383}
3384
3385static CXErrorCode
3386clang_parseTranslationUnit_Impl(CXIndex CIdx, const char *source_filename,
3387 const char *const *command_line_args,
3388 int num_command_line_args,
3389 ArrayRef<CXUnsavedFile> unsaved_files,
3390 unsigned options, CXTranslationUnit *out_TU) {
3391 // Set up the initial return values.
3392 if (out_TU)
3393 *out_TU = nullptr;
3394
3395 // Check arguments.
3396 if (!CIdx || !out_TU)
3397 return CXError_InvalidArguments;
3398
3399 CIndexer *CXXIdx = static_cast<CIndexer *>(CIdx);
3400
3401 if (CXXIdx->isOptEnabled(CXGlobalOpt_ThreadBackgroundPriorityForIndexing))
3402 setThreadBackgroundPriority();
3403
3404 bool PrecompilePreamble = options & CXTranslationUnit_PrecompiledPreamble;
3405 bool CreatePreambleOnFirstParse =
3406 options & CXTranslationUnit_CreatePreambleOnFirstParse;
3407 // FIXME: Add a flag for modules.
3408 TranslationUnitKind TUKind
3409 = (options & (CXTranslationUnit_Incomplete |
3410 CXTranslationUnit_SingleFileParse))? TU_Prefix : TU_Complete;
3411 bool CacheCodeCompletionResults
3412 = options & CXTranslationUnit_CacheCompletionResults;
3413 bool IncludeBriefCommentsInCodeCompletion
3414 = options & CXTranslationUnit_IncludeBriefCommentsInCodeCompletion;
3415 bool SingleFileParse = options & CXTranslationUnit_SingleFileParse;
3416 bool ForSerialization = options & CXTranslationUnit_ForSerialization;
3417 SkipFunctionBodiesScope SkipFunctionBodies = SkipFunctionBodiesScope::None;
3418 if (options & CXTranslationUnit_SkipFunctionBodies) {
3419 SkipFunctionBodies =
3420 (options & CXTranslationUnit_LimitSkipFunctionBodiesToPreamble)
3421 ? SkipFunctionBodiesScope::Preamble
3422 : SkipFunctionBodiesScope::PreambleAndMainFile;
3423 }
3424
3425 // Configure the diagnostics.
3426 IntrusiveRefCntPtr<DiagnosticsEngine>
3427 Diags(CompilerInstance::createDiagnostics(new DiagnosticOptions));
3428
3429 if (options & CXTranslationUnit_KeepGoing)
3430 Diags->setFatalsAsError(true);
3431
3432 CaptureDiagsKind CaptureDiagnostics = CaptureDiagsKind::All;
3433 if (options & CXTranslationUnit_IgnoreNonErrorsFromIncludedFiles)
3434 CaptureDiagnostics = CaptureDiagsKind::AllWithoutNonErrorsFromIncludes;
3435
3436 // Recover resources if we crash before exiting this function.
3437 llvm::CrashRecoveryContextCleanupRegistrar<DiagnosticsEngine,
3438 llvm::CrashRecoveryContextReleaseRefCleanup<DiagnosticsEngine> >
3439 DiagCleanup(Diags.get());
3440
3441 std::unique_ptr<std::vector<ASTUnit::RemappedFile>> RemappedFiles(
3442 new std::vector<ASTUnit::RemappedFile>());
3443
3444 // Recover resources if we crash before exiting this function.
3445 llvm::CrashRecoveryContextCleanupRegistrar<
3446 std::vector<ASTUnit::RemappedFile> > RemappedCleanup(RemappedFiles.get());
3447
3448 for (auto &UF : unsaved_files) {
3449 std::unique_ptr<llvm::MemoryBuffer> MB =
3450 llvm::MemoryBuffer::getMemBufferCopy(getContents(UF), UF.Filename);
3451 RemappedFiles->push_back(std::make_pair(UF.Filename, MB.release()));
3452 }
3453
3454 std::unique_ptr<std::vector<const char *>> Args(
3455 new std::vector<const char *>());
3456
3457 // Recover resources if we crash before exiting this method.
3458 llvm::CrashRecoveryContextCleanupRegistrar<std::vector<const char*> >
3459 ArgsCleanup(Args.get());
3460
3461 // Since the Clang C library is primarily used by batch tools dealing with
3462 // (often very broken) source code, where spell-checking can have a
3463 // significant negative impact on performance (particularly when
3464 // precompiled headers are involved), we disable it by default.
3465 // Only do this if we haven't found a spell-checking-related argument.
3466 bool FoundSpellCheckingArgument = false;
3467 for (int I = 0; I != num_command_line_args; ++I) {
3468 if (strcmp(command_line_args[I], "-fno-spell-checking") == 0 ||
3469 strcmp(command_line_args[I], "-fspell-checking") == 0) {
3470 FoundSpellCheckingArgument = true;
3471 break;
3472 }
3473 }
3474 Args->insert(Args->end(), command_line_args,
3475 command_line_args + num_command_line_args);
3476
3477 if (!FoundSpellCheckingArgument)
3478 Args->insert(Args->begin() + 1, "-fno-spell-checking");
3479
3480 // The 'source_filename' argument is optional. If the caller does not
3481 // specify it then it is assumed that the source file is specified
3482 // in the actual argument list.
3483 // Put the source file after command_line_args otherwise if '-x' flag is
3484 // present it will be unused.
3485 if (source_filename)
3486 Args->push_back(source_filename);
3487
3488 // Do we need the detailed preprocessing record?
3489 if (options & CXTranslationUnit_DetailedPreprocessingRecord) {
3490 Args->push_back("-Xclang");
3491 Args->push_back("-detailed-preprocessing-record");
3492 }
3493
3494 // Suppress any editor placeholder diagnostics.
3495 Args->push_back("-fallow-editor-placeholders");
3496
3497 unsigned NumErrors = Diags->getClient()->getNumErrors();
3498 std::unique_ptr<ASTUnit> ErrUnit;
3499 // Unless the user specified that they want the preamble on the first parse
3500 // set it up to be created on the first reparse. This makes the first parse
3501 // faster, trading for a slower (first) reparse.
3502 unsigned PrecompilePreambleAfterNParses =
3503 !PrecompilePreamble ? 0 : 2 - CreatePreambleOnFirstParse;
3504
3505 LibclangInvocationReporter InvocationReporter(
3506 *CXXIdx, LibclangInvocationReporter::OperationKind::ParseOperation,
3507 options, llvm::makeArrayRef(*Args), /*InvocationArgs=*/None,
3508 unsaved_files);
3509 std::unique_ptr<ASTUnit> Unit(ASTUnit::LoadFromCommandLine(
3510 Args->data(), Args->data() + Args->size(),
3511 CXXIdx->getPCHContainerOperations(), Diags,
3512 CXXIdx->getClangResourcesPath(), CXXIdx->getOnlyLocalDecls(),
3513 CaptureDiagnostics, *RemappedFiles.get(),
3514 /*RemappedFilesKeepOriginalName=*/true, PrecompilePreambleAfterNParses,
3515 TUKind, CacheCodeCompletionResults, IncludeBriefCommentsInCodeCompletion,
3516 /*AllowPCHWithCompilerErrors=*/true, SkipFunctionBodies, SingleFileParse,
3517 /*UserFilesAreVolatile=*/true, ForSerialization,
3518 CXXIdx->getPCHContainerOperations()->getRawReader().getFormat(),
3519 &ErrUnit));
3520
3521 // Early failures in LoadFromCommandLine may return with ErrUnit unset.
3522 if (!Unit && !ErrUnit)
3523 return CXError_ASTReadError;
3524
3525 if (NumErrors != Diags->getClient()->getNumErrors()) {
3526 // Make sure to check that 'Unit' is non-NULL.
3527 if (CXXIdx->getDisplayDiagnostics())
3528 printDiagsToStderr(Unit ? Unit.get() : ErrUnit.get());
3529 }
3530
3531 if (isASTReadError(Unit ? Unit.get() : ErrUnit.get()))
3532 return CXError_ASTReadError;
3533
3534 *out_TU = MakeCXTranslationUnit(CXXIdx, std::move(Unit));
3535 if (CXTranslationUnitImpl *TU = *out_TU) {
3536 TU->ParsingOptions = options;
3537 TU->Arguments.reserve(Args->size());
3538 for (const char *Arg : *Args)
3539 TU->Arguments.push_back(Arg);
3540 return CXError_Success;
3541 }
3542 return CXError_Failure;
3543}
3544
3545CXTranslationUnit
3546clang_parseTranslationUnit(CXIndex CIdx,
3547 const char *source_filename,
3548 const char *const *command_line_args,
3549 int num_command_line_args,
3550 struct CXUnsavedFile *unsaved_files,
3551 unsigned num_unsaved_files,
3552 unsigned options) {
3553 CXTranslationUnit TU;
3554 enum CXErrorCode Result = clang_parseTranslationUnit2(
3555 CIdx, source_filename, command_line_args, num_command_line_args,
3556 unsaved_files, num_unsaved_files, options, &TU);
3557 (void)Result;
3558 assert((TU && Result == CXError_Success) ||
3559 (!TU && Result != CXError_Success));
3560 return TU;
3561}
3562
3563enum CXErrorCode clang_parseTranslationUnit2(
3564 CXIndex CIdx, const char *source_filename,
3565 const char *const *command_line_args, int num_command_line_args,
3566 struct CXUnsavedFile *unsaved_files, unsigned num_unsaved_files,
3567 unsigned options, CXTranslationUnit *out_TU) {
3568 SmallVector<const char *, 4> Args;
3569 Args.push_back("clang");
3570 Args.append(command_line_args, command_line_args + num_command_line_args);
3571 return clang_parseTranslationUnit2FullArgv(
3572 CIdx, source_filename, Args.data(), Args.size(), unsaved_files,
3573 num_unsaved_files, options, out_TU);
3574}
3575
3576enum CXErrorCode clang_parseTranslationUnit2FullArgv(
3577 CXIndex CIdx, const char *source_filename,
3578 const char *const *command_line_args, int num_command_line_args,
3579 struct CXUnsavedFile *unsaved_files, unsigned num_unsaved_files,
3580 unsigned options, CXTranslationUnit *out_TU) {
3581 LOG_FUNC_SECTION {
3582 *Log << source_filename << ": ";
3583 for (int i = 0; i != num_command_line_args; ++i)
3584 *Log << command_line_args[i] << " ";
3585 }
3586
3587 if (num_unsaved_files && !unsaved_files)
3588 return CXError_InvalidArguments;
3589
3590 CXErrorCode result = CXError_Failure;
3591 auto ParseTranslationUnitImpl = [=, &result] {
3592 result = clang_parseTranslationUnit_Impl(
3593 CIdx, source_filename, command_line_args, num_command_line_args,
3594 llvm::makeArrayRef(unsaved_files, num_unsaved_files), options, out_TU);
3595 };
3596
3597 llvm::CrashRecoveryContext CRC;
3598
3599 if (!RunSafely(CRC, ParseTranslationUnitImpl)) {
3600 fprintf(stderr, "libclang: crash detected during parsing: {\n");
3601 fprintf(stderr, " 'source_filename' : '%s'\n", source_filename);
3602 fprintf(stderr, " 'command_line_args' : [");
3603 for (int i = 0; i != num_command_line_args; ++i) {
3604 if (i)
3605 fprintf(stderr, ", ");
3606 fprintf(stderr, "'%s'", command_line_args[i]);
3607 }
3608 fprintf(stderr, "],\n");
3609 fprintf(stderr, " 'unsaved_files' : [");
3610 for (unsigned i = 0; i != num_unsaved_files; ++i) {
3611 if (i)
3612 fprintf(stderr, ", ");
3613 fprintf(stderr, "('%s', '...', %ld)", unsaved_files[i].Filename,
3614 unsaved_files[i].Length);
3615 }
3616 fprintf(stderr, "],\n");
3617 fprintf(stderr, " 'options' : %d,\n", options);
3618 fprintf(stderr, "}\n");
3619
3620 return CXError_Crashed;
3621 } else if (getenv("LIBCLANG_RESOURCE_USAGE")) {
3622 if (CXTranslationUnit *TU = out_TU)
3623 PrintLibclangResourceUsage(*TU);
3624 }
3625
3626 return result;
3627}

3629CXString clang_Type_getObjCEncoding(CXType CT) {
3630 CXTranslationUnit tu = static_cast<CXTranslationUnit>(CT.data[1]);
3631 ASTContext &Ctx = getASTUnit(tu)->getASTContext();
3632 std::string encoding;
3633 Ctx.getObjCEncodingForType(QualType::getFromOpaquePtr(CT.data[0]),
3634 encoding);
3635
3636 return cxstring::createDup(encoding);
3637}

3639static const IdentifierInfo *getMacroIdentifier(CXCursor C) {
3640 if (C.kind == CXCursor_MacroDefinition) {
3641 if (const MacroDefinitionRecord *MDR = getCursorMacroDefinition(C))
3642 return MDR->getName();
3643 } else if (C.kind == CXCursor_MacroExpansion) {
3644 MacroExpansionCursor ME = getCursorMacroExpansion(C);
3645 return ME.getName();
3646 }
3647 return nullptr;
3648}
3649
3650unsigned clang_Cursor_isMacroFunctionLike(CXCursor C) {
3651 const IdentifierInfo *II = getMacroIdentifier(C);
3652 if (!II) {
3653 return false;
3654 }
3655 ASTUnit *ASTU = getCursorASTUnit(C);
3656 Preprocessor &PP = ASTU->getPreprocessor();
3657 if (const MacroInfo *MI = PP.getMacroInfo(II))
3658 return MI->isFunctionLike();
3659 return false;
3660}
3661
3662unsigned clang_Cursor_isMacroBuiltin(CXCursor C) {
3663 const IdentifierInfo *II = getMacroIdentifier(C);
3664 if (!II) {
3665 return false;
3666 }
3667 ASTUnit *ASTU = getCursorASTUnit(C);
3668 Preprocessor &PP = ASTU->getPreprocessor();
3669 if (const MacroInfo *MI = PP.getMacroInfo(II))
3670 return MI->isBuiltinMacro();
3671 return false;
3672}
3673
3674unsigned clang_Cursor_isFunctionInlined(CXCursor C) {
3675 const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(C);
3676 const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(D);
3677 if (!FD) {
3678 return false;
3679 }
3680 return FD->isInlined();
3681}
3682
3683static StringLiteral* getCFSTR_value(CallExpr *callExpr) {
3684 if (callExpr->getNumArgs() != 1) {
3685 return nullptr;
3686 }
3687
3688 StringLiteral *S = nullptr;
3689 auto *arg = callExpr->getArg(0);
3690 if (arg->getStmtClass() == Stmt::ImplicitCastExprClass) {
3691 ImplicitCastExpr *I = static_cast<ImplicitCastExpr *>(arg);
3692 auto *subExpr = I->getSubExprAsWritten();
3693
3694 if(subExpr->getStmtClass() != Stmt::StringLiteralClass){
3695 return nullptr;
3696 }
3697
3698 S = static_cast<StringLiteral *>(I->getSubExprAsWritten());
3699 } else if (arg->getStmtClass() == Stmt::StringLiteralClass) {
3700 S = static_cast<StringLiteral *>(callExpr->getArg(0));
3701 } else {
3702 return nullptr;
3703 }
3704 return S;
3705}
3706
3707struct ExprEvalResult {
3708 CXEvalResultKind EvalType;
3709 union {
3710 unsigned long long unsignedVal;
3711 long long intVal;
3712 double floatVal;
3713 char *stringVal;
3714 } EvalData;
3715 bool IsUnsignedInt;
3716 ~ExprEvalResult() {
3717 if (EvalType != CXEval_UnExposed && EvalType != CXEval_Float &&
3718 EvalType != CXEval_Int) {
3719 delete[] EvalData.stringVal;
3720 }
3721 }
3722};
3723
3724void clang_EvalResult_dispose(CXEvalResult E) {
3725 delete static_cast<ExprEvalResult *>(E);
3726}
3727
3728CXEvalResultKind clang_EvalResult_getKind(CXEvalResult E) {
3729 if (!E) {
3730 return CXEval_UnExposed;
3731 }
3732 return ((ExprEvalResult *)E)->EvalType;
3733}
3734
3735int clang_EvalResult_getAsInt(CXEvalResult E) {
3736 return clang_EvalResult_getAsLongLong(E);
3737}
3738
3739long long clang_EvalResult_getAsLongLong(CXEvalResult E) {
3740 if (!E) {
3741 return 0;
3742 }
3743 ExprEvalResult *Result = (ExprEvalResult*)E;
3744 if (Result->IsUnsignedInt)
3745 return Result->EvalData.unsignedVal;
3746 return Result->EvalData.intVal;
3747}
3748
3749unsigned clang_EvalResult_isUnsignedInt(CXEvalResult E) {
3750 return ((ExprEvalResult *)E)->IsUnsignedInt;
3751}
3752
3753unsigned long long clang_EvalResult_getAsUnsigned(CXEvalResult E) {
3754 if (!E) {
3755 return 0;
3756 }
3757
3758 ExprEvalResult *Result = (ExprEvalResult*)E;
3759 if (Result->IsUnsignedInt)
3760 return Result->EvalData.unsignedVal;
3761 return Result->EvalData.intVal;
3762}
3763
3764double clang_EvalResult_getAsDouble(CXEvalResult E) {
3765 if (!E) {
3766 return 0;
3767 }
3768 return ((ExprEvalResult *)E)->EvalData.floatVal;
3769}
3770
3771const char* clang_EvalResult_getAsStr(CXEvalResult E) {
3772 if (!E) {
3773 return nullptr;
3774 }
3775 return ((ExprEvalResult *)E)->EvalData.stringVal;
3776}
3777
3778static const ExprEvalResult* evaluateExpr(Expr *expr, CXCursor C) {
3779 Expr::EvalResult ER;
3780 ASTContext &ctx = getCursorContext(C);
3781 if (!expr)
3782 return nullptr;
3783
3784 expr = expr->IgnoreParens();
3785 if (!expr->EvaluateAsRValue(ER, ctx))
3786 return nullptr;
3787
3788 QualType rettype;
3789 CallExpr *callExpr;
3790 auto result = llvm::make_unique<ExprEvalResult>();
3791 result->EvalType = CXEval_UnExposed;
3792 result->IsUnsignedInt = false;
3793
3794 if (ER.Val.isInt()) {
3795 result->EvalType = CXEval_Int;
3796
3797 auto& val = ER.Val.getInt();
3798 if (val.isUnsigned()) {
3799 result->IsUnsignedInt = true;
3800 result->EvalData.unsignedVal = val.getZExtValue();
3801 } else {
3802 result->EvalData.intVal = val.getExtValue();
3803 }
3804
3805 return result.release();
3806 }
3807
3808 if (ER.Val.isFloat()) {
3809 llvm::SmallVector<char, 100> Buffer;
3810 ER.Val.getFloat().toString(Buffer);
3811 std::string floatStr(Buffer.data(), Buffer.size());
3812 result->EvalType = CXEval_Float;
3813 bool ignored;
3814 llvm::APFloat apFloat = ER.Val.getFloat();
3815 apFloat.convert(llvm::APFloat::IEEEdouble(),
3816 llvm::APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &ignored);
3817 result->EvalData.floatVal = apFloat.convertToDouble();
3818 return result.release();
3819 }
3820
3821 if (expr->getStmtClass() == Stmt::ImplicitCastExprClass) {
3822 const ImplicitCastExpr *I = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(expr);
3823 auto *subExpr = I->getSubExprAsWritten();
3824 if (subExpr->getStmtClass() == Stmt::StringLiteralClass ||
3825 subExpr->getStmtClass() == Stmt::ObjCStringLiteralClass) {
3826 const StringLiteral *StrE = nullptr;
3827 const ObjCStringLiteral *ObjCExpr;
3828 ObjCExpr = dyn_cast<ObjCStringLiteral>(subExpr);
3829
3830 if (ObjCExpr) {
3831 StrE = ObjCExpr->getString();
3832 result->EvalType = CXEval_ObjCStrLiteral;
3833 } else {
3834 StrE = cast<StringLiteral>(I->getSubExprAsWritten());
3835 result->EvalType = CXEval_StrLiteral;
3836 }
3837
3838 std::string strRef(StrE->getString().str());
3839 result->EvalData.stringVal = new char[strRef.size() + 1];
3840 strncpy((char *)result->EvalData.stringVal, strRef.c_str(),
3841 strRef.size());
3842 result->EvalData.stringVal[strRef.size()] = '\0';
3843 return result.release();
3844 }
3845 } else if (expr->getStmtClass() == Stmt::ObjCStringLiteralClass ||
3846 expr->getStmtClass() == Stmt::StringLiteralClass) {
3847 const StringLiteral *StrE = nullptr;
3848 const ObjCStringLiteral *ObjCExpr;
3849 ObjCExpr = dyn_cast<ObjCStringLiteral>(expr);
3850
3851 if (ObjCExpr) {
3852 StrE = ObjCExpr->getString();
3853 result->EvalType = CXEval_ObjCStrLiteral;
3854 } else {
3855 StrE = cast<StringLiteral>(expr);
3856 result->EvalType = CXEval_StrLiteral;
3857 }
3858
3859 std::string strRef(StrE->getString().str());
3860 result->EvalData.stringVal = new char[strRef.size() + 1];
3861 strncpy((char *)result->EvalData.stringVal, strRef.c_str(), strRef.size());
3862 result->EvalData.stringVal[strRef.size()] = '\0';
3863 return result.release();
3864 }
3865
3866 if (expr->getStmtClass() == Stmt::CStyleCastExprClass) {
3867 CStyleCastExpr *CC = static_cast<CStyleCastExpr *>(expr);
3868
3869 rettype = CC->getType();
3870 if (rettype.getAsString() == "CFStringRef" &&
3871 CC->getSubExpr()->getStmtClass() == Stmt::CallExprClass) {
3872
3873 callExpr = static_cast<CallExpr *>(CC->getSubExpr());
3874 StringLiteral *S = getCFSTR_value(callExpr);
3875 if (S) {
3876 std::string strLiteral(S->getString().str());
3877 result->EvalType = CXEval_CFStr;
3878
3879 result->EvalData.stringVal = new char[strLiteral.size() + 1];
3880 strncpy((char *)result->EvalData.stringVal, strLiteral.c_str(),
3881 strLiteral.size());
3882 result->EvalData.stringVal[strLiteral.size()] = '\0';
3883 return result.release();
3884 }
3885 }
3886
3887 } else if (expr->getStmtClass() == Stmt::CallExprClass) {
3888 callExpr = static_cast<CallExpr *>(expr);
3889 rettype = callExpr->getCallReturnType(ctx);
3890
3891 if (rettype->isVectorType() || callExpr->getNumArgs() > 1)
3892 return nullptr;
3893
3894 if (rettype->isIntegralType(ctx) || rettype->isRealFloatingType()) {
3895 if (callExpr->getNumArgs() == 1 &&
3896 !callExpr->getArg(0)->getType()->isIntegralType(ctx))
3897 return nullptr;
3898 } else if (rettype.getAsString() == "CFStringRef") {
3899
3900 StringLiteral *S = getCFSTR_value(callExpr);
3901 if (S) {
3902 std::string strLiteral(S->getString().str());
3903 result->EvalType = CXEval_CFStr;
3904 result->EvalData.stringVal = new char[strLiteral.size() + 1];
3905 strncpy((char *)result->EvalData.stringVal, strLiteral.c_str(),
3906 strLiteral.size());
3907 result->EvalData.stringVal[strLiteral.size()] = '\0';
3908 return result.release();
3909 }
3910 }
3911 } else if (expr->getStmtClass() == Stmt::DeclRefExprClass) {
3912 DeclRefExpr *D = static_cast<DeclRefExpr *>(expr);
3913 ValueDecl *V = D->getDecl();
3914 if (V->getKind() == Decl::Function) {
3915 std::string strName = V->getNameAsString();
3916 result->EvalType = CXEval_Other;
3917 result->EvalData.stringVal = new char[strName.size() + 1];
3918 strncpy(result->EvalData.stringVal, strName.c_str(), strName.size());
3919 result->EvalData.stringVal[strName.size()] = '\0';
3920 return result.release();
3921 }
3922 }
3923
3924 return nullptr;
3925}
3926
3927static const Expr *evaluateDeclExpr(const Decl *D) {
3928 if (!D)
3929 return nullptr;
3930 if (auto *Var = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D))
3931 return Var->getInit();
3932 else if (auto *Field = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(D))
3933 return Field->getInClassInitializer();
3934 return nullptr;
3935}
3936
3937static const Expr *evaluateCompoundStmtExpr(const CompoundStmt *CS) {
3938 assert(CS && "invalid compound statement");
3939 for (auto *bodyIterator : CS->body()) {
3940 if (const auto *E = dyn_cast<Expr>(bodyIterator))
3941 return E;
3942 }
3943 return nullptr;
3944}
3945
3946CXEvalResult clang_Cursor_Evaluate(CXCursor C) {
3947 if (const Expr *E =
3948 clang_getCursorKind(C) == CXCursor_CompoundStmt
3949 ? evaluateCompoundStmtExpr(cast<CompoundStmt>(getCursorStmt(C)))
3950 : evaluateDeclExpr(getCursorDecl(C)))
3951 return const_cast<CXEvalResult>(
3952 reinterpret_cast<const void *>(evaluateExpr(const_cast<Expr *>(E), C)));
3953 return nullptr;
3954}
3955
3956unsigned clang_Cursor_hasAttrs(CXCursor C) {
3957 const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(C);
3958 if (!D) {
3959 return 0;
3960 }
3961
3962 if (D->hasAttrs()) {
3963 return 1;
3964 }
3965
3966 return 0;
3967}
3968unsigned clang_defaultSaveOptions(CXTranslationUnit TU) {
3969 return CXSaveTranslationUnit_None;
3970}
3971
3972static CXSaveError clang_saveTranslationUnit_Impl(CXTranslationUnit TU,
3973 const char *FileName,
3974 unsigned options) {
3975 CIndexer *CXXIdx = TU->CIdx;
3976 if (CXXIdx->isOptEnabled(CXGlobalOpt_ThreadBackgroundPriorityForIndexing))
3977 setThreadBackgroundPriority();
3978
3979 bool hadError = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU)->Save(FileName);
3980 return hadError ? CXSaveError_Unknown : CXSaveError_None;
3981}
3982
3983int clang_saveTranslationUnit(CXTranslationUnit TU, const char *FileName,
3984 unsigned options) {
3985 LOG_FUNC_SECTION {
3986 *Log << TU << ' ' << FileName;
3987 }
3988
3989 if (isNotUsableTU(TU)) {
3990 LOG_BAD_TU(TU);
3991 return CXSaveError_InvalidTU;
3992 }
3993
3994 ASTUnit *CXXUnit = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU);
3995 ASTUnit::ConcurrencyCheck Check(*CXXUnit);
3996 if (!CXXUnit->hasSema())
3997 return CXSaveError_InvalidTU;
3998
3999 CXSaveError result;
4000 auto SaveTranslationUnitImpl = [=, &result]() {
4001 result = clang_saveTranslationUnit_Impl(TU, FileName, options);
4002 };
4003
4004 if (!CXXUnit->getDiagnostics().hasUnrecoverableErrorOccurred()) {
4005 SaveTranslationUnitImpl();
4006
4007 if (getenv("LIBCLANG_RESOURCE_USAGE"))
4008 PrintLibclangResourceUsage(TU);
4009
4010 return result;
4011 }
4012
4013 // We have an AST that has invalid nodes due to compiler errors.
4014 // Use a crash recovery thread for protection.
4015
4016 llvm::CrashRecoveryContext CRC;
4017
4018 if (!RunSafely(CRC, SaveTranslationUnitImpl)) {
4019 fprintf(stderr, "libclang: crash detected during AST saving: {\n");
4020 fprintf(stderr, " 'filename' : '%s'\n", FileName);
4021 fprintf(stderr, " 'options' : %d,\n", options);
4022 fprintf(stderr, "}\n");
4023
4024 return CXSaveError_Unknown;
4025
4026 } else if (getenv("LIBCLANG_RESOURCE_USAGE")) {
4027 PrintLibclangResourceUsage(TU);
4028 }
4029
4030 return result;
4031}
4032
4033void clang_disposeTranslationUnit(CXTranslationUnit CTUnit) {
4034 if (CTUnit) {
4035 // If the translation unit has been marked as unsafe to free, just discard
4036 // it.
4037 ASTUnit *Unit = cxtu::getASTUnit(CTUnit);
4038 if (Unit && Unit->isUnsafeToFree())
4039 return;
4040
4041 delete cxtu::getASTUnit(CTUnit);
4042 delete CTUnit->StringPool;
4043 delete static_cast<CXDiagnosticSetImpl *>(CTUnit->Diagnostics);
4044 disposeOverridenCXCursorsPool(CTUnit->OverridenCursorsPool);
4045 delete CTUnit->CommentToXML;
4046 delete CTUnit;
4047 }
4048}
4049
4050unsigned clang_suspendTranslationUnit(CXTranslationUnit CTUnit) {
4051 if (CTUnit) {
4052 ASTUnit *Unit = cxtu::getASTUnit(CTUnit);
4053
4054 if (Unit && Unit->isUnsafeToFree())
4055 return false;
4056
4057 Unit->ResetForParse();
4058 return true;
4059 }
4060
4061 return false;
4062}
4063
4064unsigned clang_defaultReparseOptions(CXTranslationUnit TU) {
4065 return CXReparse_None;
4066}
4067
4068static CXErrorCode
4069clang_reparseTranslationUnit_Impl(CXTranslationUnit TU,
4070 ArrayRef<CXUnsavedFile> unsaved_files,
4071 unsigned options) {
4072 // Check arguments.
4073 if (isNotUsableTU(TU)) {
4074 LOG_BAD_TU(TU);
4075 return CXError_InvalidArguments;
4076 }
4077
4078 // Reset the associated diagnostics.
4079 delete static_cast<CXDiagnosticSetImpl*>(TU->Diagnostics);
4080 TU->Diagnostics = nullptr;
4081
4082 CIndexer *CXXIdx = TU->CIdx;
4083 if (CXXIdx->isOptEnabled(CXGlobalOpt_ThreadBackgroundPriorityForEditing))
4084 setThreadBackgroundPriority();
4085
4086 ASTUnit *CXXUnit = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU);
4087 ASTUnit::ConcurrencyCheck Check(*CXXUnit);
4088
4089 std::unique_ptr<std::vector<ASTUnit::RemappedFile>> RemappedFiles(
4090 new std::vector<ASTUnit::RemappedFile>());
4091
4092 // Recover resources if we crash before exiting this function.
4093 llvm::CrashRecoveryContextCleanupRegistrar<
4094 std::vector<ASTUnit::RemappedFile> > RemappedCleanup(RemappedFiles.get());
4095
4096 for (auto &UF : unsaved_files) {
4097 std::unique_ptr<llvm::MemoryBuffer> MB =
4098 llvm::MemoryBuffer::getMemBufferCopy(getContents(UF), UF.Filename);
4099 RemappedFiles->push_back(std::make_pair(UF.Filename, MB.release()));
4100 }
4101
4102 if (!CXXUnit->Reparse(CXXIdx->getPCHContainerOperations(),
4103 *RemappedFiles.get()))
4104 return CXError_Success;
4105 if (isASTReadError(CXXUnit))
4106 return CXError_ASTReadError;
4107 return CXError_Failure;
4108}
4109
4110int clang_reparseTranslationUnit(CXTranslationUnit TU,
4111 unsigned num_unsaved_files,
4112 struct CXUnsavedFile *unsaved_files,
4113 unsigned options) {
4114 LOG_FUNC_SECTION {
4115 *Log << TU;
4116 }
4117
4118 if (num_unsaved_files && !unsaved_files)
4119 return CXError_InvalidArguments;
4120
4121 CXErrorCode result;
4122 auto ReparseTranslationUnitImpl = [=, &result]() {
4123 result = clang_reparseTranslationUnit_Impl(
4124 TU, llvm::makeArrayRef(unsaved_files, num_unsaved_files), options);
4125 };
4126
4127 llvm::CrashRecoveryContext CRC;
4128
4129 if (!RunSafely(CRC, ReparseTranslationUnitImpl)) {
4130 fprintf(stderr, "libclang: crash detected during reparsing\n");
4131 cxtu::getASTUnit(TU)->setUnsafeToFree(true);
4132 return CXError_Crashed;
4133 } else if (getenv("LIBCLANG_RESOURCE_USAGE"))
4134 PrintLibclangResourceUsage(TU);
4135
4136 return result;
4137}

4227 return nullptr;
4228 }
4229
4230 ASTUnit *CXXUnit = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU);

4235
4236const char *clang_getFileContents(CXTranslationUnit TU, CXFile file,
4237 size_t *size) {
4238 if (isNotUsableTU(TU)) {
4239 LOG_BAD_TU(TU);
4240 return nullptr;
4241 }
4242
4243 const SourceManager &SM = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU)->getSourceManager();
4244 FileID fid = SM.translateFile(static_cast<FileEntry *>(file));
4245 bool Invalid = true;
4246 const llvm::MemoryBuffer *buf = SM.getBuffer(fid, &Invalid);
4247 if (Invalid) {
4248 if (size)
4249 *size = 0;
4250 return nullptr;
4251 }
4252 if (size)
4253 *size = buf->getBufferSize();
4254 return buf->getBufferStart();
4255}

4257unsigned clang_isFileMultipleIncludeGuarded(CXTranslationUnit TU,
4258 CXFile file) {
4259 if (isNotUsableTU(TU)) {
4260 LOG_BAD_TU(TU);
4261 return 0;
4262 }
4263
4264 if (!file)
4265 return 0;
4266
4267 ASTUnit *CXXUnit = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU);
4268 FileEntry *FEnt = static_cast<FileEntry *>(file);
4269 return CXXUnit->getPreprocessor().getHeaderSearchInfo()
4270 .isFileMultipleIncludeGuarded(FEnt);
4271}
4272
4273int clang_getFileUniqueID(CXFile file, CXFileUniqueID *outID) {
4274 if (!file || !outID)
4275 return 1;
4276
4277 FileEntry *FEnt = static_cast<FileEntry *>(file);
4278 const llvm::sys::fs::UniqueID &ID = FEnt->getUniqueID();
4279 outID->data[0] = ID.getDevice();
4280 outID->data[1] = ID.getFile();
4281 outID->data[2] = FEnt->getModificationTime();
4282 return 0;
4283}
4284
4285int clang_File_isEqual(CXFile file1, CXFile file2) {
4286 if (file1 == file2)
4287 return true;
4288
4289 if (!file1 || !file2)
4290 return false;
4291
4292 FileEntry *FEnt1 = static_cast<FileEntry *>(file1);
4293 FileEntry *FEnt2 = static_cast<FileEntry *>(file2);
4294 return FEnt1->getUniqueID() == FEnt2->getUniqueID();
4295}

4302 return cxstring::createRef(FEnt->tryGetRealPathName());
4303}

4305//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//

4308
4309static const Decl *getDeclFromExpr(const Stmt *E) {
4310 if (const ImplicitCastExpr *CE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(E))
4311 return getDeclFromExpr(CE->getSubExpr());
4312
4313 if (const DeclRefExpr *RefExpr = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E))
4314 return RefExpr->getDecl();
4315 if (const MemberExpr *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E))
4316 return ME->getMemberDecl();
4317 if (const ObjCIvarRefExpr *RE = dyn_cast<ObjCIvarRefExpr>(E))
4318 return RE->getDecl();
4319 if (const ObjCPropertyRefExpr *PRE = dyn_cast<ObjCPropertyRefExpr>(E)) {
4320 if (PRE->isExplicitProperty())
4321 return PRE->getExplicitProperty();
4322 // It could be messaging both getter and setter as in:
4323 // ++myobj.myprop;
4324 // in which case prefer to associate the setter since it is less obvious
4325 // from inspecting the source that the setter is going to get called.
4326 if (PRE->isMessagingSetter())
4327 return PRE->getImplicitPropertySetter();
4328 return PRE->getImplicitPropertyGetter();
4329 }
4330 if (const PseudoObjectExpr *POE = dyn_cast<PseudoObjectExpr>(E))
4331 return getDeclFromExpr(POE->getSyntacticForm());
4332 if (const OpaqueValueExpr *OVE = dyn_cast<OpaqueValueExpr>(E))
4333 if (Expr *Src = OVE->getSourceExpr())
4334 return getDeclFromExpr(Src);
4335
4336 if (const CallExpr *CE = dyn_cast<CallExpr>(E))
4337 return getDeclFromExpr(CE->getCallee());
4338 if (const CXXConstructExpr *CE = dyn_cast<CXXConstructExpr>(E))
4339 if (!CE->isElidable())
4340 return CE->getConstructor();
4341 if (const CXXInheritedCtorInitExpr *CE =
4342 dyn_cast<CXXInheritedCtorInitExpr>(E))
4343 return CE->getConstructor();
4344 if (const ObjCMessageExpr *OME = dyn_cast<ObjCMessageExpr>(E))
4345 return OME->getMethodDecl();
4346
4347 if (const ObjCProtocolExpr *PE = dyn_cast<ObjCProtocolExpr>(E))
4348 return PE->getProtocol();
4349 if (const SubstNonTypeTemplateParmPackExpr *NTTP
4350 = dyn_cast<SubstNonTypeTemplateParmPackExpr>(E))
4351 return NTTP->getParameterPack();
4352 if (const SizeOfPackExpr *SizeOfPack = dyn_cast<SizeOfPackExpr>(E))
4353 if (isa<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(SizeOfPack->getPack()) ||
4354 isa<ParmVarDecl>(SizeOfPack->getPack()))
4355 return SizeOfPack->getPack();
4356
4357 return nullptr;
4358}
4359
4360static SourceLocation getLocationFromExpr(const Expr *E) {
4361 if (const ImplicitCastExpr *CE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(E))
4362 return getLocationFromExpr(CE->getSubExpr());
4363
4364 if (const ObjCMessageExpr *Msg = dyn_cast<ObjCMessageExpr>(E))
4365 return /*FIXME:*/Msg->getLeftLoc();
4366 if (const DeclRefExpr *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E))
4367 return DRE->getLocation();
4368 if (const MemberExpr *Member = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(E))
4369 return Member->getMemberLoc();
4370 if (const ObjCIvarRefExpr *Ivar = dyn_cast<ObjCIvarRefExpr>(E))
4371 return Ivar->getLocation();
4372 if (const SizeOfPackExpr *SizeOfPack = dyn_cast<SizeOfPackExpr>(E))
4373 return SizeOfPack->getPackLoc();
4374 if (const ObjCPropertyRefExpr *PropRef = dyn_cast<ObjCPropertyRefExpr>(E))
4375 return PropRef->getLocation();
4376
4377 return E->getBeginLoc();
4378}

4380extern "C" {
4381
4382unsigned clang_visitChildren(CXCursor parent,
4383 CXCursorVisitor visitor,
4384 CXClientData client_data) {
4385 CursorVisitor CursorVis(getCursorTU(parent), visitor, client_data,
4386 /*VisitPreprocessorLast=*/false);
4387 return CursorVis.VisitChildren(parent);
4388}
4389
4390#ifndef __has_feature
4391#define __has_feature(x) 0
4392#endif
4393#if __has_feature(blocks)
4394typedef enum CXChildVisitResult
4395 (^CXCursorVisitorBlock)(CXCursor cursor, CXCursor parent);
4396
4397static enum CXChildVisitResult visitWithBlock(CXCursor cursor, CXCursor parent,
4398 CXClientData client_data) {
4399 CXCursorVisitorBlock block = (CXCursorVisitorBlock)client_data;
4400 return block(cursor, parent);
4401}
4402#else
4403// If we are compiled with a compiler that doesn't have native blocks support,
4404// define and call the block manually, so the
4405typedef struct _CXChildVisitResult
4406{
4407 void *isa;
4408 int flags;
4409 int reserved;
4410 enum CXChildVisitResult(*invoke)(struct _CXChildVisitResult*, CXCursor,
4411 CXCursor);
4412} *CXCursorVisitorBlock;
4413
4414static enum CXChildVisitResult visitWithBlock(CXCursor cursor, CXCursor parent,
4415 CXClientData client_data) {
4416 CXCursorVisitorBlock block = (CXCursorVisitorBlock)client_data;
4417 return block->invoke(block, cursor, parent);
4418}
4419#endif
4420
4421
4422unsigned clang_visitChildrenWithBlock(CXCursor parent,
4423 CXCursorVisitorBlock block) {
4424 return clang_visitChildren(parent, visitWithBlock, block);
4425}
4426
4427static CXString getDeclSpelling(const Decl *D) {
4428 if (!D)
4429 return cxstring::createEmpty();
4430
4431 const NamedDecl *ND = dyn_cast<NamedDecl>(D);
4432 if (!ND) {
4433 if (const ObjCPropertyImplDecl *PropImpl =
4434 dyn_cast<ObjCPropertyImplDecl>(D))
4435 if (ObjCPropertyDecl *Property = PropImpl->getPropertyDecl())
4436 return cxstring::createDup(Property->getIdentifier()->getName());
4437
4438 if (const ImportDecl *ImportD = dyn_cast<ImportDecl>(D))
4439 if (Module *Mod = ImportD->getImportedModule())
4440 return cxstring::createDup(Mod->getFullModuleName());
4441
4442 return cxstring::createEmpty();
4443 }
4444
4445 if (const ObjCMethodDecl *OMD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(ND))
4446 return cxstring::createDup(OMD->getSelector().getAsString());
4447
4448 if (const ObjCCategoryImplDecl *CIMP = dyn_cast<ObjCCategoryImplDecl>(ND))
4449 // No, this isn't the same as the code below. getIdentifier() is non-virtual
4450 // and returns different names. NamedDecl returns the class name and
4451 // ObjCCategoryImplDecl returns the category name.
4452 return cxstring::createRef(CIMP->getIdentifier()->getNameStart());
4453
4454 if (isa<UsingDirectiveDecl>(D))
4455 return cxstring::createEmpty();
4456
4457 SmallString<1024> S;
4458 llvm::raw_svector_ostream os(S);
4459 ND->printName(os);
4460
4461 return cxstring::createDup(os.str());
4462}
4463
4464CXString clang_getCursorSpelling(CXCursor C) {
4465 if (clang_isTranslationUnit(C.kind))
4466 return clang_getTranslationUnitSpelling(getCursorTU(C));
4467
4468 if (clang_isReference(C.kind)) {
4469 switch (C.kind) {
4470 case CXCursor_ObjCSuperClassRef: {
4471 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Super = getCursorObjCSuperClassRef(C).first;
4472 return cxstring::createRef(Super->getIdentifier()->getNameStart());
4473 }
4474 case CXCursor_ObjCClassRef: {
4475 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Class = getCursorObjCClassRef(C).first;
4476 return cxstring::createRef(Class->getIdentifier()->getNameStart());
4477 }
4478 case CXCursor_ObjCProtocolRef: {
4479 const ObjCProtocolDecl *OID = getCursorObjCProtocolRef(C).first;
4480 assert(OID && "getCursorSpelling(): Missing protocol decl");
4481 return cxstring::createRef(OID->getIdentifier()->getNameStart());
4482 }
4483 case CXCursor_CXXBaseSpecifier: {
4484 const CXXBaseSpecifier *B = getCursorCXXBaseSpecifier(C);
4485 return cxstring::createDup(B->getType().getAsString());
4486 }
4487 case CXCursor_TypeRef: {
4488 const TypeDecl *Type = getCursorTypeRef(C).first;
4489 assert(Type && "Missing type decl");
4490
4491 return cxstring::createDup(getCursorContext(C).getTypeDeclType(Type).
4492 getAsString());
4493 }
4494 case CXCursor_TemplateRef: {
4495 const TemplateDecl *Template = getCursorTemplateRef(C).first;
4496 assert(Template && "Missing template decl");
4497
4498 return cxstring::createDup(Template->getNameAsString());
4499 }
4500
4501 case CXCursor_NamespaceRef: {
4502 const NamedDecl *NS = getCursorNamespaceRef(C).first;
4503 assert(NS && "Missing namespace decl");
4504
4505 return cxstring::createDup(NS->getNameAsString());
4506 }
4507
4508 case CXCursor_MemberRef: {
4509 const FieldDecl *Field = getCursorMemberRef(C).first;
4510 assert(Field && "Missing member decl");
4511
4512 return cxstring::createDup(Field->getNameAsString());
4513 }
4514
4515 case CXCursor_LabelRef: {
4516 const LabelStmt *Label = getCursorLabelRef(C).first;
4517 assert(Label && "Missing label");
4518
4519 return cxstring::createRef(Label->getName());
4520 }
4521
4522 case CXCursor_OverloadedDeclRef: {
4523 OverloadedDeclRefStorage Storage = getCursorOverloadedDeclRef(C).first;
4524 if (const Decl *D = Storage.dyn_cast<const Decl *>()) {
4525 if (const NamedDecl *ND = dyn_cast<NamedDecl>(D))
4526 return cxstring::createDup(ND->getNameAsString());
4527 return cxstring::createEmpty();
4528 }
4529 if (const OverloadExpr *E = Storage.dyn_cast<const OverloadExpr *>())
4530 return cxstring::createDup(E->getName().getAsString());
4531 OverloadedTemplateStorage *Ovl
4532 = Storage.get<OverloadedTemplateStorage*>();
4533 if (Ovl->size() == 0)
4534 return cxstring::createEmpty();
4535 return cxstring::createDup((*Ovl->begin())->getNameAsString());
4536 }
4537
4538 case CXCursor_VariableRef: {
4539 const VarDecl *Var = getCursorVariableRef(C).first;
4540 assert(Var && "Missing variable decl");
4541
4542 return cxstring::createDup(Var->getNameAsString());
4543 }
4544
4545 default:
4546 return cxstring::createRef("<not implemented>");
4547 }
4548 }
4549
4550 if (clang_isExpression(C.kind)) {
4551 const Expr *E = getCursorExpr(C);
4552
4553 if (C.kind == CXCursor_ObjCStringLiteral ||
4554 C.kind == CXCursor_StringLiteral) {
4555 const StringLiteral *SLit;
4556 if (const ObjCStringLiteral *OSL = dyn_cast<ObjCStringLiteral>(E)) {
4557 SLit = OSL->getString();
4558 } else {
4559 SLit = cast<StringLiteral>(E);
4560 }
4561 SmallString<256> Buf;
4562 llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(Buf);
4563 SLit->outputString(OS);
4564 return cxstring::createDup(OS.str());
4565 }
4566
4567 const Decl *D = getDeclFromExpr(getCursorExpr(C));
4568 if (D)
4569 return getDeclSpelling(D);
4570 return cxstring::createEmpty();
4571 }
4572
4573 if (clang_isStatement(C.kind)) {
4574 const Stmt *S = getCursorStmt(C);
4575 if (const LabelStmt *Label = dyn_cast_or_null<LabelStmt>(S))
4576 return cxstring::createRef(Label->getName());
4577
4578 return cxstring::createEmpty();
4579 }
4580
4581 if (C.kind == CXCursor_MacroExpansion)
4582 return cxstring::createRef(getCursorMacroExpansion(C).getName()
4583 ->getNameStart());
4584
4585 if (C.kind == CXCursor_MacroDefinition)
4586 return cxstring::createRef(getCursorMacroDefinition(C)->getName()
4587 ->getNameStart());
4588
4589 if (C.kind == CXCursor_InclusionDirective)
4590 return cxstring::createDup(getCursorInclusionDirective(C)->getFileName());
4591
4592 if (clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
4593 return getDeclSpelling(getCursorDecl(C));
4594
4595 if (C.kind == CXCursor_AnnotateAttr) {
4596 const AnnotateAttr *AA = cast<AnnotateAttr>(cxcursor::getCursorAttr(C));
4597 return cxstring::createDup(AA->getAnnotation());
4598 }
4599
4600 if (C.kind == CXCursor_AsmLabelAttr) {
4601 const AsmLabelAttr *AA = cast<AsmLabelAttr>(cxcursor::getCursorAttr(C));
4602 return cxstring::createDup(AA->getLabel());
4603 }
4604
4605 if (C.kind == CXCursor_PackedAttr) {
4606 return cxstring::createRef("packed");
4607 }
4608
4609 if (C.kind == CXCursor_VisibilityAttr) {
4610 const VisibilityAttr *AA = cast<VisibilityAttr>(cxcursor::getCursorAttr(C));
4611 switch (AA->getVisibility()) {
4612 case VisibilityAttr::VisibilityType::Default:
4613 return cxstring::createRef("default");
4614 case VisibilityAttr::VisibilityType::Hidden:
4615 return cxstring::createRef("hidden");
4616 case VisibilityAttr::VisibilityType::Protected:
4617 return cxstring::createRef("protected");
4618 }
4619 llvm_unreachable("unknown visibility type");
4620 }
4621
4622 return cxstring::createEmpty();
4623}
4624
4625CXSourceRange clang_Cursor_getSpellingNameRange(CXCursor C,
4626 unsigned pieceIndex,
4627 unsigned options) {
4628 if (clang_Cursor_isNull(C))
4629 return clang_getNullRange();
4630
4631 ASTContext &Ctx = getCursorContext(C);
4632
4633 if (clang_isStatement(C.kind)) {
4634 const Stmt *S = getCursorStmt(C);
4635 if (const LabelStmt *Label = dyn_cast_or_null<LabelStmt>(S)) {
4636 if (pieceIndex > 0)
4637 return clang_getNullRange();
4638 return cxloc::translateSourceRange(Ctx, Label->getIdentLoc());
4639 }
4640
4641 return clang_getNullRange();
4642 }
4643
4644 if (C.kind == CXCursor_ObjCMessageExpr) {
4645 if (const ObjCMessageExpr *
4646 ME = dyn_cast_or_null<ObjCMessageExpr>(getCursorExpr(C))) {
4647 if (pieceIndex >= ME->getNumSelectorLocs())
4648 return clang_getNullRange();
4649 return cxloc::translateSourceRange(Ctx, ME->getSelectorLoc(pieceIndex));
4650 }
4651 }
4652
4653 if (C.kind == CXCursor_ObjCInstanceMethodDecl ||
4654 C.kind == CXCursor_ObjCClassMethodDecl) {
4655 if (const ObjCMethodDecl *
4656 MD = dyn_cast_or_null<ObjCMethodDecl>(getCursorDecl(C))) {
4657 if (pieceIndex >= MD->getNumSelectorLocs())
4658 return clang_getNullRange();
4659 return cxloc::translateSourceRange(Ctx, MD->getSelectorLoc(pieceIndex));
4660 }
4661 }
4662
4663 if (C.kind == CXCursor_ObjCCategoryDecl ||
4664 C.kind == CXCursor_ObjCCategoryImplDecl) {
4665 if (pieceIndex > 0)
4666 return clang_getNullRange();
4667 if (const ObjCCategoryDecl *
4668 CD = dyn_cast_or_null<ObjCCategoryDecl>(getCursorDecl(C)))
4669 return cxloc::translateSourceRange(Ctx, CD->getCategoryNameLoc());
4670 if (const ObjCCategoryImplDecl *
4671 CID = dyn_cast_or_null<ObjCCategoryImplDecl>(getCursorDecl(C)))
4672 return cxloc::translateSourceRange(Ctx, CID->getCategoryNameLoc());
4673 }
4674
4675 if (C.kind == CXCursor_ModuleImportDecl) {
4676 if (pieceIndex > 0)
4677 return clang_getNullRange();
4678 if (const ImportDecl *ImportD =
4679 dyn_cast_or_null<ImportDecl>(getCursorDecl(C))) {
4680 ArrayRef<SourceLocation> Locs = ImportD->getIdentifierLocs();
4681 if (!Locs.empty())
4682 return cxloc::translateSourceRange(Ctx,
4683 SourceRange(Locs.front(), Locs.back()));
4684 }
4685 return clang_getNullRange();
4686 }
4687
4688 if (C.kind == CXCursor_CXXMethod || C.kind == CXCursor_Destructor ||
4689 C.kind == CXCursor_ConversionFunction ||
4690 C.kind == CXCursor_FunctionDecl) {
4691 if (pieceIndex > 0)
4692 return clang_getNullRange();
4693 if (const FunctionDecl *FD =
4694 dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(getCursorDecl(C))) {
4695 DeclarationNameInfo FunctionName = FD->getNameInfo();
4696 return cxloc::translateSourceRange(Ctx, FunctionName.getSourceRange());
4697 }
4698 return clang_getNullRange();
4699 }
4700
4701 // FIXME: A CXCursor_InclusionDirective should give the location of the
4702 // filename, but we don't keep track of this.
4703
4704 // FIXME: A CXCursor_AnnotateAttr should give the location of the annotation
4705 // but we don't keep track of this.
4706
4707 // FIXME: A CXCursor_AsmLabelAttr should give the location of the label
4708 // but we don't keep track of this.
4709
4710 // Default handling, give the location of the cursor.
4711
4712 if (pieceIndex > 0)
4713 return clang_getNullRange();
4714
4715 CXSourceLocation CXLoc = clang_getCursorLocation(C);
4716 SourceLocation Loc = cxloc::translateSourceLocation(CXLoc);
4717 return cxloc::translateSourceRange(Ctx, Loc);
4718}
4719
4720CXString clang_Cursor_getMangling(CXCursor C) {
4721 if (clang_isInvalid(C.kind) || !clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
4722 return cxstring::createEmpty();
4723
4724 // Mangling only works for functions and variables.
4725 const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(C);
4726 if (!D || !(isa<FunctionDecl>(D) || isa<VarDecl>(D)))
4727 return cxstring::createEmpty();
4728
4729 ASTContext &Ctx = D->getASTContext();
4730 index::CodegenNameGenerator CGNameGen(Ctx);
4731 return cxstring::createDup(CGNameGen.getName(D));
4732}
4733
4734CXStringSet *clang_Cursor_getCXXManglings(CXCursor C) {
4735 if (clang_isInvalid(C.kind) || !clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
4736 return nullptr;
4737
4738 const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(C);
4739 if (!(isa<CXXRecordDecl>(D) || isa<CXXMethodDecl>(D)))
4740 return nullptr;
4741
4742 ASTContext &Ctx = D->getASTContext();
4743 index::CodegenNameGenerator CGNameGen(Ctx);
4744 std::vector<std::string> Manglings = CGNameGen.getAllManglings(D);
4745 return cxstring::createSet(Manglings);
4746}
4747
4748CXStringSet *clang_Cursor_getObjCManglings(CXCursor C) {
4749 if (clang_isInvalid(C.kind) || !clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
4750 return nullptr;
4751
4752 const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(C);
4753 if (!(isa<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(D) || isa<ObjCImplementationDecl>(D)))
4754 return nullptr;
4755
4756 ASTContext &Ctx = D->getASTContext();
4757 index::CodegenNameGenerator CGNameGen(Ctx);
4758 std::vector<std::string> Manglings = CGNameGen.getAllManglings(D);
4759 return cxstring::createSet(Manglings);
4760}
4761
4762CXPrintingPolicy clang_getCursorPrintingPolicy(CXCursor C) {
4763 if (clang_Cursor_isNull(C))
4764 return 0;
4765 return new PrintingPolicy(getCursorContext(C).getPrintingPolicy());
4766}
4767
4768void clang_PrintingPolicy_dispose(CXPrintingPolicy Policy) {
4769 if (Policy)
4770 delete static_cast<PrintingPolicy *>(Policy);
4771}
4772
4773unsigned
4774clang_PrintingPolicy_getProperty(CXPrintingPolicy Policy,
4775 enum CXPrintingPolicyProperty Property) {
4776 if (!Policy)
4777 return 0;
4778
4779 PrintingPolicy *P = static_cast<PrintingPolicy *>(Policy);
4780 switch (Property) {
4781 case CXPrintingPolicy_Indentation:
4782 return P->Indentation;
4783 case CXPrintingPolicy_SuppressSpecifiers:
4784 return P->SuppressSpecifiers;
4785 case CXPrintingPolicy_SuppressTagKeyword:
4786 return P->SuppressTagKeyword;
4787 case CXPrintingPolicy_IncludeTagDefinition:
4788 return P->IncludeTagDefinition;
4789 case CXPrintingPolicy_SuppressScope:
4790 return P->SuppressScope;
4791 case CXPrintingPolicy_SuppressUnwrittenScope:
4792 return P->SuppressUnwrittenScope;
4793 case CXPrintingPolicy_SuppressInitializers:
4794 return P->SuppressInitializers;
4795 case CXPrintingPolicy_ConstantArraySizeAsWritten:
4796 return P->ConstantArraySizeAsWritten;
4797 case CXPrintingPolicy_AnonymousTagLocations:
4798 return P->AnonymousTagLocations;
4799 case CXPrintingPolicy_SuppressStrongLifetime:
4800 return P->SuppressStrongLifetime;
4801 case CXPrintingPolicy_SuppressLifetimeQualifiers:
4802 return P->SuppressLifetimeQualifiers;
4803 case CXPrintingPolicy_SuppressTemplateArgsInCXXConstructors:
4804 return P->SuppressTemplateArgsInCXXConstructors;
4805 case CXPrintingPolicy_Bool:
4806 return P->Bool;
4807 case CXPrintingPolicy_Restrict:
4808 return P->Restrict;
4809 case CXPrintingPolicy_Alignof:
4810 return P->Alignof;
4811 case CXPrintingPolicy_UnderscoreAlignof:
4812 return P->UnderscoreAlignof;
4813 case CXPrintingPolicy_UseVoidForZeroParams:
4814 return P->UseVoidForZeroParams;
4815 case CXPrintingPolicy_TerseOutput:
4816 return P->TerseOutput;
4817 case CXPrintingPolicy_PolishForDeclaration:
4818 return P->PolishForDeclaration;
4819 case CXPrintingPolicy_Half:
4820 return P->Half;
4821 case CXPrintingPolicy_MSWChar:
4822 return P->MSWChar;
4823 case CXPrintingPolicy_IncludeNewlines:
4824 return P->IncludeNewlines;
4825 case CXPrintingPolicy_MSVCFormatting:
4826 return P->MSVCFormatting;
4827 case CXPrintingPolicy_ConstantsAsWritten:
4828 return P->ConstantsAsWritten;
4829 case CXPrintingPolicy_SuppressImplicitBase:
4830 return P->SuppressImplicitBase;
4831 case CXPrintingPolicy_FullyQualifiedName:
4832 return P->FullyQualifiedName;
4833 }
4834
4835 assert(false && "Invalid CXPrintingPolicyProperty");
4836 return 0;
4837}

4871 case CXPrintingPolicy_AnonymousTagLocations:
4872 P->AnonymousTagLocations = Value;
4873 return;
4874 case CXPrintingPolicy_SuppressStrongLifetime:
4875 P->SuppressStrongLifetime = Value;
4876 return;
4877 case CXPrintingPolicy_SuppressLifetimeQualifiers:
4878 P->SuppressLifetimeQualifiers = Value;
4879 return;
4880 case CXPrintingPolicy_SuppressTemplateArgsInCXXConstructors:
4881 P->SuppressTemplateArgsInCXXConstructors = Value;
4882 return;
4883 case CXPrintingPolicy_Bool:
4884 P->Bool = Value;
4885 return;
4886 case CXPrintingPolicy_Restrict:
4887 P->Restrict = Value;
4888 return;

4929
4930CXString clang_getCursorPrettyPrinted(CXCursor C, CXPrintingPolicy cxPolicy) {
4931 if (clang_Cursor_isNull(C))
4932 return cxstring::createEmpty();
4933
4934 if (clang_isDeclaration(C.kind)) {
4935 const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(C);
4936 if (!D)
4937 return cxstring::createEmpty();
4938
4939 SmallString<128> Str;
4940 llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(Str);
4941 PrintingPolicy *UserPolicy = static_cast<PrintingPolicy *>(cxPolicy);
4942 D->print(OS, UserPolicy ? *UserPolicy
4943 : getCursorContext(C).getPrintingPolicy());
4944
4945 return cxstring::createDup(OS.str());
4946 }
4947
4948 return cxstring::createEmpty();
4949}
4950
4951CXString clang_getCursorDisplayName(CXCursor C) {
4952 if (!clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
4953 return clang_getCursorSpelling(C);
4954
4955 const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(C);
4956 if (!D)
4957 return cxstring::createEmpty();
4958
4959 PrintingPolicy Policy = getCursorContext(C).getPrintingPolicy();
4960 if (const FunctionTemplateDecl *FunTmpl = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D))
4961 D = FunTmpl->getTemplatedDecl();
4962
4963 if (const FunctionDecl *Function = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
4964 SmallString<64> Str;
4965 llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(Str);
4966 OS << *Function;
4967 if (Function->getPrimaryTemplate())
4968 OS << "<>";
4969 OS << "(";
4970 for (unsigned I = 0, N = Function->getNumParams(); I != N; ++I) {
4971 if (I)
4972 OS << ", ";
4973 OS << Function->getParamDecl(I)->getType().getAsString(Policy);
4974 }
4975
4976 if (Function->isVariadic()) {
4977 if (Function->getNumParams())
4978 OS << ", ";
4979 OS << "...";
4980 }
4981 OS << ")";
4982 return cxstring::createDup(OS.str());
4983 }
4984
4985 if (const ClassTemplateDecl *ClassTemplate = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateDecl>(D)) {
4986 SmallString<64> Str;
4987 llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(Str);
4988 OS << *ClassTemplate;
4989 OS << "<";
4990 TemplateParameterList *Params = ClassTemplate->getTemplateParameters();
4991 for (unsigned I = 0, N = Params->size(); I != N; ++I) {
4992 if (I)
4993 OS << ", ";
4994
4995 NamedDecl *Param = Params->getParam(I);
4996 if (Param->getIdentifier()) {
4997 OS << Param->getIdentifier()->getName();
4998 continue;
4999 }
5000
5001 // There is no parameter name, which makes this tricky. Try to come up
5002 // with something useful that isn't too long.
5003 if (TemplateTypeParmDecl *TTP = dyn_cast<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(Param))
5004 OS << (TTP->wasDeclaredWithTypename()? "typename" : "class");
5005 else if (NonTypeTemplateParmDecl *NTTP
5006 = dyn_cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(Param))
5007 OS << NTTP->getType().getAsString(Policy);
5008 else
5009 OS << "template<...> class";
5010 }
5011
5012 OS << ">";
5013 return cxstring::createDup(OS.str());
5014 }
5015
5016 if (const ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *ClassSpec
5017 = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(D)) {
5018 // If the type was explicitly written, use that.
5019 if (TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo = ClassSpec->getTypeAsWritten())
5020 return cxstring::createDup(TSInfo->getType().getAsString(Policy));
5021
5022 SmallString<128> Str;
5023 llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(Str);
5024 OS << *ClassSpec;
5025 printTemplateArgumentList(OS, ClassSpec->getTemplateArgs().asArray(),
5026 Policy);
5027 return cxstring::createDup(OS.str());
5028 }
5029
5030 return clang_getCursorSpelling(C);
5031}
