5512
5513struct GetCursorData {
5514 SourceLocation TokenBeginLoc;
5515 bool PointsAtMacroArgExpansion;
5516 bool VisitedObjCPropertyImplDecl;
5517 SourceLocation VisitedDeclaratorDeclStartLoc;
5518 CXCursor &BestCursor;
5519
5520 GetCursorData(SourceManager &SM,
5521 SourceLocation tokenBegin, CXCursor &outputCursor)
5522 : TokenBeginLoc(tokenBegin), BestCursor(outputCursor) {
5523 PointsAtMacroArgExpansion = SM.isMacroArgExpansion(tokenBegin);
5524 VisitedObjCPropertyImplDecl = false;
5525 }
5526};
5527
5528static enum CXChildVisitResult GetCursorVisitor(CXCursor cursor,
5529 CXCursor parent,
5530 CXClientData client_data) {
5531 GetCursorData *Data = static_cast<GetCursorData *>(client_data);
5532 CXCursor *BestCursor = &Data->BestCursor;
5533
5534 // If we point inside a macro argument we should provide info of what the
5535 // token is so use the actual cursor, don't replace it with a macro expansion
5536 // cursor.
5537 if (cursor.kind == CXCursor_MacroExpansion && Data->PointsAtMacroArgExpansion)
5538 return CXChildVisit_Recurse;
5539
5540 if (clang_isDeclaration(cursor.kind)) {
5541 // Avoid having the implicit methods override the property decls.
5542 if (const ObjCMethodDecl *MD
5543 = dyn_cast_or_null<ObjCMethodDecl>(getCursorDecl(cursor))) {
5544 if (MD->isImplicit())
5545 return CXChildVisit_Break;
5546
5547 } else if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID
5548 = dyn_cast_or_null<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(getCursorDecl(cursor))) {
5549 // Check that when we have multiple @class references in the same line,
5550 // that later ones do not override the previous ones.
5551 // If we have:
5552 // @class Foo, Bar;
5553 // source ranges for both start at '@', so 'Bar' will end up overriding
5554 // 'Foo' even though the cursor location was at 'Foo'.
5555 if (BestCursor->kind == CXCursor_ObjCInterfaceDecl ||
5556 BestCursor->kind == CXCursor_ObjCClassRef)
5557 if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *PrevID
5558 = dyn_cast_or_null<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(getCursorDecl(*BestCursor))){
5559 if (PrevID != ID &&
5560 !PrevID->isThisDeclarationADefinition() &&
5561 !ID->isThisDeclarationADefinition())
5562 return CXChildVisit_Break;
5563 }
5564
5565 } else if (const DeclaratorDecl *DD
5566 = dyn_cast_or_null<DeclaratorDecl>(getCursorDecl(cursor))) {
5567 SourceLocation StartLoc = DD->getSourceRange().getBegin();
5568 // Check that when we have multiple declarators in the same line,
5569 // that later ones do not override the previous ones.
5570 // If we have:
5571 // int Foo, Bar;
5572 // source ranges for both start at 'int', so 'Bar' will end up overriding
5573 // 'Foo' even though the cursor location was at 'Foo'.
5574 if (Data->VisitedDeclaratorDeclStartLoc == StartLoc)
5575 return CXChildVisit_Break;
5576 Data->VisitedDeclaratorDeclStartLoc = StartLoc;
5577
5578 } else if (const ObjCPropertyImplDecl *PropImp
5579 = dyn_cast_or_null<ObjCPropertyImplDecl>(getCursorDecl(cursor))) {
5580 (void)PropImp;
5581 // Check that when we have multiple @synthesize in the same line,
5582 // that later ones do not override the previous ones.
5583 // If we have:
5584 // @synthesize Foo, Bar;
5585 // source ranges for both start at '@', so 'Bar' will end up overriding
5586 // 'Foo' even though the cursor location was at 'Foo'.
5587 if (Data->VisitedObjCPropertyImplDecl)
5588 return CXChildVisit_Break;
5589 Data->VisitedObjCPropertyImplDecl = true;
5590 }
5591 }
5592
5593 if (clang_isExpression(cursor.kind) &&
5594 clang_isDeclaration(BestCursor->kind)) {
5595 if (const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(*BestCursor)) {
5596 // Avoid having the cursor of an expression replace the declaration cursor
5597 // when the expression source range overlaps the declaration range.
5598 // This can happen for C++ constructor expressions whose range generally
5599 // include the variable declaration, e.g.:
5600 // MyCXXClass foo; // Make sure pointing at 'foo' returns a VarDecl cursor.
5601 if (D->getLocation().isValid() && Data->TokenBeginLoc.isValid() &&
5602 D->getLocation() == Data->TokenBeginLoc)
5603 return CXChildVisit_Break;
5604 }
5605 }
5606
5607 // If our current best cursor is the construction of a temporary object,
5608 // don't replace that cursor with a type reference, because we want
5609 // clang_getCursor() to point at the constructor.
5610 if (clang_isExpression(BestCursor->kind) &&
5611 isa<CXXTemporaryObjectExpr>(getCursorExpr(*BestCursor)) &&
5612 cursor.kind == CXCursor_TypeRef) {
5613 // Keep the cursor pointing at CXXTemporaryObjectExpr but also mark it
5614 // as having the actual point on the type reference.
5615 *BestCursor = getTypeRefedCallExprCursor(*BestCursor);
5616 return CXChildVisit_Recurse;
5617 }
5618
5619 // If we already have an Objective-C superclass reference, don't
5620 // update it further.
5621 if (BestCursor->kind == CXCursor_ObjCSuperClassRef)
5622 return CXChildVisit_Break;
5623
5624 *BestCursor = cursor;
5625 return CXChildVisit_Recurse;
5626}
5627
5628CXCursor clang_getCursor(CXTranslationUnit TU, CXSourceLocation Loc) {
5629 if (isNotUsableTU(TU)) {
5630 LOG_BAD_TU(TU);
5631 return clang_getNullCursor();
5632 }
5633
5634 ASTUnit *CXXUnit = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU);
5635 ASTUnit::ConcurrencyCheck Check(*CXXUnit);
5636
5637 SourceLocation SLoc = cxloc::translateSourceLocation(Loc);
5638 CXCursor Result = cxcursor::getCursor(TU, SLoc);
5639
5640 LOG_FUNC_SECTION {
5641 CXFile SearchFile;
5642 unsigned SearchLine, SearchColumn;
5643 CXFile ResultFile;
5644 unsigned ResultLine, ResultColumn;
5645 CXString SearchFileName, ResultFileName, KindSpelling, USR;
5646 const char *IsDef = clang_isCursorDefinition(Result)? " (Definition)" : "";
5647 CXSourceLocation ResultLoc = clang_getCursorLocation(Result);
5648
5649 clang_getFileLocation(Loc, &SearchFile, &SearchLine, &SearchColumn,
5650 nullptr);
5651 clang_getFileLocation(ResultLoc, &ResultFile, &ResultLine,
5652 &ResultColumn, nullptr);
5653 SearchFileName = clang_getFileName(SearchFile);
5654 ResultFileName = clang_getFileName(ResultFile);
5655 KindSpelling = clang_getCursorKindSpelling(Result.kind);
5656 USR = clang_getCursorUSR(Result);
5657 *Log << llvm::format("(%s:%d:%d) = %s",
5658 clang_getCString(SearchFileName), SearchLine, SearchColumn,
5659 clang_getCString(KindSpelling))
5660 << llvm::format("(%s:%d:%d):%s%s",
5661 clang_getCString(ResultFileName), ResultLine, ResultColumn,
5662 clang_getCString(USR), IsDef);
5663 clang_disposeString(SearchFileName);
5664 clang_disposeString(ResultFileName);
5665 clang_disposeString(KindSpelling);
5666 clang_disposeString(USR);
5667
5668 CXCursor Definition = clang_getCursorDefinition(Result);
5669 if (!clang_equalCursors(Definition, clang_getNullCursor())) {
5670 CXSourceLocation DefinitionLoc = clang_getCursorLocation(Definition);
5671 CXString DefinitionKindSpelling
5672 = clang_getCursorKindSpelling(Definition.kind);
5673 CXFile DefinitionFile;
5674 unsigned DefinitionLine, DefinitionColumn;
5675 clang_getFileLocation(DefinitionLoc, &DefinitionFile,
5676 &DefinitionLine, &DefinitionColumn, nullptr);
5677 CXString DefinitionFileName = clang_getFileName(DefinitionFile);
5678 *Log << llvm::format(" -> %s(%s:%d:%d)",
5679 clang_getCString(DefinitionKindSpelling),
5680 clang_getCString(DefinitionFileName),
5681 DefinitionLine, DefinitionColumn);
5682 clang_disposeString(DefinitionFileName);
5683 clang_disposeString(DefinitionKindSpelling);
5684 }
5685 }
5686
5687 return Result;
5688}
5689
5690CXCursor clang_getNullCursor(void) {
5691 return MakeCXCursorInvalid(CXCursor_InvalidFile);
5692}
5693
5694unsigned clang_equalCursors(CXCursor X, CXCursor Y) {
5695 // Clear out the "FirstInDeclGroup" part in a declaration cursor, since we
5696 // can't set consistently. For example, when visiting a DeclStmt we will set
5697 // it but we don't set it on the result of clang_getCursorDefinition for
5698 // a reference of the same declaration.
5699 // FIXME: Setting "FirstInDeclGroup" in CXCursors is a hack that only works
5700 // when visiting a DeclStmt currently, the AST should be enhanced to be able
5701 // to provide that kind of info.
5702 if (clang_isDeclaration(X.kind))
5703 X.data[1] = nullptr;
5704 if (clang_isDeclaration(Y.kind))
5705 Y.data[1] = nullptr;
5706
5707 return X == Y;
5708}
5709
5710unsigned clang_hashCursor(CXCursor C) {
5711 unsigned Index = 0;
5712 if (clang_isExpression(C.kind) || clang_isStatement(C.kind))
5713 Index = 1;
5714
5715 return llvm::DenseMapInfo<std::pair<unsigned, const void*> >::getHashValue(
5716 std::make_pair(C.kind, C.data[Index]));
5717}
5718
5719unsigned clang_isInvalid(enum CXCursorKind K) {
5720 return K >= CXCursor_FirstInvalid && K <= CXCursor_LastInvalid;
5721}
5722
5723unsigned clang_isDeclaration(enum CXCursorKind K) {
5724 return (K >= CXCursor_FirstDecl && K <= CXCursor_LastDecl) ||
5725 (K >= CXCursor_FirstExtraDecl && K <= CXCursor_LastExtraDecl);
5726}
5727
5728unsigned clang_isInvalidDeclaration(CXCursor C) {
5729 if (clang_isDeclaration(C.kind)) {
5730 if (const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(C))
5731 return D->isInvalidDecl();
5732 }
5733
5734 return 0;
5735}
5736
5737unsigned clang_isReference(enum CXCursorKind K) {
5738 return K >= CXCursor_FirstRef && K <= CXCursor_LastRef;
5739}
5740
5741unsigned clang_isExpression(enum CXCursorKind K) {
5742 return K >= CXCursor_FirstExpr && K <= CXCursor_LastExpr;
5743}
5744
5745unsigned clang_isStatement(enum CXCursorKind K) {
5746 return K >= CXCursor_FirstStmt && K <= CXCursor_LastStmt;
5747}
5748
5749unsigned clang_isAttribute(enum CXCursorKind K) {
5750 return K >= CXCursor_FirstAttr && K <= CXCursor_LastAttr;
5751}
5752
5753unsigned clang_isTranslationUnit(enum CXCursorKind K) {
5754 return K == CXCursor_TranslationUnit;
5755}
5756
5757unsigned clang_isPreprocessing(enum CXCursorKind K) {
5758 return K >= CXCursor_FirstPreprocessing && K <= CXCursor_LastPreprocessing;
5759}
5760
5761unsigned clang_isUnexposed(enum CXCursorKind K) {
5762 switch (K) {
5763 case CXCursor_UnexposedDecl:
5764 case CXCursor_UnexposedExpr:
5765 case CXCursor_UnexposedStmt:
5766 case CXCursor_UnexposedAttr:
5767 return true;
5768 default:
5769 return false;
5770 }
5771}
5772
5773CXCursorKind clang_getCursorKind(CXCursor C) {
5774 return C.kind;
5775}
5776
5777CXSourceLocation clang_getCursorLocation(CXCursor C) {
5778 if (clang_isReference(C.kind)) {
5779 switch (C.kind) {
5780 case CXCursor_ObjCSuperClassRef: {
5781 std::pair<const ObjCInterfaceDecl *, SourceLocation> P
5782 = getCursorObjCSuperClassRef(C);
5783 return cxloc::translateSourceLocation(P.first->getASTContext(), P.second);
5784 }
5785
5786 case CXCursor_ObjCProtocolRef: {
5787 std::pair<const ObjCProtocolDecl *, SourceLocation> P
5788 = getCursorObjCProtocolRef(C);
5789 return cxloc::translateSourceLocation(P.first->getASTContext(), P.second);
5790 }
5791
5792 case CXCursor_ObjCClassRef: {
5793 std::pair<const ObjCInterfaceDecl *, SourceLocation> P
5794 = getCursorObjCClassRef(C);
5795 return cxloc::translateSourceLocation(P.first->getASTContext(), P.second);
5796 }
5797
5798 case CXCursor_TypeRef: {
5799 std::pair<const TypeDecl *, SourceLocation> P = getCursorTypeRef(C);
5800 return cxloc::translateSourceLocation(P.first->getASTContext(), P.second);
5801 }
5802
5803 case CXCursor_TemplateRef: {
5804 std::pair<const TemplateDecl *, SourceLocation> P =
5805 getCursorTemplateRef(C);
5806 return cxloc::translateSourceLocation(P.first->getASTContext(), P.second);
5807 }
5808
5809 case CXCursor_NamespaceRef: {
5810 std::pair<const NamedDecl *, SourceLocation> P = getCursorNamespaceRef(C);
5811 return cxloc::translateSourceLocation(P.first->getASTContext(), P.second);
5812 }
5813
5814 case CXCursor_MemberRef: {
5815 std::pair<const FieldDecl *, SourceLocation> P = getCursorMemberRef(C);
5816 return cxloc::translateSourceLocation(P.first->getASTContext(), P.second);
5817 }
5818
5819 case CXCursor_VariableRef: {
5820 std::pair<const VarDecl *, SourceLocation> P = getCursorVariableRef(C);
5821 return cxloc::translateSourceLocation(P.first->getASTContext(), P.second);
5822 }
5823
5824 case CXCursor_CXXBaseSpecifier: {
5825 const CXXBaseSpecifier *BaseSpec = getCursorCXXBaseSpecifier(C);
5826 if (!BaseSpec)
5827 return clang_getNullLocation();
5828
5829 if (TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo = BaseSpec->getTypeSourceInfo())
5830 return cxloc::translateSourceLocation(getCursorContext(C),
5831 TSInfo->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc());
5832
5833 return cxloc::translateSourceLocation(getCursorContext(C),
5834 BaseSpec->getBeginLoc());
5835 }
5836
5837 case CXCursor_LabelRef: {
5838 std::pair<const LabelStmt *, SourceLocation> P = getCursorLabelRef(C);
5839 return cxloc::translateSourceLocation(getCursorContext(C), P.second);
5840 }
5841
5842 case CXCursor_OverloadedDeclRef:
5843 return cxloc::translateSourceLocation(getCursorContext(C),
5844 getCursorOverloadedDeclRef(C).second);
5845
5846 default:
5847 // FIXME: Need a way to enumerate all non-reference cases.
5848 llvm_unreachable("Missed a reference kind");
5849 }
5850 }
5851
5852 if (clang_isExpression(C.kind))
5853 return cxloc::translateSourceLocation(getCursorContext(C),
5854 getLocationFromExpr(getCursorExpr(C)));
5855
5856 if (clang_isStatement(C.kind))
5857 return cxloc::translateSourceLocation(getCursorContext(C),
5858 getCursorStmt(C)->getBeginLoc());
5859
5860 if (C.kind == CXCursor_PreprocessingDirective) {
5861 SourceLocation L = cxcursor::getCursorPreprocessingDirective(C).getBegin();
5862 return cxloc::translateSourceLocation(getCursorContext(C), L);
5863 }
5864
5865 if (C.kind == CXCursor_MacroExpansion) {
5866 SourceLocation L
5867 = cxcursor::getCursorMacroExpansion(C).getSourceRange().getBegin();
5868 return cxloc::translateSourceLocation(getCursorContext(C), L);
5869 }
5870
5871 if (C.kind == CXCursor_MacroDefinition) {
5872 SourceLocation L = cxcursor::getCursorMacroDefinition(C)->getLocation();
5873 return cxloc::translateSourceLocation(getCursorContext(C), L);
5874 }
5875
5876 if (C.kind == CXCursor_InclusionDirective) {
5877 SourceLocation L
5878 = cxcursor::getCursorInclusionDirective(C)->getSourceRange().getBegin();
5879 return cxloc::translateSourceLocation(getCursorContext(C), L);
5880 }
5881
5882 if (clang_isAttribute(C.kind)) {
5883 SourceLocation L
5884 = cxcursor::getCursorAttr(C)->getLocation();
5885 return cxloc::translateSourceLocation(getCursorContext(C), L);
5886 }
5887
5888 if (!clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
5889 return clang_getNullLocation();
5890
5891 const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(C);
5892 if (!D)
5893 return clang_getNullLocation();
5894
5895 SourceLocation Loc = D->getLocation();
5896 // FIXME: Multiple variables declared in a single declaration
5897 // currently lack the information needed to correctly determine their
5898 // ranges when accounting for the type-specifier. We use context
5899 // stored in the CXCursor to determine if the VarDecl is in a DeclGroup,
5900 // and if so, whether it is the first decl.
5901 if (const VarDecl *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
5902 if (!cxcursor::isFirstInDeclGroup(C))
5903 Loc = VD->getLocation();
5904 }
5905
5906 // For ObjC methods, give the start location of the method name.
5907 if (const ObjCMethodDecl *MD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D))
5908 Loc = MD->getSelectorStartLoc();
5909
5910 return cxloc::translateSourceLocation(getCursorContext(C), Loc);
5911}
5912
5913} // end extern "C"
5914
5915CXCursor cxcursor::getCursor(CXTranslationUnit TU, SourceLocation SLoc) {
5916 assert(TU);
5917
5918 // Guard against an invalid SourceLocation, or we may assert in one
5919 // of the following calls.
5920 if (SLoc.isInvalid())
5921 return clang_getNullCursor();
5922
5923 ASTUnit *CXXUnit = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU);
5924
5925 // Translate the given source location to make it point at the beginning of
5926 // the token under the cursor.
5927 SLoc = Lexer::GetBeginningOfToken(SLoc, CXXUnit->getSourceManager(),
5928 CXXUnit->getASTContext().getLangOpts());
5929
5930 CXCursor Result = MakeCXCursorInvalid(CXCursor_NoDeclFound);
5931 if (SLoc.isValid()) {
5932 GetCursorData ResultData(CXXUnit->getSourceManager(), SLoc, Result);
5933 CursorVisitor CursorVis(TU, GetCursorVisitor, &ResultData,
5934 /*VisitPreprocessorLast=*/true,
5935 /*VisitIncludedEntities=*/false,
5936 SourceLocation(SLoc));
5937 CursorVis.visitFileRegion();
5938 }
5939
5940 return Result;
5941}
5942
5943static SourceRange getRawCursorExtent(CXCursor C) {
5944 if (clang_isReference(C.kind)) {
5945 switch (C.kind) {
5946 case CXCursor_ObjCSuperClassRef:
5947 return getCursorObjCSuperClassRef(C).second;
5948
5949 case CXCursor_ObjCProtocolRef:
5950 return getCursorObjCProtocolRef(C).second;
5951
5952 case CXCursor_ObjCClassRef:
5953 return getCursorObjCClassRef(C).second;
5954
5955 case CXCursor_TypeRef:
5956 return getCursorTypeRef(C).second;
5957
5958 case CXCursor_TemplateRef:
5959 return getCursorTemplateRef(C).second;
5960
5961 case CXCursor_NamespaceRef:
5962 return getCursorNamespaceRef(C).second;
5963
5964 case CXCursor_MemberRef:
5965 return getCursorMemberRef(C).second;
5966
5967 case CXCursor_CXXBaseSpecifier:
5968 return getCursorCXXBaseSpecifier(C)->getSourceRange();
5969
5970 case CXCursor_LabelRef:
5971 return getCursorLabelRef(C).second;
5972
5973 case CXCursor_OverloadedDeclRef:
5974 return getCursorOverloadedDeclRef(C).second;
5975
5976 case CXCursor_VariableRef:
5977 return getCursorVariableRef(C).second;
5978
5979 default:
5980 // FIXME: Need a way to enumerate all non-reference cases.
5981 llvm_unreachable("Missed a reference kind");
5982 }
5983 }
5984
5985 if (clang_isExpression(C.kind))
5986 return getCursorExpr(C)->getSourceRange();
5987
5988 if (clang_isStatement(C.kind))
5989 return getCursorStmt(C)->getSourceRange();
5990
5991 if (clang_isAttribute(C.kind))
5992 return getCursorAttr(C)->getRange();
5993
5994 if (C.kind == CXCursor_PreprocessingDirective)
5995 return cxcursor::getCursorPreprocessingDirective(C);
5996
5997 if (C.kind == CXCursor_MacroExpansion) {
5998 ASTUnit *TU = getCursorASTUnit(C);
5999 SourceRange Range = cxcursor::getCursorMacroExpansion(C).getSourceRange();
6000 return TU->mapRangeFromPreamble(Range);
6001 }
6002
6003 if (C.kind == CXCursor_MacroDefinition) {
6004 ASTUnit *TU = getCursorASTUnit(C);
6005 SourceRange Range = cxcursor::getCursorMacroDefinition(C)->getSourceRange();
6006 return TU->mapRangeFromPreamble(Range);
6007 }
6008
6009 if (C.kind == CXCursor_InclusionDirective) {
6010 ASTUnit *TU = getCursorASTUnit(C);
6011 SourceRange Range = cxcursor::getCursorInclusionDirective(C)->getSourceRange();
6012 return TU->mapRangeFromPreamble(Range);
6013 }
6014
6015 if (C.kind == CXCursor_TranslationUnit) {
6016 ASTUnit *TU = getCursorASTUnit(C);
6017 FileID MainID = TU->getSourceManager().getMainFileID();
6018 SourceLocation Start = TU->getSourceManager().getLocForStartOfFile(MainID);
6019 SourceLocation End = TU->getSourceManager().getLocForEndOfFile(MainID);
6020 return SourceRange(Start, End);
6021 }
6022
6023 if (clang_isDeclaration(C.kind)) {
6024 const Decl *D = cxcursor::getCursorDecl(C);
6025 if (!D)
6026 return SourceRange();
6027
6028 SourceRange R = D->getSourceRange();
6029 // FIXME: Multiple variables declared in a single declaration
6030 // currently lack the information needed to correctly determine their
6031 // ranges when accounting for the type-specifier. We use context
6032 // stored in the CXCursor to determine if the VarDecl is in a DeclGroup,
6033 // and if so, whether it is the first decl.
6034 if (const VarDecl *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
6035 if (!cxcursor::isFirstInDeclGroup(C))
6036 R.setBegin(VD->getLocation());
6037 }
6038 return R;
6039 }
6040 return SourceRange();
6041}
6042
6043/// Retrieves the "raw" cursor extent, which is then extended to include
6044/// the decl-specifier-seq for declarations.
6045static SourceRange getFullCursorExtent(CXCursor C, SourceManager &SrcMgr) {
6046 if (clang_isDeclaration(C.kind)) {
6047 const Decl *D = cxcursor::getCursorDecl(C);
6048 if (!D)
6049 return SourceRange();
6050
6051 SourceRange R = D->getSourceRange();
6052
6053 // Adjust the start of the location for declarations preceded by
6054 // declaration specifiers.
6055 SourceLocation StartLoc;
6056 if (const DeclaratorDecl *DD = dyn_cast<DeclaratorDecl>(D)) {
6057 if (TypeSourceInfo *TI = DD->getTypeSourceInfo())
6058 StartLoc = TI->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc();
6059 } else if (const TypedefDecl *Typedef = dyn_cast<TypedefDecl>(D)) {
6060 if (TypeSourceInfo *TI = Typedef->getTypeSourceInfo())
6061 StartLoc = TI->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc();
6062 }
6063
6064 if (StartLoc.isValid() && R.getBegin().isValid() &&
6065 SrcMgr.isBeforeInTranslationUnit(StartLoc, R.getBegin()))
6066 R.setBegin(StartLoc);
6067
6068 // FIXME: Multiple variables declared in a single declaration
6069 // currently lack the information needed to correctly determine their
6070 // ranges when accounting for the type-specifier. We use context
6071 // stored in the CXCursor to determine if the VarDecl is in a DeclGroup,
6072 // and if so, whether it is the first decl.
6073 if (const VarDecl *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
6074 if (!cxcursor::isFirstInDeclGroup(C))
6075 R.setBegin(VD->getLocation());
6076 }
6077
6078 return R;
6079 }
6080
6081 return getRawCursorExtent(C);
6082}
6083
6084CXSourceRange clang_getCursorExtent(CXCursor C) {
6085 SourceRange R = getRawCursorExtent(C);
6086 if (R.isInvalid())
6087 return clang_getNullRange();
6088
6089 return cxloc::translateSourceRange(getCursorContext(C), R);
6090}
6091
6092CXCursor clang_getCursorReferenced(CXCursor C) {
6093 if (clang_isInvalid(C.kind))
6094 return clang_getNullCursor();
6095
6096 CXTranslationUnit tu = getCursorTU(C);
6097 if (clang_isDeclaration(C.kind)) {
6098 const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(C);
6099 if (!D)
6100 return clang_getNullCursor();
6101 if (const UsingDecl *Using = dyn_cast<UsingDecl>(D))
6102 return MakeCursorOverloadedDeclRef(Using, D->getLocation(), tu);
6103 if (const ObjCPropertyImplDecl *PropImpl =
6104 dyn_cast<ObjCPropertyImplDecl>(D))
6105 if (ObjCPropertyDecl *Property = PropImpl->getPropertyDecl())
6106 return MakeCXCursor(Property, tu);
6107
6108 return C;
6109 }
6110
6111 if (clang_isExpression(C.kind)) {
6112 const Expr *E = getCursorExpr(C);
6113 const Decl *D = getDeclFromExpr(E);
6114 if (D) {
6115 CXCursor declCursor = MakeCXCursor(D, tu);
6116 declCursor = getSelectorIdentifierCursor(getSelectorIdentifierIndex(C),
6117 declCursor);
6118 return declCursor;
6119 }
6120
6121 if (const OverloadExpr *Ovl = dyn_cast_or_null<OverloadExpr>(E))
6122 return MakeCursorOverloadedDeclRef(Ovl, tu);
6123
6124 return clang_getNullCursor();
6125 }
6126
6127 if (clang_isStatement(C.kind)) {
6128 const Stmt *S = getCursorStmt(C);
6129 if (const GotoStmt *Goto = dyn_cast_or_null<GotoStmt>(S))
6130 if (LabelDecl *label = Goto->getLabel())
6131 if (LabelStmt *labelS = label->getStmt())
6132 return MakeCXCursor(labelS, getCursorDecl(C), tu);
6133
6134 return clang_getNullCursor();
6135 }
6136
6137 if (C.kind == CXCursor_MacroExpansion) {
6138 if (const MacroDefinitionRecord *Def =
6139 getCursorMacroExpansion(C).getDefinition())
6140 return MakeMacroDefinitionCursor(Def, tu);
6141 }
6142
6143 if (!clang_isReference(C.kind))
6144 return clang_getNullCursor();
6145
6146 switch (C.kind) {
6147 case CXCursor_ObjCSuperClassRef:
6148 return MakeCXCursor(getCursorObjCSuperClassRef(C).first, tu);
6149
6150 case CXCursor_ObjCProtocolRef: {
6151 const ObjCProtocolDecl *Prot = getCursorObjCProtocolRef(C).first;
6152 if (const ObjCProtocolDecl *Def = Prot->getDefinition())
6153 return MakeCXCursor(Def, tu);
6154
6155 return MakeCXCursor(Prot, tu);
6156 }
6157
6158 case CXCursor_ObjCClassRef: {
6159 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Class = getCursorObjCClassRef(C).first;
6160 if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Def = Class->getDefinition())
6161 return MakeCXCursor(Def, tu);
6162
6163 return MakeCXCursor(Class, tu);
6164 }
6165
6166 case CXCursor_TypeRef:
6167 return MakeCXCursor(getCursorTypeRef(C).first, tu );
6168
6169 case CXCursor_TemplateRef:
6170 return MakeCXCursor(getCursorTemplateRef(C).first, tu );
6171
6172 case CXCursor_NamespaceRef:
6173 return MakeCXCursor(getCursorNamespaceRef(C).first, tu );
6174
6175 case CXCursor_MemberRef:
6176 return MakeCXCursor(getCursorMemberRef(C).first, tu );
6177
6178 case CXCursor_CXXBaseSpecifier: {
6179 const CXXBaseSpecifier *B = cxcursor::getCursorCXXBaseSpecifier(C);
6180 return clang_getTypeDeclaration(cxtype::MakeCXType(B->getType(),
6181 tu ));
6182 }
6183
6184 case CXCursor_LabelRef:
6185 // FIXME: We end up faking the "parent" declaration here because we
6186 // don't want to make CXCursor larger.
6187 return MakeCXCursor(getCursorLabelRef(C).first,
6188 cxtu::getASTUnit(tu)->getASTContext()
6189 .getTranslationUnitDecl(),
6190 tu);
6191
6192 case CXCursor_OverloadedDeclRef:
6193 return C;
6194
6195 case CXCursor_VariableRef:
6196 return MakeCXCursor(getCursorVariableRef(C).first, tu);
6197
6198 default:
6199 // We would prefer to enumerate all non-reference cursor kinds here.
6200 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled reference cursor kind");
6201 }
6202}
6203
6204CXCursor clang_getCursorDefinition(CXCursor C) {
6205 if (clang_isInvalid(C.kind))
6206 return clang_getNullCursor();
6207
6208 CXTranslationUnit TU = getCursorTU(C);
6209
6210 bool WasReference = false;
6211 if (clang_isReference(C.kind) || clang_isExpression(C.kind)) {
6212 C = clang_getCursorReferenced(C);
6213 WasReference = true;
6214 }
6215
6216 if (C.kind == CXCursor_MacroExpansion)
6217 return clang_getCursorReferenced(C);
6218
6219 if (!clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
6220 return clang_getNullCursor();
6221
6222 const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(C);
6223 if (!D)
6224 return clang_getNullCursor();
6225
6226 switch (D->getKind()) {
6227 // Declaration kinds that don't really separate the notions of
6228 // declaration and definition.
6229 case Decl::Namespace:
6230 case Decl::Typedef:
6231 case Decl::TypeAlias:
6232 case Decl::TypeAliasTemplate:
6233 case Decl::TemplateTypeParm:
6234 case Decl::EnumConstant:
6235 case Decl::Field:
6236 case Decl::Binding:
6237 case Decl::MSProperty:
6238 case Decl::IndirectField:
6239 case Decl::ObjCIvar:
6240 case Decl::ObjCAtDefsField:
6241 case Decl::ImplicitParam:
6242 case Decl::ParmVar:
6243 case Decl::NonTypeTemplateParm:
6244 case Decl::TemplateTemplateParm:
6245 case Decl::ObjCCategoryImpl:
6246 case Decl::ObjCImplementation:
6247 case Decl::AccessSpec:
6248 case Decl::LinkageSpec:
6249 case Decl::Export:
6250 case Decl::ObjCPropertyImpl:
6251 case Decl::FileScopeAsm:
6252 case Decl::StaticAssert:
6253 case Decl::Block:
6254 case Decl::Captured:
6255 case Decl::OMPCapturedExpr:
6256 case Decl::Label: // FIXME: Is this right??
6257 case Decl::ClassScopeFunctionSpecialization:
6258 case Decl::CXXDeductionGuide:
6259 case Decl::Import:
6260 case Decl::OMPThreadPrivate:
6261 case Decl::OMPAllocate:
6262 case Decl::OMPDeclareReduction:
6263 case Decl::OMPDeclareMapper:
6264 case Decl::OMPRequires:
6265 case Decl::ObjCTypeParam:
6266 case Decl::BuiltinTemplate:
6267 case Decl::PragmaComment:
6268 case Decl::PragmaDetectMismatch:
6269 case Decl::UsingPack:
6270 return C;
6271
6272 // Declaration kinds that don't make any sense here, but are
6273 // nonetheless harmless.
6274 case Decl::Empty:
6275 case Decl::TranslationUnit:
6276 case Decl::ExternCContext:
6277 break;
6278
6279 // Declaration kinds for which the definition is not resolvable.
6280 case Decl::UnresolvedUsingTypename:
6281 case Decl::UnresolvedUsingValue:
6282 break;
6283
6284 case Decl::UsingDirective:
6285 return MakeCXCursor(cast<UsingDirectiveDecl>(D)->getNominatedNamespace(),
6286 TU);
6287
6288 case Decl::NamespaceAlias:
6289 return MakeCXCursor(cast<NamespaceAliasDecl>(D)->getNamespace(), TU);
6290
6291 case Decl::Enum:
6292 case Decl::Record:
6293 case Decl::CXXRecord:
6294 case Decl::ClassTemplateSpecialization:
6295 case Decl::ClassTemplatePartialSpecialization:
6296 if (TagDecl *Def = cast<TagDecl>(D)->getDefinition())
6297 return MakeCXCursor(Def, TU);
6298 return clang_getNullCursor();
6299
6300 case Decl::Function:
6301 case Decl::CXXMethod:
6302 case Decl::CXXConstructor:
6303 case Decl::CXXDestructor:
6304 case Decl::CXXConversion: {
6305 const FunctionDecl *Def = nullptr;
6306 if (cast<FunctionDecl>(D)->getBody(Def))
6307 return MakeCXCursor(Def, TU);
6308 return clang_getNullCursor();
6309 }
6310
6311 case Decl::Var:
6312 case Decl::VarTemplateSpecialization:
6313 case Decl::VarTemplatePartialSpecialization:
6314 case Decl::Decomposition: {
6315 // Ask the variable if it has a definition.
6316 if (const VarDecl *Def = cast<VarDecl>(D)->getDefinition())
6317 return MakeCXCursor(Def, TU);
6318 return clang_getNullCursor();
6319 }
6320
6321 case Decl::FunctionTemplate: {
6322 const FunctionDecl *Def = nullptr;
6323 if (cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D)->getTemplatedDecl()->getBody(Def))
6324 return MakeCXCursor(Def->getDescribedFunctionTemplate(), TU);
6325 return clang_getNullCursor();
6326 }
6327
6328 case Decl::ClassTemplate: {
6329 if (RecordDecl *Def = cast<ClassTemplateDecl>(D)->getTemplatedDecl()
6330 ->getDefinition())
6331 return MakeCXCursor(cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Def)->getDescribedClassTemplate(),
6332 TU);
6333 return clang_getNullCursor();
6334 }
6335
6336 case Decl::VarTemplate: {
6337 if (VarDecl *Def =
6338 cast<VarTemplateDecl>(D)->getTemplatedDecl()->getDefinition())
6339 return MakeCXCursor(cast<VarDecl>(Def)->getDescribedVarTemplate(), TU);
6340 return clang_getNullCursor();
6341 }
6342
6343 case Decl::Using:
6344 return MakeCursorOverloadedDeclRef(cast<UsingDecl>(D),
6345 D->getLocation(), TU);
6346
6347 case Decl::UsingShadow:
6348 case Decl::ConstructorUsingShadow:
6349 return clang_getCursorDefinition(
6350 MakeCXCursor(cast<UsingShadowDecl>(D)->getTargetDecl(),
6351 TU));
6352
6353 case Decl::ObjCMethod: {
6354 const ObjCMethodDecl *Method = cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D);
6355 if (Method->isThisDeclarationADefinition())
6356 return C;
6357
6358 // Dig out the method definition in the associated
6359 // @implementation, if we have it.
6360 // FIXME: The ASTs should make finding the definition easier.
6361 if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Class
6362 = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(Method->getDeclContext()))
6363 if (ObjCImplementationDecl *ClassImpl = Class->getImplementation())
6364 if (ObjCMethodDecl *Def = ClassImpl->getMethod(Method->getSelector(),
6365 Method->isInstanceMethod()))
6366 if (Def->isThisDeclarationADefinition())
6367 return MakeCXCursor(Def, TU);
6368
6369 return clang_getNullCursor();
6370 }
6371
6372 case Decl::ObjCCategory:
6373 if (ObjCCategoryImplDecl *Impl
6374 = cast<ObjCCategoryDecl>(D)->getImplementation())
6375 return MakeCXCursor(Impl, TU);
6376 return clang_getNullCursor();
6377
6378 case Decl::ObjCProtocol:
6379 if (const ObjCProtocolDecl *Def = cast<ObjCProtocolDecl>(D)->getDefinition())
6380 return MakeCXCursor(Def, TU);
6381 return clang_getNullCursor();
6382
6383 case Decl::ObjCInterface: {
6384 // There are two notions of a "definition" for an Objective-C
6385 // class: the interface and its implementation. When we resolved a
6386 // reference to an Objective-C class, produce the @interface as
6387 // the definition; when we were provided with the interface,
6388 // produce the @implementation as the definition.
6389 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *IFace = cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(D);
6390 if (WasReference) {
6391 if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Def = IFace->getDefinition())
6392 return MakeCXCursor(Def, TU);
6393 } else if (ObjCImplementationDecl *Impl = IFace->getImplementation())
6394 return MakeCXCursor(Impl, TU);
6395 return clang_getNullCursor();
6396 }
6397
6398 case Decl::ObjCProperty:
6399 // FIXME: We don't really know where to find the
6400 // ObjCPropertyImplDecls that implement this property.
6401 return clang_getNullCursor();
6402
6403 case Decl::ObjCCompatibleAlias:
6404 if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Class
6405 = cast<ObjCCompatibleAliasDecl>(D)->getClassInterface())
6406 if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Def = Class->getDefinition())
6407 return MakeCXCursor(Def, TU);
6408
6409 return clang_getNullCursor();
6410
6411 case Decl::Friend:
6412 if (NamedDecl *Friend = cast<FriendDecl>(D)->getFriendDecl())
6413 return clang_getCursorDefinition(MakeCXCursor(Friend, TU));
6414 return clang_getNullCursor();
6415
6416 case Decl::FriendTemplate:
6417 if (NamedDecl *Friend = cast<FriendTemplateDecl>(D)->getFriendDecl())
6418 return clang_getCursorDefinition(MakeCXCursor(Friend, TU));
6419 return clang_getNullCursor();
6420 }
6421
6422 return clang_getNullCursor();
6423}
6424
6425unsigned clang_isCursorDefinition(CXCursor C) {
6426 if (!clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
6427 return 0;
6428
6429 return clang_getCursorDefinition(C) == C;
6430}
6431
6432CXCursor clang_getCanonicalCursor(CXCursor C) {
6433 if (!clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
6434 return C;
6435
6436 if (const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(C)) {
6437 if (const ObjCCategoryImplDecl *CatImplD = dyn_cast<ObjCCategoryImplDecl>(D))
6438 if (ObjCCategoryDecl *CatD = CatImplD->getCategoryDecl())
6439 return MakeCXCursor(CatD, getCursorTU(C));
6440
6441 if (const ObjCImplDecl *ImplD = dyn_cast<ObjCImplDecl>(D))
6442 if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *IFD = ImplD->getClassInterface())
6443 return MakeCXCursor(IFD, getCursorTU(C));
6444
6445 return MakeCXCursor(D->getCanonicalDecl(), getCursorTU(C));
6446 }
6447
6448 return C;
6449}
6450
6451int clang_Cursor_getObjCSelectorIndex(CXCursor cursor) {
6452 return cxcursor::getSelectorIdentifierIndexAndLoc(cursor).first;
6453}
6454
6455unsigned clang_getNumOverloadedDecls(CXCursor C) {
6456 if (C.kind != CXCursor_OverloadedDeclRef)
6457 return 0;
6458
6459 OverloadedDeclRefStorage Storage = getCursorOverloadedDeclRef(C).first;
6460 if (const OverloadExpr *E = Storage.dyn_cast<const OverloadExpr *>())
6461 return E->getNumDecls();
6462
6463 if (OverloadedTemplateStorage *S
6464 = Storage.dyn_cast<OverloadedTemplateStorage*>())
6465 return S->size();
6466
6467 const Decl *D = Storage.get<const Decl *>();
6468 if (const UsingDecl *Using = dyn_cast<UsingDecl>(D))
6469 return Using->shadow_size();
6470
6471 return 0;
6472}
6473
6474CXCursor clang_getOverloadedDecl(CXCursor cursor, unsigned index) {
6475 if (cursor.kind != CXCursor_OverloadedDeclRef)
6476 return clang_getNullCursor();
6477
6478 if (index >= clang_getNumOverloadedDecls(cursor))
6479 return clang_getNullCursor();
6480
6481 CXTranslationUnit TU = getCursorTU(cursor);
6482 OverloadedDeclRefStorage Storage = getCursorOverloadedDeclRef(cursor).first;
6483 if (const OverloadExpr *E = Storage.dyn_cast<const OverloadExpr *>())
6484 return MakeCXCursor(E->decls_begin()[index], TU);
6485
6486 if (OverloadedTemplateStorage *S
6487 = Storage.dyn_cast<OverloadedTemplateStorage*>())
6488 return MakeCXCursor(S->begin()[index], TU);
6489
6490 const Decl *D = Storage.get<const Decl *>();
6491 if (const UsingDecl *Using = dyn_cast<UsingDecl>(D)) {
6492 // FIXME: This is, unfortunately, linear time.
6493 UsingDecl::shadow_iterator Pos = Using->shadow_begin();
6494 std::advance(Pos, index);
6495 return MakeCXCursor(cast<UsingShadowDecl>(*Pos)->getTargetDecl(), TU);
6496 }
6497
6498 return clang_getNullCursor();
6499}
6500
6501void clang_getDefinitionSpellingAndExtent(CXCursor C,
6502 const char **startBuf,
6503 const char **endBuf,
6504 unsigned *startLine,
6505 unsigned *startColumn,
6506 unsigned *endLine,
6507 unsigned *endColumn) {
6508 assert(getCursorDecl(C) && "CXCursor has null decl");
6509 const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(getCursorDecl(C));
6510 CompoundStmt *Body = dyn_cast<CompoundStmt>(FD->getBody());
6511
6512 SourceManager &SM = FD->getASTContext().getSourceManager();
6513 *startBuf = SM.getCharacterData(Body->getLBracLoc());
6514 *endBuf = SM.getCharacterData(Body->getRBracLoc());
6515 *startLine = SM.getSpellingLineNumber(Body->getLBracLoc());
6516 *startColumn = SM.getSpellingColumnNumber(Body->getLBracLoc());
6517 *endLine = SM.getSpellingLineNumber(Body->getRBracLoc());
6518 *endColumn = SM.getSpellingColumnNumber(Body->getRBracLoc());
6519}
6520
6521
6522CXSourceRange clang_getCursorReferenceNameRange(CXCursor C, unsigned NameFlags,
6523 unsigned PieceIndex) {
6524 RefNamePieces Pieces;
6525
6526 switch (C.kind) {
6527 case CXCursor_MemberRefExpr:
6528 if (const MemberExpr *E = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(getCursorExpr(C)))
6529 Pieces = buildPieces(NameFlags, true, E->getMemberNameInfo(),
6530 E->getQualifierLoc().getSourceRange());
6531 break;
6532
6533 case CXCursor_DeclRefExpr:
6534 if (const DeclRefExpr *E = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(getCursorExpr(C))) {
6535 SourceRange TemplateArgLoc(E->getLAngleLoc(), E->getRAngleLoc());
6536 Pieces =
6537 buildPieces(NameFlags, false, E->getNameInfo(),
6538 E->getQualifierLoc().getSourceRange(), &TemplateArgLoc);
6539 }
6540 break;
6541
6542 case CXCursor_CallExpr:
6543 if (const CXXOperatorCallExpr *OCE =
6544 dyn_cast<CXXOperatorCallExpr>(getCursorExpr(C))) {
6545 const Expr *Callee = OCE->getCallee();
6546 if (const ImplicitCastExpr *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(Callee))
6547 Callee = ICE->getSubExpr();
6548
6549 if (const DeclRefExpr *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(Callee))
6550 Pieces = buildPieces(NameFlags, false, DRE->getNameInfo(),
6551 DRE->getQualifierLoc().getSourceRange());
6552 }
6553 break;
6554
6555 default:
6556 break;
6557 }
6558
6559 if (Pieces.empty()) {
6560 if (PieceIndex == 0)
6561 return clang_getCursorExtent(C);
6562 } else if (PieceIndex < Pieces.size()) {
6563 SourceRange R = Pieces[PieceIndex];
6564 if (R.isValid())
6565 return cxloc::translateSourceRange(getCursorContext(C), R);
6566 }
6567
6568 return clang_getNullRange();
6569}
6570
6571void clang_enableStackTraces(void) {
6572 // FIXME: Provide an argv0 here so we can find llvm-symbolizer.
6573 llvm::sys::PrintStackTraceOnErrorSignal(StringRef());
6574}
6575
6576void clang_executeOnThread(void (*fn)(void*), void *user_data,
6577 unsigned stack_size) {
6578 llvm::llvm_execute_on_thread(fn, user_data, stack_size);
6579}
6580
6581//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6582// Token-based Operations.
6583//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6584
6585/* CXToken layout:
6586 * int_data[0]: a CXTokenKind
6587 * int_data[1]: starting token location
6588 * int_data[2]: token length
6589 * int_data[3]: reserved
6590 * ptr_data: for identifiers and keywords, an IdentifierInfo*.
6591 * otherwise unused.
6592 */
6593CXTokenKind clang_getTokenKind(CXToken CXTok) {
6594 return static_cast<CXTokenKind>(CXTok.int_data[0]);
6595}
6596
6597CXString clang_getTokenSpelling(CXTranslationUnit TU, CXToken CXTok) {
6598 switch (clang_getTokenKind(CXTok)) {
6599 case CXToken_Identifier:
6600 case CXToken_Keyword:
6601 // We know we have an IdentifierInfo*, so use that.
6602 return cxstring::createRef(static_cast<IdentifierInfo *>(CXTok.ptr_data)
6603 ->getNameStart());
6604
6605 case CXToken_Literal: {
6606 // We have stashed the starting pointer in the ptr_data field. Use it.
6607 const char *Text = static_cast<const char *>(CXTok.ptr_data);
6608 return cxstring::createDup(StringRef(Text, CXTok.int_data[2]));
6609 }
6610
6611 case CXToken_Punctuation:
6612 case CXToken_Comment:
6613 break;
6614 }
6615
6616 if (isNotUsableTU(TU)) {
6617 LOG_BAD_TU(TU);
6618 return cxstring::createEmpty();
6619 }
6620
6621 // We have to find the starting buffer pointer the hard way, by
6622 // deconstructing the source location.
6623 ASTUnit *CXXUnit = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU);
6624 if (!CXXUnit)
6625 return cxstring::createEmpty();
6626
6627 SourceLocation Loc = SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(CXTok.int_data[1]);
6628 std::pair<FileID, unsigned> LocInfo
6629 = CXXUnit->getSourceManager().getDecomposedSpellingLoc(Loc);
6630 bool Invalid = false;
6631 StringRef Buffer
6632 = CXXUnit->getSourceManager().getBufferData(LocInfo.first, &Invalid);
6633 if (Invalid)
6634 return cxstring::createEmpty();
6635
6636 return cxstring::createDup(Buffer.substr(LocInfo.second, CXTok.int_data[2]));
6637}
6638
6639CXSourceLocation clang_getTokenLocation(CXTranslationUnit TU, CXToken CXTok) {
6640 if (isNotUsableTU(TU)) {
6641 LOG_BAD_TU(TU);
6642 return clang_getNullLocation();
6643 }
6644
6645 ASTUnit *CXXUnit = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU);
6646 if (!CXXUnit)
6647 return clang_getNullLocation();
6648
6649 return cxloc::translateSourceLocation(CXXUnit->getASTContext(),
6650 SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(CXTok.int_data[1]));
6651}
6652
6653CXSourceRange clang_getTokenExtent(CXTranslationUnit TU, CXToken CXTok) {
6654 if (isNotUsableTU(TU)) {
6655 LOG_BAD_TU(TU);
6656 return clang_getNullRange();
6657 }
6658
6659 ASTUnit *CXXUnit = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU);
6660 if (!CXXUnit)
6661 return clang_getNullRange();
6662
6663 return cxloc::translateSourceRange(CXXUnit->getASTContext(),
6664 SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(CXTok.int_data[1]));
6665}
6666
6667static void getTokens(ASTUnit *CXXUnit, SourceRange Range,
6668 SmallVectorImpl<CXToken> &CXTokens) {
6669 SourceManager &SourceMgr = CXXUnit->getSourceManager();
6670 std::pair<FileID, unsigned> BeginLocInfo
6671 = SourceMgr.getDecomposedSpellingLoc(Range.getBegin());
6672 std::pair<FileID, unsigned> EndLocInfo
6673 = SourceMgr.getDecomposedSpellingLoc(Range.getEnd());
6674
6675 // Cannot tokenize across files.
6676 if (BeginLocInfo.first != EndLocInfo.first)
6677 return;
6678
6679 // Create a lexer
6680 bool Invalid = false;
6681 StringRef Buffer
6682 = SourceMgr.getBufferData(BeginLocInfo.first, &Invalid);
6683 if (Invalid)
6684 return;
6685
6686 Lexer Lex(SourceMgr.getLocForStartOfFile(BeginLocInfo.first),
6687 CXXUnit->getASTContext().getLangOpts(),
6688 Buffer.begin(), Buffer.data() + BeginLocInfo.second, Buffer.end());
6689 Lex.SetCommentRetentionState(true);
6690
6691 // Lex tokens until we hit the end of the range.
6692 const char *EffectiveBufferEnd = Buffer.data() + EndLocInfo.second;
6693 Token Tok;
6694 bool previousWasAt = false;
6695 do {
6696 // Lex the next token
6697 Lex.LexFromRawLexer(Tok);
6698 if (Tok.is(tok::eof))
6699 break;
6700
6701 // Initialize the CXToken.
6702 CXToken CXTok;
6703
6704 // - Common fields
6705 CXTok.int_data[1] = Tok.getLocation().getRawEncoding();
6706 CXTok.int_data[2] = Tok.getLength();
6707 CXTok.int_data[3] = 0;
6708
6709 // - Kind-specific fields
6710 if (Tok.isLiteral()) {
6711 CXTok.int_data[0] = CXToken_Literal;
6712 CXTok.ptr_data = const_cast<char *>(Tok.getLiteralData());
6713 } else if (Tok.is(tok::raw_identifier)) {
6714 // Lookup the identifier to determine whether we have a keyword.
6715 IdentifierInfo *II
6716 = CXXUnit->getPreprocessor().LookUpIdentifierInfo(Tok);
6717
6718 if ((II->getObjCKeywordID() != tok::objc_not_keyword) && previousWasAt) {
6719 CXTok.int_data[0] = CXToken_Keyword;
6720 }
6721 else {
6722 CXTok.int_data[0] = Tok.is(tok::identifier)
6723 ? CXToken_Identifier
6724 : CXToken_Keyword;
6725 }
6726 CXTok.ptr_data = II;
6727 } else if (Tok.is(tok::comment)) {
6728 CXTok.int_data[0] = CXToken_Comment;
6729 CXTok.ptr_data = nullptr;
6730 } else {
6731 CXTok.int_data[0] = CXToken_Punctuation;
6732 CXTok.ptr_data = nullptr;
6733 }
6734 CXTokens.push_back(CXTok);
6735 previousWasAt = Tok.is(tok::at);
6736 } while (Lex.getBufferLocation() < EffectiveBufferEnd);
6737}
6738
6739CXToken *clang_getToken(CXTranslationUnit TU, CXSourceLocation Location) {
6740 LOG_FUNC_SECTION {
6741 *Log << TU << ' ' << Location;
6742 }
6743
6744 if (isNotUsableTU(TU)) {
6745 LOG_BAD_TU(TU);
6746 return NULL;
6747 }
6748
6749 ASTUnit *CXXUnit = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU);
6750 if (!CXXUnit)
6751 return NULL;
6752
6753 SourceLocation Begin = cxloc::translateSourceLocation(Location);
6754 if (Begin.isInvalid())
6755 return NULL;
6756 SourceManager &SM = CXXUnit->getSourceManager();
6757 std::pair<FileID, unsigned> DecomposedEnd = SM.getDecomposedLoc(Begin);
6758 DecomposedEnd.second += Lexer::MeasureTokenLength(Begin, SM, CXXUnit->getLangOpts());
6759
6760 SourceLocation End = SM.getComposedLoc(DecomposedEnd.first, DecomposedEnd.second);
6761
6762 SmallVector<CXToken, 32> CXTokens;
6763 getTokens(CXXUnit, SourceRange(Begin, End), CXTokens);
6764
6765 if (CXTokens.empty())
6766 return NULL;
6767
6768 CXTokens.resize(1);
6769 CXToken *Token = static_cast<CXToken *>(llvm::safe_malloc(sizeof(CXToken)));
6770
6771 memmove(Token, CXTokens.data(), sizeof(CXToken));
6772 return Token;
6773}
6774
6775void clang_tokenize(CXTranslationUnit TU, CXSourceRange Range,
6776 CXToken **Tokens, unsigned *NumTokens) {
6777 LOG_FUNC_SECTION {
6778 *Log << TU << ' ' << Range;
6779 }
6780
6781 if (Tokens)
6782 *Tokens = nullptr;
6783 if (NumTokens)
6784 *NumTokens = 0;
6785
6786 if (isNotUsableTU(TU)) {
6787 LOG_BAD_TU(TU);
6788 return;
6789 }
6790
6791 ASTUnit *CXXUnit = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU);
6792 if (!CXXUnit || !Tokens || !NumTokens)
6793 return;
6794
6795 ASTUnit::ConcurrencyCheck Check(*CXXUnit);
6796
6797 SourceRange R = cxloc::translateCXSourceRange(Range);
6798 if (R.isInvalid())
6799 return;
6800
6801 SmallVector<CXToken, 32> CXTokens;
6802 getTokens(CXXUnit, R, CXTokens);
6803
6804 if (CXTokens.empty())
6805 return;
6806
6807 *Tokens = static_cast<CXToken *>(
6808 llvm::safe_malloc(sizeof(CXToken) * CXTokens.size()));
6809 memmove(*Tokens, CXTokens.data(), sizeof(CXToken) * CXTokens.size());
6810 *NumTokens = CXTokens.size();
6811}
6812
6813void clang_disposeTokens(CXTranslationUnit TU,
6814 CXToken *Tokens, unsigned NumTokens) {
6815 free(Tokens);
6816}
