6818//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6819// Token annotation APIs.
6820//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6821
6822static enum CXChildVisitResult AnnotateTokensVisitor(CXCursor cursor,
6823 CXCursor parent,
6824 CXClientData client_data);
6825static bool AnnotateTokensPostChildrenVisitor(CXCursor cursor,
6826 CXClientData client_data);
6827
6828namespace {
6829class AnnotateTokensWorker {
6830 CXToken *Tokens;
6831 CXCursor *Cursors;
6832 unsigned NumTokens;
6833 unsigned TokIdx;
6834 unsigned PreprocessingTokIdx;
6835 CursorVisitor AnnotateVis;
6836 SourceManager &SrcMgr;
6837 bool HasContextSensitiveKeywords;
6838
6839 struct PostChildrenAction {
6840 CXCursor cursor;
6841 enum Action { Invalid, Ignore, Postpone } action;
6842 };
6843 using PostChildrenActions = SmallVector<PostChildrenAction, 0>;
6844
6845 struct PostChildrenInfo {
6846 CXCursor Cursor;
6847 SourceRange CursorRange;
6848 unsigned BeforeReachingCursorIdx;
6849 unsigned BeforeChildrenTokenIdx;
6850 PostChildrenActions ChildActions;
6851 };
6852 SmallVector<PostChildrenInfo, 8> PostChildrenInfos;
6853
6854 CXToken &getTok(unsigned Idx) {
6855 assert(Idx < NumTokens);
6856 return Tokens[Idx];
6857 }
6858 const CXToken &getTok(unsigned Idx) const {
6859 assert(Idx < NumTokens);
6860 return Tokens[Idx];
6861 }
6862 bool MoreTokens() const { return TokIdx < NumTokens; }
6863 unsigned NextToken() const { return TokIdx; }
6864 void AdvanceToken() { ++TokIdx; }
6865 SourceLocation GetTokenLoc(unsigned tokI) {
6866 return SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(getTok(tokI).int_data[1]);
6867 }
6868 bool isFunctionMacroToken(unsigned tokI) const {
6869 return getTok(tokI).int_data[3] != 0;
6870 }
6871 SourceLocation getFunctionMacroTokenLoc(unsigned tokI) const {
6872 return SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(getTok(tokI).int_data[3]);
6873 }
6874
6875 void annotateAndAdvanceTokens(CXCursor, RangeComparisonResult, SourceRange);
6876 bool annotateAndAdvanceFunctionMacroTokens(CXCursor, RangeComparisonResult,
6877 SourceRange);
6878
6879public:
6880 AnnotateTokensWorker(CXToken *tokens, CXCursor *cursors, unsigned numTokens,
6881 CXTranslationUnit TU, SourceRange RegionOfInterest)
6882 : Tokens(tokens), Cursors(cursors),
6883 NumTokens(numTokens), TokIdx(0), PreprocessingTokIdx(0),
6884 AnnotateVis(TU,
6885 AnnotateTokensVisitor, this,
6886 /*VisitPreprocessorLast=*/true,
6887 /*VisitIncludedEntities=*/false,
6888 RegionOfInterest,
6889 /*VisitDeclsOnly=*/false,
6890 AnnotateTokensPostChildrenVisitor),
6891 SrcMgr(cxtu::getASTUnit(TU)->getSourceManager()),
6892 HasContextSensitiveKeywords(false) { }
6893
6894 void VisitChildren(CXCursor C) { AnnotateVis.VisitChildren(C); }
6895 enum CXChildVisitResult Visit(CXCursor cursor, CXCursor parent);
6896 bool IsIgnoredChildCursor(CXCursor cursor) const;
6897 PostChildrenActions DetermineChildActions(CXCursor Cursor) const;
6898
6899 bool postVisitChildren(CXCursor cursor);
6900 void HandlePostPonedChildCursors(const PostChildrenInfo &Info);
6901 void HandlePostPonedChildCursor(CXCursor Cursor, unsigned StartTokenIndex);
6902
6903 void AnnotateTokens();
6904
6905 /// Determine whether the annotator saw any cursors that have
6906 /// context-sensitive keywords.
6907 bool hasContextSensitiveKeywords() const {
6908 return HasContextSensitiveKeywords;
6909 }
6910
6911 ~AnnotateTokensWorker() {
6912 assert(PostChildrenInfos.empty());
6913 }
6914};
6915}
6916
6917void AnnotateTokensWorker::AnnotateTokens() {
6918 // Walk the AST within the region of interest, annotating tokens
6919 // along the way.
6920 AnnotateVis.visitFileRegion();
6921}
6922
6923bool AnnotateTokensWorker::IsIgnoredChildCursor(CXCursor cursor) const {
6924 if (PostChildrenInfos.empty())
6925 return false;
6926
6927 for (const auto &ChildAction : PostChildrenInfos.back().ChildActions) {
6928 if (ChildAction.cursor == cursor &&
6929 ChildAction.action == PostChildrenAction::Ignore) {
6930 return true;
6931 }
6932 }
6933
6934 return false;
6935}
6936
6937const CXXOperatorCallExpr *GetSubscriptOrCallOperator(CXCursor Cursor) {
6938 if (!clang_isExpression(Cursor.kind))
6939 return nullptr;
6940
6941 const Expr *E = getCursorExpr(Cursor);
6942 if (const auto *OCE = dyn_cast<CXXOperatorCallExpr>(E)) {
6943 const OverloadedOperatorKind Kind = OCE->getOperator();
6944 if (Kind == OO_Call || Kind == OO_Subscript)
6945 return OCE;
6946 }
6947
6948 return nullptr;
6949}
6950
6951AnnotateTokensWorker::PostChildrenActions
6952AnnotateTokensWorker::DetermineChildActions(CXCursor Cursor) const {
6953 PostChildrenActions actions;
6954
6955 // The DeclRefExpr of CXXOperatorCallExpr refering to the custom operator is
6956 // visited before the arguments to the operator call. For the Call and
6957 // Subscript operator the range of this DeclRefExpr includes the whole call
6958 // expression, so that all tokens in that range would be mapped to the
6959 // operator function, including the tokens of the arguments. To avoid that,
6960 // ensure to visit this DeclRefExpr as last node.
6961 if (const auto *OCE = GetSubscriptOrCallOperator(Cursor)) {
6962 const Expr *Callee = OCE->getCallee();
6963 if (const ImplicitCastExpr *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(Callee)) {
6964 const Expr *SubExpr = ICE->getSubExpr();
6965 if (const DeclRefExpr *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(SubExpr)) {
6966 const Decl *parentDecl = getCursorDecl(Cursor);
6967 CXTranslationUnit TU = clang_Cursor_getTranslationUnit(Cursor);
6968
6969 // Visit the DeclRefExpr as last.
6970 CXCursor cxChild = MakeCXCursor(DRE, parentDecl, TU);
6971 actions.push_back({cxChild, PostChildrenAction::Postpone});
6972
6973 // The parent of the DeclRefExpr, an ImplicitCastExpr, has an equally
6974 // wide range as the DeclRefExpr. We can skip visiting this entirely.
6975 cxChild = MakeCXCursor(ICE, parentDecl, TU);
6976 actions.push_back({cxChild, PostChildrenAction::Ignore});
6977 }
6978 }
6979 }
6980
6981 return actions;
6982}
6983
6984static inline void updateCursorAnnotation(CXCursor &Cursor,
6985 const CXCursor &updateC) {
6986 if (clang_isInvalid(updateC.kind) || !clang_isInvalid(Cursor.kind))
6987 return;
6988 Cursor = updateC;
6989}
6990
6991/// It annotates and advances tokens with a cursor until the comparison
6992//// between the cursor location and the source range is the same as
6993/// \arg compResult.
6994///
6995/// Pass RangeBefore to annotate tokens with a cursor until a range is reached.
6996/// Pass RangeOverlap to annotate tokens inside a range.
6997void AnnotateTokensWorker::annotateAndAdvanceTokens(CXCursor updateC,
6998 RangeComparisonResult compResult,
6999 SourceRange range) {
7000 while (MoreTokens()) {
7001 const unsigned I = NextToken();
7002 if (isFunctionMacroToken(I))
7003 if (!annotateAndAdvanceFunctionMacroTokens(updateC, compResult, range))
7004 return;
7005
7006 SourceLocation TokLoc = GetTokenLoc(I);
7007 if (LocationCompare(SrcMgr, TokLoc, range) == compResult) {
7008 updateCursorAnnotation(Cursors[I], updateC);
7009 AdvanceToken();
7010 continue;
7011 }
7012 break;
7013 }
7014}
7015
7016/// Special annotation handling for macro argument tokens.
7017/// \returns true if it advanced beyond all macro tokens, false otherwise.
7018bool AnnotateTokensWorker::annotateAndAdvanceFunctionMacroTokens(
7019 CXCursor updateC,
7020 RangeComparisonResult compResult,
7021 SourceRange range) {
7022 assert(MoreTokens());
7023 assert(isFunctionMacroToken(NextToken()) &&
7024 "Should be called only for macro arg tokens");
7025
7026 // This works differently than annotateAndAdvanceTokens; because expanded
7027 // macro arguments can have arbitrary translation-unit source order, we do not
7028 // advance the token index one by one until a token fails the range test.
7029 // We only advance once past all of the macro arg tokens if all of them
7030 // pass the range test. If one of them fails we keep the token index pointing
7031 // at the start of the macro arg tokens so that the failing token will be
7032 // annotated by a subsequent annotation try.
7033
7034 bool atLeastOneCompFail = false;
7035
7036 unsigned I = NextToken();
7037 for (; I < NumTokens && isFunctionMacroToken(I); ++I) {
7038 SourceLocation TokLoc = getFunctionMacroTokenLoc(I);
7039 if (TokLoc.isFileID())
7040 continue; // not macro arg token, it's parens or comma.
7041 if (LocationCompare(SrcMgr, TokLoc, range) == compResult) {
7042 if (clang_isInvalid(clang_getCursorKind(Cursors[I])))
7043 Cursors[I] = updateC;
7044 } else
7045 atLeastOneCompFail = true;
7046 }
7047
7048 if (atLeastOneCompFail)
7049 return false;
7050
7051 TokIdx = I; // All of the tokens were handled, advance beyond all of them.
7052 return true;
7053}
7054
7055enum CXChildVisitResult
7056AnnotateTokensWorker::Visit(CXCursor cursor, CXCursor parent) {
7057 SourceRange cursorRange = getRawCursorExtent(cursor);
7058 if (cursorRange.isInvalid())
7059 return CXChildVisit_Recurse;
7060
7061 if (IsIgnoredChildCursor(cursor))
7062 return CXChildVisit_Continue;
7063
7064 if (!HasContextSensitiveKeywords) {
7065 // Objective-C properties can have context-sensitive keywords.
7066 if (cursor.kind == CXCursor_ObjCPropertyDecl) {
7067 if (const ObjCPropertyDecl *Property
7068 = dyn_cast_or_null<ObjCPropertyDecl>(getCursorDecl(cursor)))
7069 HasContextSensitiveKeywords = Property->getPropertyAttributesAsWritten() != 0;
7070 }
7071 // Objective-C methods can have context-sensitive keywords.
7072 else if (cursor.kind == CXCursor_ObjCInstanceMethodDecl ||
7073 cursor.kind == CXCursor_ObjCClassMethodDecl) {
7074 if (const ObjCMethodDecl *Method
7075 = dyn_cast_or_null<ObjCMethodDecl>(getCursorDecl(cursor))) {
7076 if (Method->getObjCDeclQualifier())
7077 HasContextSensitiveKeywords = true;
7078 else {
7079 for (const auto *P : Method->parameters()) {
7080 if (P->getObjCDeclQualifier()) {
7081 HasContextSensitiveKeywords = true;
7082 break;
7083 }
7084 }
7085 }
7086 }
7087 }
7088 // C++ methods can have context-sensitive keywords.
7089 else if (cursor.kind == CXCursor_CXXMethod) {
7090 if (const CXXMethodDecl *Method
7091 = dyn_cast_or_null<CXXMethodDecl>(getCursorDecl(cursor))) {
7092 if (Method->hasAttr<FinalAttr>() || Method->hasAttr<OverrideAttr>())
7093 HasContextSensitiveKeywords = true;
7094 }
7095 }
7096 // C++ classes can have context-sensitive keywords.
7097 else if (cursor.kind == CXCursor_StructDecl ||
7098 cursor.kind == CXCursor_ClassDecl ||
7099 cursor.kind == CXCursor_ClassTemplate ||
7100 cursor.kind == CXCursor_ClassTemplatePartialSpecialization) {
7101 if (const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(cursor))
7102 if (D->hasAttr<FinalAttr>())
7103 HasContextSensitiveKeywords = true;
7104 }
7105 }
7106
7107 // Don't override a property annotation with its getter/setter method.
7108 if (cursor.kind == CXCursor_ObjCInstanceMethodDecl &&
7109 parent.kind == CXCursor_ObjCPropertyDecl)
7110 return CXChildVisit_Continue;
7111
7112 if (clang_isPreprocessing(cursor.kind)) {
7113 // Items in the preprocessing record are kept separate from items in
7114 // declarations, so we keep a separate token index.
7115 unsigned SavedTokIdx = TokIdx;
7116 TokIdx = PreprocessingTokIdx;
7117
7118 // Skip tokens up until we catch up to the beginning of the preprocessing
7119 // entry.
7120 while (MoreTokens()) {
7121 const unsigned I = NextToken();
7122 SourceLocation TokLoc = GetTokenLoc(I);
7123 switch (LocationCompare(SrcMgr, TokLoc, cursorRange)) {
7124 case RangeBefore:
7125 AdvanceToken();
7126 continue;
7127 case RangeAfter:
7128 case RangeOverlap:
7129 break;
7130 }
7131 break;
7132 }
7133
7134 // Look at all of the tokens within this range.
7135 while (MoreTokens()) {
7136 const unsigned I = NextToken();
7137 SourceLocation TokLoc = GetTokenLoc(I);
7138 switch (LocationCompare(SrcMgr, TokLoc, cursorRange)) {
7139 case RangeBefore:
7140 llvm_unreachable("Infeasible");
7141 case RangeAfter:
7142 break;
7143 case RangeOverlap:
7144 // For macro expansions, just note where the beginning of the macro
7145 // expansion occurs.
7146 if (cursor.kind == CXCursor_MacroExpansion) {
7147 if (TokLoc == cursorRange.getBegin())
7148 Cursors[I] = cursor;
7149 AdvanceToken();
7150 break;
7151 }
7152 // We may have already annotated macro names inside macro definitions.
7153 if (Cursors[I].kind != CXCursor_MacroExpansion)
7154 Cursors[I] = cursor;
7155 AdvanceToken();
7156 continue;
7157 }
7158 break;
7159 }
7160
7161 // Save the preprocessing token index; restore the non-preprocessing
7162 // token index.
7163 PreprocessingTokIdx = TokIdx;
7164 TokIdx = SavedTokIdx;
7165 return CXChildVisit_Recurse;
7166 }
7167
7168 if (cursorRange.isInvalid())
7169 return CXChildVisit_Continue;
7170
7171 unsigned BeforeReachingCursorIdx = NextToken();
7172 const enum CXCursorKind cursorK = clang_getCursorKind(cursor);
7173 const enum CXCursorKind K = clang_getCursorKind(parent);
7174 const CXCursor updateC =
7175 (clang_isInvalid(K) || K == CXCursor_TranslationUnit ||
7176 // Attributes are annotated out-of-order, skip tokens until we reach it.
7177 clang_isAttribute(cursor.kind))
7178 ? clang_getNullCursor() : parent;
7179
7180 annotateAndAdvanceTokens(updateC, RangeBefore, cursorRange);
7181
7182 // Avoid having the cursor of an expression "overwrite" the annotation of the
7183 // variable declaration that it belongs to.
7184 // This can happen for C++ constructor expressions whose range generally
7185 // include the variable declaration, e.g.:
7186 // MyCXXClass foo; // Make sure we don't annotate 'foo' as a CallExpr cursor.
7187 if (clang_isExpression(cursorK) && MoreTokens()) {
7188 const Expr *E = getCursorExpr(cursor);
7189 if (const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(cursor)) {
7190 const unsigned I = NextToken();
7191 if (E->getBeginLoc().isValid() && D->getLocation().isValid() &&
7192 E->getBeginLoc() == D->getLocation() &&
7193 E->getBeginLoc() == GetTokenLoc(I)) {
7194 updateCursorAnnotation(Cursors[I], updateC);
7195 AdvanceToken();
7196 }
7197 }
7198 }
7199
7200 // Before recursing into the children keep some state that we are going
7201 // to use in the AnnotateTokensWorker::postVisitChildren callback to do some
7202 // extra work after the child nodes are visited.
7203 // Note that we don't call VisitChildren here to avoid traversing statements
7204 // code-recursively which can blow the stack.
7205
7206 PostChildrenInfo Info;
7207 Info.Cursor = cursor;
7208 Info.CursorRange = cursorRange;
7209 Info.BeforeReachingCursorIdx = BeforeReachingCursorIdx;
7210 Info.BeforeChildrenTokenIdx = NextToken();
7211 Info.ChildActions = DetermineChildActions(cursor);
7212 PostChildrenInfos.push_back(Info);
7213
7214 return CXChildVisit_Recurse;
7215}
7216
7217bool AnnotateTokensWorker::postVisitChildren(CXCursor cursor) {
7218 if (PostChildrenInfos.empty())
7219 return false;
7220 const PostChildrenInfo &Info = PostChildrenInfos.back();
7221 if (!clang_equalCursors(Info.Cursor, cursor))
7222 return false;
7223
7224 HandlePostPonedChildCursors(Info);
7225
7226 const unsigned BeforeChildren = Info.BeforeChildrenTokenIdx;
7227 const unsigned AfterChildren = NextToken();
7228 SourceRange cursorRange = Info.CursorRange;
7229
7230 // Scan the tokens that are at the end of the cursor, but are not captured
7231 // but the child cursors.
7232 annotateAndAdvanceTokens(cursor, RangeOverlap, cursorRange);
7233
7234 // Scan the tokens that are at the beginning of the cursor, but are not
7235 // capture by the child cursors.
7236 for (unsigned I = BeforeChildren; I != AfterChildren; ++I) {
7237 if (!clang_isInvalid(clang_getCursorKind(Cursors[I])))
7238 break;
7239
7240 Cursors[I] = cursor;
7241 }
7242
7243 // Attributes are annotated out-of-order, rewind TokIdx to when we first
7244 // encountered the attribute cursor.
7245 if (clang_isAttribute(cursor.kind))
7246 TokIdx = Info.BeforeReachingCursorIdx;
7247
7248 PostChildrenInfos.pop_back();
7249 return false;
7250}
7251
7252void AnnotateTokensWorker::HandlePostPonedChildCursors(
7253 const PostChildrenInfo &Info) {
7254 for (const auto &ChildAction : Info.ChildActions) {
7255 if (ChildAction.action == PostChildrenAction::Postpone) {
7256 HandlePostPonedChildCursor(ChildAction.cursor,
7257 Info.BeforeChildrenTokenIdx);
7258 }
7259 }
7260}
7261
7262void AnnotateTokensWorker::HandlePostPonedChildCursor(
7263 CXCursor Cursor, unsigned StartTokenIndex) {
7264 unsigned I = StartTokenIndex;
7265
7266 // The bracket tokens of a Call or Subscript operator are mapped to
7267 // CallExpr/CXXOperatorCallExpr because we skipped visiting the corresponding
7268 // DeclRefExpr. Remap these tokens to the DeclRefExpr cursors.
7269 for (unsigned RefNameRangeNr = 0; I < NumTokens; RefNameRangeNr++) {
7270 const CXSourceRange CXRefNameRange = clang_getCursorReferenceNameRange(
7271 Cursor, CXNameRange_WantQualifier, RefNameRangeNr);
7272 if (clang_Range_isNull(CXRefNameRange))
7273 break; // All ranges handled.
7274
7275 SourceRange RefNameRange = cxloc::translateCXSourceRange(CXRefNameRange);
7276 while (I < NumTokens) {
7277 const SourceLocation TokenLocation = GetTokenLoc(I);
7278 if (!TokenLocation.isValid())
7279 break;
7280
7281 // Adapt the end range, because LocationCompare() reports
7282 // RangeOverlap even for the not-inclusive end location.
7283 const SourceLocation fixedEnd =
7284 RefNameRange.getEnd().getLocWithOffset(-1);
7285 RefNameRange = SourceRange(RefNameRange.getBegin(), fixedEnd);
7286
7287 const RangeComparisonResult ComparisonResult =
7288 LocationCompare(SrcMgr, TokenLocation, RefNameRange);
7289
7290 if (ComparisonResult == RangeOverlap) {
7291 Cursors[I++] = Cursor;
7292 } else if (ComparisonResult == RangeBefore) {
7293 ++I; // Not relevant token, check next one.
7294 } else if (ComparisonResult == RangeAfter) {
7295 break; // All tokens updated for current range, check next.
7296 }
7297 }
7298 }
7299}
7300
7301static enum CXChildVisitResult AnnotateTokensVisitor(CXCursor cursor,
7302 CXCursor parent,
7303 CXClientData client_data) {
7304 return static_cast<AnnotateTokensWorker*>(client_data)->Visit(cursor, parent);
7305}
7306
7307static bool AnnotateTokensPostChildrenVisitor(CXCursor cursor,
7308 CXClientData client_data) {
7309 return static_cast<AnnotateTokensWorker*>(client_data)->
7310 postVisitChildren(cursor);
7311}
7312
7313namespace {
7314
7315/// Uses the macro expansions in the preprocessing record to find
7316/// and mark tokens that are macro arguments. This info is used by the
7317/// AnnotateTokensWorker.
7318class MarkMacroArgTokensVisitor {
7319 SourceManager &SM;
7320 CXToken *Tokens;
7321 unsigned NumTokens;
7322 unsigned CurIdx;
7323
7324public:
7325 MarkMacroArgTokensVisitor(SourceManager &SM,
7326 CXToken *tokens, unsigned numTokens)
7327 : SM(SM), Tokens(tokens), NumTokens(numTokens), CurIdx(0) { }
7328
7329 CXChildVisitResult visit(CXCursor cursor, CXCursor parent) {
7330 if (cursor.kind != CXCursor_MacroExpansion)
7331 return CXChildVisit_Continue;
7332
7333 SourceRange macroRange = getCursorMacroExpansion(cursor).getSourceRange();
7334 if (macroRange.getBegin() == macroRange.getEnd())
7335 return CXChildVisit_Continue; // it's not a function macro.
7336
7337 for (; CurIdx < NumTokens; ++CurIdx) {
7338 if (!SM.isBeforeInTranslationUnit(getTokenLoc(CurIdx),
7339 macroRange.getBegin()))
7340 break;
7341 }
7342
7343 if (CurIdx == NumTokens)
7344 return CXChildVisit_Break;
7345
7346 for (; CurIdx < NumTokens; ++CurIdx) {
7347 SourceLocation tokLoc = getTokenLoc(CurIdx);
7348 if (!SM.isBeforeInTranslationUnit(tokLoc, macroRange.getEnd()))
7349 break;
7350
7351 setFunctionMacroTokenLoc(CurIdx, SM.getMacroArgExpandedLocation(tokLoc));
7352 }
7353
7354 if (CurIdx == NumTokens)
7355 return CXChildVisit_Break;
7356
7357 return CXChildVisit_Continue;
7358 }
7359
7360private:
7361 CXToken &getTok(unsigned Idx) {
7362 assert(Idx < NumTokens);
7363 return Tokens[Idx];
7364 }
7365 const CXToken &getTok(unsigned Idx) const {
7366 assert(Idx < NumTokens);
7367 return Tokens[Idx];
7368 }
7369
7370 SourceLocation getTokenLoc(unsigned tokI) {
7371 return SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(getTok(tokI).int_data[1]);
7372 }
7373
7374 void setFunctionMacroTokenLoc(unsigned tokI, SourceLocation loc) {
7375 // The third field is reserved and currently not used. Use it here
7376 // to mark macro arg expanded tokens with their expanded locations.
7377 getTok(tokI).int_data[3] = loc.getRawEncoding();
7378 }
7379};
7380
7381} // end anonymous namespace
7382
7383static CXChildVisitResult
7384MarkMacroArgTokensVisitorDelegate(CXCursor cursor, CXCursor parent,
7385 CXClientData client_data) {
7386 return static_cast<MarkMacroArgTokensVisitor*>(client_data)->visit(cursor,
7387 parent);
7388}
7389
7390/// Used by \c annotatePreprocessorTokens.
7391/// \returns true if lexing was finished, false otherwise.
7392static bool lexNext(Lexer &Lex, Token &Tok,
7393 unsigned &NextIdx, unsigned NumTokens) {
7394 if (NextIdx >= NumTokens)
7395 return true;
7396
7397 ++NextIdx;
7398 Lex.LexFromRawLexer(Tok);
7399 return Tok.is(tok::eof);
7400}
7401
7402static void annotatePreprocessorTokens(CXTranslationUnit TU,
7403 SourceRange RegionOfInterest,
7404 CXCursor *Cursors,
7405 CXToken *Tokens,
7406 unsigned NumTokens) {
7407 ASTUnit *CXXUnit = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU);
7408
7409 Preprocessor &PP = CXXUnit->getPreprocessor();
7410 SourceManager &SourceMgr = CXXUnit->getSourceManager();
7411 std::pair<FileID, unsigned> BeginLocInfo
7412 = SourceMgr.getDecomposedSpellingLoc(RegionOfInterest.getBegin());
7413 std::pair<FileID, unsigned> EndLocInfo
7414 = SourceMgr.getDecomposedSpellingLoc(RegionOfInterest.getEnd());
7415
7416 if (BeginLocInfo.first != EndLocInfo.first)
7417 return;
7418
7419 StringRef Buffer;
7420 bool Invalid = false;
7421 Buffer = SourceMgr.getBufferData(BeginLocInfo.first, &Invalid);
7422 if (Buffer.empty() || Invalid)
7423 return;
7424
7425 Lexer Lex(SourceMgr.getLocForStartOfFile(BeginLocInfo.first),
7426 CXXUnit->getASTContext().getLangOpts(),
7427 Buffer.begin(), Buffer.data() + BeginLocInfo.second,
7428 Buffer.end());
7429 Lex.SetCommentRetentionState(true);
7430
7431 unsigned NextIdx = 0;
7432 // Lex tokens in raw mode until we hit the end of the range, to avoid
7433 // entering #includes or expanding macros.
7434 while (true) {
7435 Token Tok;
7436 if (lexNext(Lex, Tok, NextIdx, NumTokens))
7437 break;
7438 unsigned TokIdx = NextIdx-1;
7439 assert(Tok.getLocation() ==
7440 SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(Tokens[TokIdx].int_data[1]));
7441
7442 reprocess:
7443 if (Tok.is(tok::hash) && Tok.isAtStartOfLine()) {
7444 // We have found a preprocessing directive. Annotate the tokens
7445 // appropriately.
7446 //
7447 // FIXME: Some simple tests here could identify macro definitions and
7448 // #undefs, to provide specific cursor kinds for those.
7449
7450 SourceLocation BeginLoc = Tok.getLocation();
7451 if (lexNext(Lex, Tok, NextIdx, NumTokens))
7452 break;
7453
7454 MacroInfo *MI = nullptr;
7455 if (Tok.is(tok::raw_identifier) && Tok.getRawIdentifier() == "define") {
7456 if (lexNext(Lex, Tok, NextIdx, NumTokens))
7457 break;
7458
7459 if (Tok.is(tok::raw_identifier)) {
7460 IdentifierInfo &II =
7461 PP.getIdentifierTable().get(Tok.getRawIdentifier());
7462 SourceLocation MappedTokLoc =
7463 CXXUnit->mapLocationToPreamble(Tok.getLocation());
7464 MI = getMacroInfo(II, MappedTokLoc, TU);
7465 }
7466 }
7467
7468 bool finished = false;
7469 do {
7470 if (lexNext(Lex, Tok, NextIdx, NumTokens)) {
7471 finished = true;
7472 break;
7473 }
7474 // If we are in a macro definition, check if the token was ever a
7475 // macro name and annotate it if that's the case.
7476 if (MI) {
7477 SourceLocation SaveLoc = Tok.getLocation();
7478 Tok.setLocation(CXXUnit->mapLocationToPreamble(SaveLoc));
7479 MacroDefinitionRecord *MacroDef =
7480 checkForMacroInMacroDefinition(MI, Tok, TU);
7481 Tok.setLocation(SaveLoc);
7482 if (MacroDef)
7483 Cursors[NextIdx - 1] =
7484 MakeMacroExpansionCursor(MacroDef, Tok.getLocation(), TU);
7485 }
7486 } while (!Tok.isAtStartOfLine());
7487
7488 unsigned LastIdx = finished ? NextIdx-1 : NextIdx-2;
7489 assert(TokIdx <= LastIdx);
7490 SourceLocation EndLoc =
7491 SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(Tokens[LastIdx].int_data[1]);
7492 CXCursor Cursor =
7493 MakePreprocessingDirectiveCursor(SourceRange(BeginLoc, EndLoc), TU);
7494
7495 for (; TokIdx <= LastIdx; ++TokIdx)
7496 updateCursorAnnotation(Cursors[TokIdx], Cursor);
7497
7498 if (finished)
7499 break;
7500 goto reprocess;
7501 }
7502 }
7503}
7504
7505// This gets run a separate thread to avoid stack blowout.
7506static void clang_annotateTokensImpl(CXTranslationUnit TU, ASTUnit *CXXUnit,
7507 CXToken *Tokens, unsigned NumTokens,
7508 CXCursor *Cursors) {
7509 CIndexer *CXXIdx = TU->CIdx;
7510 if (CXXIdx->isOptEnabled(CXGlobalOpt_ThreadBackgroundPriorityForEditing))
7511 setThreadBackgroundPriority();
7512
7513 // Determine the region of interest, which contains all of the tokens.
7514 SourceRange RegionOfInterest;
7515 RegionOfInterest.setBegin(
7516 cxloc::translateSourceLocation(clang_getTokenLocation(TU, Tokens[0])));
7517 RegionOfInterest.setEnd(
7518 cxloc::translateSourceLocation(clang_getTokenLocation(TU,
7519 Tokens[NumTokens-1])));
7520
7521 // Relex the tokens within the source range to look for preprocessing
7522 // directives.
7523 annotatePreprocessorTokens(TU, RegionOfInterest, Cursors, Tokens, NumTokens);
7524
7525 // If begin location points inside a macro argument, set it to the expansion
7526 // location so we can have the full context when annotating semantically.
7527 {
7528 SourceManager &SM = CXXUnit->getSourceManager();
7529 SourceLocation Loc =
7530 SM.getMacroArgExpandedLocation(RegionOfInterest.getBegin());
7531 if (Loc.isMacroID())
7532 RegionOfInterest.setBegin(SM.getExpansionLoc(Loc));
7533 }
7534
7535 if (CXXUnit->getPreprocessor().getPreprocessingRecord()) {
7536 // Search and mark tokens that are macro argument expansions.
7537 MarkMacroArgTokensVisitor Visitor(CXXUnit->getSourceManager(),
7538 Tokens, NumTokens);
7539 CursorVisitor MacroArgMarker(TU,
7540 MarkMacroArgTokensVisitorDelegate, &Visitor,
7541 /*VisitPreprocessorLast=*/true,
7542 /*VisitIncludedEntities=*/false,
7543 RegionOfInterest);
7544 MacroArgMarker.visitPreprocessedEntitiesInRegion();
7545 }
7546
7547 // Annotate all of the source locations in the region of interest that map to
7548 // a specific cursor.
7549 AnnotateTokensWorker W(Tokens, Cursors, NumTokens, TU, RegionOfInterest);
7550
7551 // FIXME: We use a ridiculous stack size here because the data-recursion
7552 // algorithm uses a large stack frame than the non-data recursive version,
7553 // and AnnotationTokensWorker currently transforms the data-recursion
7554 // algorithm back into a traditional recursion by explicitly calling
7555 // VisitChildren(). We will need to remove this explicit recursive call.
7556 W.AnnotateTokens();
7557
7558 // If we ran into any entities that involve context-sensitive keywords,
7559 // take another pass through the tokens to mark them as such.
7560 if (W.hasContextSensitiveKeywords()) {
7561 for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumTokens; ++I) {
7562 if (clang_getTokenKind(Tokens[I]) != CXToken_Identifier)
7563 continue;
7564
7565 if (Cursors[I].kind == CXCursor_ObjCPropertyDecl) {
7566 IdentifierInfo *II = static_cast<IdentifierInfo *>(Tokens[I].ptr_data);
7567 if (const ObjCPropertyDecl *Property
7568 = dyn_cast_or_null<ObjCPropertyDecl>(getCursorDecl(Cursors[I]))) {
7569 if (Property->getPropertyAttributesAsWritten() != 0 &&
7570 llvm::StringSwitch<bool>(II->getName())
7571 .Case("readonly", true)
7572 .Case("assign", true)
7573 .Case("unsafe_unretained", true)
7574 .Case("readwrite", true)
7575 .Case("retain", true)
7576 .Case("copy", true)
7577 .Case("nonatomic", true)
7578 .Case("atomic", true)
7579 .Case("getter", true)
7580 .Case("setter", true)
7581 .Case("strong", true)
7582 .Case("weak", true)
7583 .Case("class", true)
7584 .Default(false))
7585 Tokens[I].int_data[0] = CXToken_Keyword;
7586 }
7587 continue;
7588 }
7589
7590 if (Cursors[I].kind == CXCursor_ObjCInstanceMethodDecl ||
7591 Cursors[I].kind == CXCursor_ObjCClassMethodDecl) {
7592 IdentifierInfo *II = static_cast<IdentifierInfo *>(Tokens[I].ptr_data);
7593 if (llvm::StringSwitch<bool>(II->getName())
7594 .Case("in", true)
7595 .Case("out", true)
7596 .Case("inout", true)
7597 .Case("oneway", true)
7598 .Case("bycopy", true)
7599 .Case("byref", true)
7600 .Default(false))
7601 Tokens[I].int_data[0] = CXToken_Keyword;
7602 continue;
7603 }
7604
7605 if (Cursors[I].kind == CXCursor_CXXFinalAttr ||
7606 Cursors[I].kind == CXCursor_CXXOverrideAttr) {
7607 Tokens[I].int_data[0] = CXToken_Keyword;
7608 continue;
7609 }
7610 }
7611 }
7612}
7613
7614void clang_annotateTokens(CXTranslationUnit TU,
7615 CXToken *Tokens, unsigned NumTokens,
7616 CXCursor *Cursors) {
7617 if (isNotUsableTU(TU)) {
7618 LOG_BAD_TU(TU);
7619 return;
7620 }
7621 if (NumTokens == 0 || !Tokens || !Cursors) {
7622 LOG_FUNC_SECTION { *Log << "<null input>"; }
7623 return;
7624 }
7625
7626 LOG_FUNC_SECTION {
7627 *Log << TU << ' ';
7628 CXSourceLocation bloc = clang_getTokenLocation(TU, Tokens[0]);
7629 CXSourceLocation eloc = clang_getTokenLocation(TU, Tokens[NumTokens-1]);
7630 *Log << clang_getRange(bloc, eloc);
7631 }
7632
7633 // Any token we don't specifically annotate will have a NULL cursor.
7634 CXCursor C = clang_getNullCursor();
7635 for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumTokens; ++I)
7636 Cursors[I] = C;
7637
7638 ASTUnit *CXXUnit = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU);
7639 if (!CXXUnit)
7640 return;
7641
7642 ASTUnit::ConcurrencyCheck Check(*CXXUnit);
7643
7644 auto AnnotateTokensImpl = [=]() {
7645 clang_annotateTokensImpl(TU, CXXUnit, Tokens, NumTokens, Cursors);
7646 };
7647 llvm::CrashRecoveryContext CRC;
7648 if (!RunSafely(CRC, AnnotateTokensImpl, GetSafetyThreadStackSize() * 2)) {
7649 fprintf(stderr, "libclang: crash detected while annotating tokens\n");
7650 }
7651}
7652
7653//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7654// Operations for querying linkage of a cursor.
7655//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7656
7657CXLinkageKind clang_getCursorLinkage(CXCursor cursor) {
7658 if (!clang_isDeclaration(cursor.kind))
7659 return CXLinkage_Invalid;
7660
7661 const Decl *D = cxcursor::getCursorDecl(cursor);
7662 if (const NamedDecl *ND = dyn_cast_or_null<NamedDecl>(D))
7663 switch (ND->getLinkageInternal()) {
7664 case NoLinkage:
7665 case VisibleNoLinkage: return CXLinkage_NoLinkage;
7666 case ModuleInternalLinkage:
7667 case InternalLinkage: return CXLinkage_Internal;
7668 case UniqueExternalLinkage: return CXLinkage_UniqueExternal;
7669 case ModuleLinkage:
7670 case ExternalLinkage: return CXLinkage_External;
7671 };
7672
7673 return CXLinkage_Invalid;
7674}
7675
7676//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7677// Operations for querying visibility of a cursor.
7678//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7679
7680CXVisibilityKind clang_getCursorVisibility(CXCursor cursor) {
7681 if (!clang_isDeclaration(cursor.kind))
7682 return CXVisibility_Invalid;
7683
7684 const Decl *D = cxcursor::getCursorDecl(cursor);
7685 if (const NamedDecl *ND = dyn_cast_or_null<NamedDecl>(D))
7686 switch (ND->getVisibility()) {
7687 case HiddenVisibility: return CXVisibility_Hidden;
7688 case ProtectedVisibility: return CXVisibility_Protected;
7689 case DefaultVisibility: return CXVisibility_Default;
7690 };
7691
7692 return CXVisibility_Invalid;
7693}
7694
7695//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7696// Operations for querying language of a cursor.
7697//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7698
7699static CXLanguageKind getDeclLanguage(const Decl *D) {
7700 if (!D)
7701 return CXLanguage_C;
7702
7703 switch (D->getKind()) {
7704 default:
7705 break;
7706 case Decl::ImplicitParam:
7707 case Decl::ObjCAtDefsField:
7708 case Decl::ObjCCategory:
7709 case Decl::ObjCCategoryImpl:
7710 case Decl::ObjCCompatibleAlias:
7711 case Decl::ObjCImplementation:
7712 case Decl::ObjCInterface:
7713 case Decl::ObjCIvar:
7714 case Decl::ObjCMethod:
7715 case Decl::ObjCProperty:
7716 case Decl::ObjCPropertyImpl:
7717 case Decl::ObjCProtocol:
7718 case Decl::ObjCTypeParam:
7719 return CXLanguage_ObjC;
7720 case Decl::CXXConstructor:
7721 case Decl::CXXConversion:
7722 case Decl::CXXDestructor:
7723 case Decl::CXXMethod:
7724 case Decl::CXXRecord:
7725 case Decl::ClassTemplate:
7726 case Decl::ClassTemplatePartialSpecialization:
7727 case Decl::ClassTemplateSpecialization:
7728 case Decl::Friend:
7729 case Decl::FriendTemplate:
7730 case Decl::FunctionTemplate:
7731 case Decl::LinkageSpec:
7732 case Decl::Namespace:
7733 case Decl::NamespaceAlias:
7734 case Decl::NonTypeTemplateParm:
7735 case Decl::StaticAssert:
7736 case Decl::TemplateTemplateParm:
7737 case Decl::TemplateTypeParm:
7738 case Decl::UnresolvedUsingTypename:
7739 case Decl::UnresolvedUsingValue:
7740 case Decl::Using:
7741 case Decl::UsingDirective:
7742 case Decl::UsingShadow:
7743 return CXLanguage_CPlusPlus;
7744 }
7745
7746 return CXLanguage_C;
7747}
7748
7749static CXAvailabilityKind getCursorAvailabilityForDecl(const Decl *D) {
7750 if (isa<FunctionDecl>(D) && cast<FunctionDecl>(D)->isDeleted())
7751 return CXAvailability_NotAvailable;
7752
7753 switch (D->getAvailability()) {
7754 case AR_Available:
7755 case AR_NotYetIntroduced:
7756 if (const EnumConstantDecl *EnumConst = dyn_cast<EnumConstantDecl>(D))
7757 return getCursorAvailabilityForDecl(
7758 cast<Decl>(EnumConst->getDeclContext()));
7759 return CXAvailability_Available;
7760
7761 case AR_Deprecated:
7762 return CXAvailability_Deprecated;
7763
7764 case AR_Unavailable:
7765 return CXAvailability_NotAvailable;
7766 }
7767
7768 llvm_unreachable("Unknown availability kind!");
7769}
7770
7771enum CXAvailabilityKind clang_getCursorAvailability(CXCursor cursor) {
7772 if (clang_isDeclaration(cursor.kind))
7773 if (const Decl *D = cxcursor::getCursorDecl(cursor))
7774 return getCursorAvailabilityForDecl(D);
7775
7776 return CXAvailability_Available;
7777}
7778
7779static CXVersion convertVersion(VersionTuple In) {
7780 CXVersion Out = { -1, -1, -1 };
7781 if (In.empty())
7782 return Out;
7783
7784 Out.Major = In.getMajor();
7785
7786 Optional<unsigned> Minor = In.getMinor();
7787 if (Minor.hasValue())
7788 Out.Minor = *Minor;
7789 else
7790 return Out;
7791
7792 Optional<unsigned> Subminor = In.getSubminor();
7793 if (Subminor.hasValue())
7794 Out.Subminor = *Subminor;
7795
7796 return Out;
7797}
7798
7799static void getCursorPlatformAvailabilityForDecl(
7800 const Decl *D, int *always_deprecated, CXString *deprecated_message,
7801 int *always_unavailable, CXString *unavailable_message,
7802 SmallVectorImpl<AvailabilityAttr *> &AvailabilityAttrs) {
7803 bool HadAvailAttr = false;
7804 for (auto A : D->attrs()) {
7805 if (DeprecatedAttr *Deprecated = dyn_cast<DeprecatedAttr>(A)) {
7806 HadAvailAttr = true;
7807 if (always_deprecated)
7808 *always_deprecated = 1;
7809 if (deprecated_message) {
7810 clang_disposeString(*deprecated_message);
7811 *deprecated_message = cxstring::createDup(Deprecated->getMessage());
7812 }
7813 continue;
7814 }
7815
7816 if (UnavailableAttr *Unavailable = dyn_cast<UnavailableAttr>(A)) {
7817 HadAvailAttr = true;
7818 if (always_unavailable)
7819 *always_unavailable = 1;
7820 if (unavailable_message) {
7821 clang_disposeString(*unavailable_message);
7822 *unavailable_message = cxstring::createDup(Unavailable->getMessage());
7823 }
7824 continue;
7825 }
7826
7827 if (AvailabilityAttr *Avail = dyn_cast<AvailabilityAttr>(A)) {
7828 AvailabilityAttrs.push_back(Avail);
7829 HadAvailAttr = true;
7830 }
7831 }
7832
7833 if (!HadAvailAttr)
7834 if (const EnumConstantDecl *EnumConst = dyn_cast<EnumConstantDecl>(D))
7835 return getCursorPlatformAvailabilityForDecl(
7836 cast<Decl>(EnumConst->getDeclContext()), always_deprecated,
7837 deprecated_message, always_unavailable, unavailable_message,
7838 AvailabilityAttrs);
7839
7840 if (AvailabilityAttrs.empty())
7841 return;
7842
7843 llvm::sort(AvailabilityAttrs,
7844 [](AvailabilityAttr *LHS, AvailabilityAttr *RHS) {
7845 return LHS->getPlatform()->getName() <
7846 RHS->getPlatform()->getName();
7847 });
7848 ASTContext &Ctx = D->getASTContext();
7849 auto It = std::unique(
7850 AvailabilityAttrs.begin(), AvailabilityAttrs.end(),
7851 [&Ctx](AvailabilityAttr *LHS, AvailabilityAttr *RHS) {
7852 if (LHS->getPlatform() != RHS->getPlatform())
7853 return false;
7854
7855 if (LHS->getIntroduced() == RHS->getIntroduced() &&
7856 LHS->getDeprecated() == RHS->getDeprecated() &&
7857 LHS->getObsoleted() == RHS->getObsoleted() &&
7858 LHS->getMessage() == RHS->getMessage() &&
7859 LHS->getReplacement() == RHS->getReplacement())
7860 return true;
7861
7862 if ((!LHS->getIntroduced().empty() && !RHS->getIntroduced().empty()) ||
7863 (!LHS->getDeprecated().empty() && !RHS->getDeprecated().empty()) ||
7864 (!LHS->getObsoleted().empty() && !RHS->getObsoleted().empty()))
7865 return false;
7866
7867 if (LHS->getIntroduced().empty() && !RHS->getIntroduced().empty())
7868 LHS->setIntroduced(Ctx, RHS->getIntroduced());
7869
7870 if (LHS->getDeprecated().empty() && !RHS->getDeprecated().empty()) {
7871 LHS->setDeprecated(Ctx, RHS->getDeprecated());
7872 if (LHS->getMessage().empty())
7873 LHS->setMessage(Ctx, RHS->getMessage());
7874 if (LHS->getReplacement().empty())
7875 LHS->setReplacement(Ctx, RHS->getReplacement());
7876 }
7877
7878 if (LHS->getObsoleted().empty() && !RHS->getObsoleted().empty()) {
7879 LHS->setObsoleted(Ctx, RHS->getObsoleted());
7880 if (LHS->getMessage().empty())
7881 LHS->setMessage(Ctx, RHS->getMessage());
7882 if (LHS->getReplacement().empty())
7883 LHS->setReplacement(Ctx, RHS->getReplacement());
7884 }
7885
7886 return true;
7887 });
7888 AvailabilityAttrs.erase(It, AvailabilityAttrs.end());
7889}
7890
7891int clang_getCursorPlatformAvailability(CXCursor cursor, int *always_deprecated,
7892 CXString *deprecated_message,
7893 int *always_unavailable,
7894 CXString *unavailable_message,
7895 CXPlatformAvailability *availability,
7896 int availability_size) {
7897 if (always_deprecated)
7898 *always_deprecated = 0;
7899 if (deprecated_message)
7900 *deprecated_message = cxstring::createEmpty();
7901 if (always_unavailable)
7902 *always_unavailable = 0;
7903 if (unavailable_message)
7904 *unavailable_message = cxstring::createEmpty();
7905
7906 if (!clang_isDeclaration(cursor.kind))
7907 return 0;
7908
7909 const Decl *D = cxcursor::getCursorDecl(cursor);
7910 if (!D)
7911 return 0;
7912
7913 SmallVector<AvailabilityAttr *, 8> AvailabilityAttrs;
7914 getCursorPlatformAvailabilityForDecl(D, always_deprecated, deprecated_message,
7915 always_unavailable, unavailable_message,
7916 AvailabilityAttrs);
7917 for (const auto &Avail :
7918 llvm::enumerate(llvm::makeArrayRef(AvailabilityAttrs)
7919 .take_front(availability_size))) {
7920 availability[Avail.index()].Platform =
7921 cxstring::createDup(Avail.value()->getPlatform()->getName());
7922 availability[Avail.index()].Introduced =
7923 convertVersion(Avail.value()->getIntroduced());
7924 availability[Avail.index()].Deprecated =
7925 convertVersion(Avail.value()->getDeprecated());
7926 availability[Avail.index()].Obsoleted =
7927 convertVersion(Avail.value()->getObsoleted());
7928 availability[Avail.index()].Unavailable = Avail.value()->getUnavailable();
7929 availability[Avail.index()].Message =
7930 cxstring::createDup(Avail.value()->getMessage());
7931 }
7932
7933 return AvailabilityAttrs.size();
7934}
7935
7936void clang_disposeCXPlatformAvailability(CXPlatformAvailability *availability) {
7937 clang_disposeString(availability->Platform);
7938 clang_disposeString(availability->Message);
7939}

7943 return getDeclLanguage(cxcursor::getCursorDecl(cursor));
7944

7948CXTLSKind clang_getCursorTLSKind(CXCursor cursor) {
7949 const Decl *D = cxcursor::getCursorDecl(cursor);
7950 if (const VarDecl *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
7951 switch (VD->getTLSKind()) {
7952 case VarDecl::TLS_None:
7953 return CXTLS_None;
7954 case VarDecl::TLS_Dynamic:
7955 return CXTLS_Dynamic;
7956 case VarDecl::TLS_Static:
7957 return CXTLS_Static;
7958 }
7959 }
7960
7961 return CXTLS_None;
7962}
7963
7964 /// If the given cursor is the "templated" declaration
7965 /// describing a class or function template, return the class or
7966 /// function template.
7967static const Decl *maybeGetTemplateCursor(const Decl *D) {
7968 if (!D)
7969 return nullptr;
7970
7971 if (const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D))
7972 if (FunctionTemplateDecl *FunTmpl = FD->getDescribedFunctionTemplate())
7973 return FunTmpl;
7974
7975 if (const CXXRecordDecl *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D))
7976 if (ClassTemplateDecl *ClassTmpl = RD->getDescribedClassTemplate())
7977 return ClassTmpl;
7978
7979 return D;
7980}

7982
7983enum CX_StorageClass clang_Cursor_getStorageClass(CXCursor C) {
7984 StorageClass sc = SC_None;
7985 const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(C);
7986 if (D) {
7987 if (const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
7988 sc = FD->getStorageClass();
7989 } else if (const VarDecl *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
7990 sc = VD->getStorageClass();
7991 } else {
7992 return CX_SC_Invalid;
7993 }
7994 } else {
7995 return CX_SC_Invalid;
7996 }
7997 switch (sc) {
7998 case SC_None:
7999 return CX_SC_None;
8000 case SC_Extern:
8001 return CX_SC_Extern;
8002 case SC_Static:
8003 return CX_SC_Static;
8004 case SC_PrivateExtern:
8005 return CX_SC_PrivateExtern;
8006 case SC_Auto:
8007 return CX_SC_Auto;
8008 case SC_Register:
8009 return CX_SC_Register;
8010 }
8011 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled storage class!");
8012}
8013
8014CXCursor clang_getCursorSemanticParent(CXCursor cursor) {
8015 if (clang_isDeclaration(cursor.kind)) {
8016 if (const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(cursor)) {
8017 const DeclContext *DC = D->getDeclContext();
8018 if (!DC)
8019 return clang_getNullCursor();
8020
8021 return MakeCXCursor(maybeGetTemplateCursor(cast<Decl>(DC)),
8022 getCursorTU(cursor));
8023 }
8024 }
8025
8026 if (clang_isStatement(cursor.kind) || clang_isExpression(cursor.kind)) {
8027 if (const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(cursor))
8028 return MakeCXCursor(D, getCursorTU(cursor));
8029 }
8030
8031 return clang_getNullCursor();
8032}
8033
8034CXCursor clang_getCursorLexicalParent(CXCursor cursor) {
8035 if (clang_isDeclaration(cursor.kind)) {
8036 if (const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(cursor)) {
8037 const DeclContext *DC = D->getLexicalDeclContext();
8038 if (!DC)
8039 return clang_getNullCursor();
8040
8041 return MakeCXCursor(maybeGetTemplateCursor(cast<Decl>(DC)),
8042 getCursorTU(cursor));
8043 }
8044 }
8045
8046 // FIXME: Note that we can't easily compute the lexical context of a
8047 // statement or expression, so we return nothing.
8048 return clang_getNullCursor();
8049}

8051CXFile clang_getIncludedFile(CXCursor cursor) {
8052 if (cursor.kind != CXCursor_InclusionDirective)
8053 return nullptr;
8054
8055 const InclusionDirective *ID = getCursorInclusionDirective(cursor);
8056 return const_cast<FileEntry *>(ID->getFile());
8057}

8059unsigned clang_Cursor_getObjCPropertyAttributes(CXCursor C, unsigned reserved) {
8060 if (C.kind != CXCursor_ObjCPropertyDecl)
8061 return CXObjCPropertyAttr_noattr;
8062
8063 unsigned Result = CXObjCPropertyAttr_noattr;
8064 const ObjCPropertyDecl *PD = dyn_cast<ObjCPropertyDecl>(getCursorDecl(C));
8065 ObjCPropertyDecl::PropertyAttributeKind Attr =
8066 PD->getPropertyAttributesAsWritten();
8067
8068#define SET_CXOBJCPROP_ATTR(A) \
8069 if (Attr & ObjCPropertyDecl::OBJC_PR_##A) \
8070 Result |= CXObjCPropertyAttr_##A
8071 SET_CXOBJCPROP_ATTR(readonly);
8072 SET_CXOBJCPROP_ATTR(getter);
8073 SET_CXOBJCPROP_ATTR(assign);
8074 SET_CXOBJCPROP_ATTR(readwrite);
8075 SET_CXOBJCPROP_ATTR(retain);
8076 SET_CXOBJCPROP_ATTR(copy);
8077 SET_CXOBJCPROP_ATTR(nonatomic);
8078 SET_CXOBJCPROP_ATTR(setter);
8079 SET_CXOBJCPROP_ATTR(atomic);
8080 SET_CXOBJCPROP_ATTR(weak);
8081 SET_CXOBJCPROP_ATTR(strong);
8082 SET_CXOBJCPROP_ATTR(unsafe_unretained);
8083 SET_CXOBJCPROP_ATTR(class);
8084#undef SET_CXOBJCPROP_ATTR
8085
8086 return Result;
8087}

8089CXString clang_Cursor_getObjCPropertyGetterName(CXCursor C) {
8090 if (C.kind != CXCursor_ObjCPropertyDecl)
8091 return cxstring::createNull();
8092
8093 const ObjCPropertyDecl *PD = dyn_cast<ObjCPropertyDecl>(getCursorDecl(C));
8094 Selector sel = PD->getGetterName();
8095 if (sel.isNull())
8096 return cxstring::createNull();
8097
8098 return cxstring::createDup(sel.getAsString());
8099}

8101CXString clang_Cursor_getObjCPropertySetterName(CXCursor C) {

8103 return cxstring::createNull();
8104
8105 const ObjCPropertyDecl *PD = dyn_cast<ObjCPropertyDecl>(getCursorDecl(C));

8113unsigned clang_Cursor_getObjCDeclQualifiers(CXCursor C) {
8114 if (!clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
8115 return CXObjCDeclQualifier_None;
8116
8117 Decl::ObjCDeclQualifier QT = Decl::OBJC_TQ_None;
8118 const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(C);
8119 if (const ObjCMethodDecl *MD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D))
8120 QT = MD->getObjCDeclQualifier();
8121 else if (const ParmVarDecl *PD = dyn_cast<ParmVarDecl>(D))
8122 QT = PD->getObjCDeclQualifier();
8123 if (QT == Decl::OBJC_TQ_None)
8124 return CXObjCDeclQualifier_None;
8125
8126 unsigned Result = CXObjCDeclQualifier_None;
8127 if (QT & Decl::OBJC_TQ_In) Result |= CXObjCDeclQualifier_In;
8128 if (QT & Decl::OBJC_TQ_Inout) Result |= CXObjCDeclQualifier_Inout;
8129 if (QT & Decl::OBJC_TQ_Out) Result |= CXObjCDeclQualifier_Out;
8130 if (QT & Decl::OBJC_TQ_Bycopy) Result |= CXObjCDeclQualifier_Bycopy;
8131 if (QT & Decl::OBJC_TQ_Byref) Result |= CXObjCDeclQualifier_Byref;
8132 if (QT & Decl::OBJC_TQ_Oneway) Result |= CXObjCDeclQualifier_Oneway;
8133
8134 return Result;
8135}

8137unsigned clang_Cursor_isObjCOptional(CXCursor C) {
8138 if (!clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
8139 return 0;
8140
8141 const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(C);
8142 if (const ObjCPropertyDecl *PD = dyn_cast<ObjCPropertyDecl>(D))
8143 return PD->getPropertyImplementation() == ObjCPropertyDecl::Optional;
8144 if (const ObjCMethodDecl *MD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D))
8145 return MD->getImplementationControl() == ObjCMethodDecl::Optional;
8146
8147 return 0;
8148}

8150unsigned clang_Cursor_isVariadic(CXCursor C) {
8151 if (!clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
8152 return 0;
8153
8154 const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(C);
8155 if (const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D))
8156 return FD->isVariadic();
8157 if (const ObjCMethodDecl *MD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D))
8158 return MD->isVariadic();
8159
8160 return 0;
8161}

8163unsigned clang_Cursor_isExternalSymbol(CXCursor C,
8164 CXString *language, CXString *definedIn,
8165 unsigned *isGenerated) {
8166 if (!clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
8167 return 0;
8168
8169 const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(C);
8170
8171 if (auto *attr = D->getExternalSourceSymbolAttr()) {
8172 if (language)
8173 *language = cxstring::createDup(attr->getLanguage());
8174 if (definedIn)
8175 *definedIn = cxstring::createDup(attr->getDefinedIn());
8176 if (isGenerated)
8177 *isGenerated = attr->getGeneratedDeclaration();
8178 return 1;
8179 }
8180 return 0;
8181}

8183CXSourceRange clang_Cursor_getCommentRange(CXCursor C) {
8184 if (!clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
8185 return clang_getNullRange();
8186
8187 const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(C);
8188 ASTContext &Context = getCursorContext(C);
8189 const RawComment *RC = Context.getRawCommentForAnyRedecl(D);
8190 if (!RC)
8191 return clang_getNullRange();
8192
8193 return cxloc::translateSourceRange(Context, RC->getSourceRange());
8194}
8195
8196CXString clang_Cursor_getRawCommentText(CXCursor C) {
8197 if (!clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
8198 return cxstring::createNull();
8199
8200 const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(C);
8201 ASTContext &Context = getCursorContext(C);
8202 const RawComment *RC = Context.getRawCommentForAnyRedecl(D);
8203 StringRef RawText = RC ? RC->getRawText(Context.getSourceManager()) :
8204 StringRef();
8205
8206 // Don't duplicate the string because RawText points directly into source
8207 // code.
8208 return cxstring::createRef(RawText);
8209}
8210
8211CXString clang_Cursor_getBriefCommentText(CXCursor C) {
8212 if (!clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
8213 return cxstring::createNull();
8214
8215 const Decl *D = getCursorDecl(C);
8216 const ASTContext &Context = getCursorContext(C);
8217 const RawComment *RC = Context.getRawCommentForAnyRedecl(D);
8218
8219 if (RC) {
8220 StringRef BriefText = RC->getBriefText(Context);
8221
8222 // Don't duplicate the string because RawComment ensures that this memory
8223 // will not go away.
8224 return cxstring::createRef(BriefText);
8225 }
8226
8227 return cxstring::createNull();
8228}

8233 dyn_cast_or_null<ImportDecl>(getCursorDecl(C)))
8234 return ImportD->getImportedModule();

8237 return nullptr;
8238}

8240CXModule clang_getModuleForFile(CXTranslationUnit TU, CXFile File) {
8241 if (isNotUsableTU(TU)) {
8242 LOG_BAD_TU(TU);
8243 return nullptr;
8244 }
8245 if (!File)
8246 return nullptr;
8247 FileEntry *FE = static_cast<FileEntry *>(File);
8248
8249 ASTUnit &Unit = *cxtu::getASTUnit(TU);
8250 HeaderSearch &HS = Unit.getPreprocessor().getHeaderSearchInfo();
8251 ModuleMap::KnownHeader Header = HS.findModuleForHeader(FE);
8252
8253 return Header.getModule();
8254}

8291unsigned clang_Module_getNumTopLevelHeaders(CXTranslationUnit TU,
8292 CXModule CXMod) {
8293 if (isNotUsableTU(TU)) {
8294 LOG_BAD_TU(TU);
8295 return 0;
8296 }
8297 if (!CXMod)
8298 return 0;
8299 Module *Mod = static_cast<Module*>(CXMod);
8300 FileManager &FileMgr = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU)->getFileManager();
8301 ArrayRef<const FileEntry *> TopHeaders = Mod->getTopHeaders(FileMgr);
8302 return TopHeaders.size();
8303}
8304
8305CXFile clang_Module_getTopLevelHeader(CXTranslationUnit TU,
8306 CXModule CXMod, unsigned Index) {
8307 if (isNotUsableTU(TU)) {
8308 LOG_BAD_TU(TU);
8309 return nullptr;
8310 }
8311 if (!CXMod)
8312 return nullptr;
8313 Module *Mod = static_cast<Module*>(CXMod);
8314 FileManager &FileMgr = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU)->getFileManager();
8315
8316 ArrayRef<const FileEntry *> TopHeaders = Mod->getTopHeaders(FileMgr);
8317 if (Index < TopHeaders.size())
8318 return const_cast<FileEntry *>(TopHeaders[Index]);
8319
8320 return nullptr;
8321}

8327unsigned clang_CXXConstructor_isDefaultConstructor(CXCursor C) {
8328 if (!clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
8329 return 0;
8330
8331 const Decl *D = cxcursor::getCursorDecl(C);
8332 const CXXConstructorDecl *Constructor =
8333 D ? dyn_cast_or_null<CXXConstructorDecl>(D->getAsFunction()) : nullptr;
8334 return (Constructor && Constructor->isDefaultConstructor()) ? 1 : 0;
8335}

8342 const CXXConstructorDecl *Constructor =

8344 return (Constructor && Constructor->isCopyConstructor()) ? 1 : 0;

8350

8388unsigned clang_CXXMethod_isConst(CXCursor C) {
8389 if (!clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
8390 return 0;
8391
8392 const Decl *D = cxcursor::getCursorDecl(C);
8393 const CXXMethodDecl *Method =
8394 D ? dyn_cast_or_null<CXXMethodDecl>(D->getAsFunction()) : nullptr;
8395 return (Method && Method->getMethodQualifiers().hasConst()) ? 1 : 0;
8396}
8397
8398unsigned clang_CXXMethod_isDefaulted(CXCursor C) {
8399 if (!clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
8400 return 0;
8401
8402 const Decl *D = cxcursor::getCursorDecl(C);
8403 const CXXMethodDecl *Method =
8404 D ? dyn_cast_or_null<CXXMethodDecl>(D->getAsFunction()) : nullptr;
8405 return (Method && Method->isDefaulted()) ? 1 : 0;
8406}
8407
8408unsigned clang_CXXMethod_isStatic(CXCursor C) {
8409 if (!clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
8410 return 0;
8411
8412 const Decl *D = cxcursor::getCursorDecl(C);
8413 const CXXMethodDecl *Method =
8414 D ? dyn_cast_or_null<CXXMethodDecl>(D->getAsFunction()) : nullptr;
8415 return (Method && Method->isStatic()) ? 1 : 0;
8416}
8417
8418unsigned clang_CXXMethod_isVirtual(CXCursor C) {
8419 if (!clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
8420 return 0;
8421
8422 const Decl *D = cxcursor::getCursorDecl(C);
8423 const CXXMethodDecl *Method =
8424 D ? dyn_cast_or_null<CXXMethodDecl>(D->getAsFunction()) : nullptr;
8425 return (Method && Method->isVirtual()) ? 1 : 0;
8426}
8427
8428unsigned clang_CXXRecord_isAbstract(CXCursor C) {
8429 if (!clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
8430 return 0;
8431
8432 const auto *D = cxcursor::getCursorDecl(C);
8433 const auto *RD = dyn_cast_or_null<CXXRecordDecl>(D);
8434 if (RD)
8435 RD = RD->getDefinition();
8436 return (RD && RD->isAbstract()) ? 1 : 0;
8437}
8438
8439unsigned clang_EnumDecl_isScoped(CXCursor C) {
8440 if (!clang_isDeclaration(C.kind))
8441 return 0;
8442
8443 const Decl *D = cxcursor::getCursorDecl(C);
8444 auto *Enum = dyn_cast_or_null<EnumDecl>(D);
8445 return (Enum && Enum->isScoped()) ? 1 : 0;
8446}

8449// Attribute introspection.
8450//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8451
8452CXType clang_getIBOutletCollectionType(CXCursor C) {
8453 if (C.kind != CXCursor_IBOutletCollectionAttr)
8454 return cxtype::MakeCXType(QualType(), cxcursor::getCursorTU(C));
8455
8456 const IBOutletCollectionAttr *A =
8457 cast<IBOutletCollectionAttr>(cxcursor::getCursorAttr(C));
8458
8459 return cxtype::MakeCXType(A->getInterface(), cxcursor::getCursorTU(C));
8460}

8462//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8463// Inspecting memory usage.
8464//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8465
8466typedef std::vector<CXTUResourceUsageEntry> MemUsageEntries;
8467
8468static inline void createCXTUResourceUsageEntry(MemUsageEntries &entries,
8469 enum CXTUResourceUsageKind k,
8470 unsigned long amount) {
8471 CXTUResourceUsageEntry entry = { k, amount };
8472 entries.push_back(entry);
8473}
8474
8475const char *clang_getTUResourceUsageName(CXTUResourceUsageKind kind) {
8476 const char *str = "";
8477 switch (kind) {
8478 case CXTUResourceUsage_AST:
8479 str = "ASTContext: expressions, declarations, and types";
8480 break;
8481 case CXTUResourceUsage_Identifiers:
8482 str = "ASTContext: identifiers";
8483 break;
8484 case CXTUResourceUsage_Selectors:
8485 str = "ASTContext: selectors";
8486 break;
8487 case CXTUResourceUsage_GlobalCompletionResults:
8488 str = "Code completion: cached global results";
8489 break;
8490 case CXTUResourceUsage_SourceManagerContentCache:
8491 str = "SourceManager: content cache allocator";
8492 break;
8493 case CXTUResourceUsage_AST_SideTables:
8494 str = "ASTContext: side tables";
8495 break;
8496 case CXTUResourceUsage_SourceManager_Membuffer_Malloc:
8497 str = "SourceManager: malloc'ed memory buffers";
8498 break;
8499 case CXTUResourceUsage_SourceManager_Membuffer_MMap:
8500 str = "SourceManager: mmap'ed memory buffers";
8501 break;
8502 case CXTUResourceUsage_ExternalASTSource_Membuffer_Malloc:
8503 str = "ExternalASTSource: malloc'ed memory buffers";
8504 break;
8505 case CXTUResourceUsage_ExternalASTSource_Membuffer_MMap:
8506 str = "ExternalASTSource: mmap'ed memory buffers";
8507 break;
8508 case CXTUResourceUsage_Preprocessor:
8509 str = "Preprocessor: malloc'ed memory";
8510 break;
8511 case CXTUResourceUsage_PreprocessingRecord:
8512 str = "Preprocessor: PreprocessingRecord";
8513 break;
8514 case CXTUResourceUsage_SourceManager_DataStructures:
8515 str = "SourceManager: data structures and tables";
8516 break;
8517 case CXTUResourceUsage_Preprocessor_HeaderSearch:
8518 str = "Preprocessor: header search tables";
8519 break;
8520 }
8521 return str;
8522}
8523
8524CXTUResourceUsage clang_getCXTUResourceUsage(CXTranslationUnit TU) {
8525 if (isNotUsableTU(TU)) {
8526 LOG_BAD_TU(TU);
8527 CXTUResourceUsage usage = { (void*) nullptr, 0, nullptr };
8528 return usage;
8529 }
8530
8531 ASTUnit *astUnit = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU);
8532 std::unique_ptr<MemUsageEntries> entries(new MemUsageEntries());
8533 ASTContext &astContext = astUnit->getASTContext();
8534
8535 // How much memory is used by AST nodes and types?
8536 createCXTUResourceUsageEntry(*entries, CXTUResourceUsage_AST,
8537 (unsigned long) astContext.getASTAllocatedMemory());
8538
8539 // How much memory is used by identifiers?
8540 createCXTUResourceUsageEntry(*entries, CXTUResourceUsage_Identifiers,
8541 (unsigned long) astContext.Idents.getAllocator().getTotalMemory());
8542
8543 // How much memory is used for selectors?
8544 createCXTUResourceUsageEntry(*entries, CXTUResourceUsage_Selectors,
8545 (unsigned long) astContext.Selectors.getTotalMemory());
8546
8547 // How much memory is used by ASTContext's side tables?
8548 createCXTUResourceUsageEntry(*entries, CXTUResourceUsage_AST_SideTables,
8549 (unsigned long) astContext.getSideTableAllocatedMemory());
8550
8551 // How much memory is used for caching global code completion results?
8552 unsigned long completionBytes = 0;
8553 if (GlobalCodeCompletionAllocator *completionAllocator =
8554 astUnit->getCachedCompletionAllocator().get()) {
8555 completionBytes = completionAllocator->getTotalMemory();
8556 }
8557 createCXTUResourceUsageEntry(*entries,
8558 CXTUResourceUsage_GlobalCompletionResults,
8559 completionBytes);
8560
8561 // How much memory is being used by SourceManager's content cache?
8562 createCXTUResourceUsageEntry(*entries,
8563 CXTUResourceUsage_SourceManagerContentCache,
8564 (unsigned long) astContext.getSourceManager().getContentCacheSize());
8565
8566 // How much memory is being used by the MemoryBuffer's in SourceManager?
8567 const SourceManager::MemoryBufferSizes &srcBufs =
8568 astUnit->getSourceManager().getMemoryBufferSizes();
8569
8570 createCXTUResourceUsageEntry(*entries,
8571 CXTUResourceUsage_SourceManager_Membuffer_Malloc,
8572 (unsigned long) srcBufs.malloc_bytes);
8573 createCXTUResourceUsageEntry(*entries,
8574 CXTUResourceUsage_SourceManager_Membuffer_MMap,
8575 (unsigned long) srcBufs.mmap_bytes);
8576 createCXTUResourceUsageEntry(*entries,
8577 CXTUResourceUsage_SourceManager_DataStructures,
8578 (unsigned long) astContext.getSourceManager()
8579 .getDataStructureSizes());
8580
8581 // How much memory is being used by the ExternalASTSource?
8582 if (ExternalASTSource *esrc = astContext.getExternalSource()) {
8583 const ExternalASTSource::MemoryBufferSizes &sizes =
8584 esrc->getMemoryBufferSizes();
8585
8586 createCXTUResourceUsageEntry(*entries,
8587 CXTUResourceUsage_ExternalASTSource_Membuffer_Malloc,
8588 (unsigned long) sizes.malloc_bytes);
8589 createCXTUResourceUsageEntry(*entries,
8590 CXTUResourceUsage_ExternalASTSource_Membuffer_MMap,
8591 (unsigned long) sizes.mmap_bytes);
8592 }
8593
8594 // How much memory is being used by the Preprocessor?
8595 Preprocessor &pp = astUnit->getPreprocessor();
8596 createCXTUResourceUsageEntry(*entries,
8597 CXTUResourceUsage_Preprocessor,
8598 pp.getTotalMemory());
8599
8600 if (PreprocessingRecord *pRec = pp.getPreprocessingRecord()) {
8601 createCXTUResourceUsageEntry(*entries,
8602 CXTUResourceUsage_PreprocessingRecord,
8603 pRec->getTotalMemory());
8604 }
8605
8606 createCXTUResourceUsageEntry(*entries,
8607 CXTUResourceUsage_Preprocessor_HeaderSearch,
8608 pp.getHeaderSearchInfo().getTotalMemory());
8609
8610 CXTUResourceUsage usage = { (void*) entries.get(),
8611 (unsigned) entries->size(),
8612 !entries->empty() ? &(*entries)[0] : nullptr };
8613 (void)entries.release();
8614 return usage;
8615}
8616
8617void clang_disposeCXTUResourceUsage(CXTUResourceUsage usage) {
8618 if (usage.data)
8619 delete (MemUsageEntries*) usage.data;
8620}
8621
8622CXSourceRangeList *clang_getSkippedRanges(CXTranslationUnit TU, CXFile file) {
8623 CXSourceRangeList *skipped = new CXSourceRangeList;
8624 skipped->count = 0;
8625 skipped->ranges = nullptr;
8626
8627 if (isNotUsableTU(TU)) {
8628 LOG_BAD_TU(TU);
8629 return skipped;
8630 }
8631
8632 if (!file)
8633 return skipped;
8634
8635 ASTUnit *astUnit = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU);
8636 PreprocessingRecord *ppRec = astUnit->getPreprocessor().getPreprocessingRecord();
8637 if (!ppRec)
8638 return skipped;
8639
8640 ASTContext &Ctx = astUnit->getASTContext();
8641 SourceManager &sm = Ctx.getSourceManager();
8642 FileEntry *fileEntry = static_cast<FileEntry *>(file);
8643 FileID wantedFileID = sm.translateFile(fileEntry);
8644 bool isMainFile = wantedFileID == sm.getMainFileID();
8645
8646 const std::vector<SourceRange> &SkippedRanges = ppRec->getSkippedRanges();
8647 std::vector<SourceRange> wantedRanges;
8648 for (std::vector<SourceRange>::const_iterator i = SkippedRanges.begin(), ei = SkippedRanges.end();
8649 i != ei; ++i) {
8650 if (sm.getFileID(i->getBegin()) == wantedFileID || sm.getFileID(i->getEnd()) == wantedFileID)
8651 wantedRanges.push_back(*i);
8652 else if (isMainFile && (astUnit->isInPreambleFileID(i->getBegin()) || astUnit->isInPreambleFileID(i->getEnd())))
8653 wantedRanges.push_back(*i);
8654 }
8655
8656 skipped->count = wantedRanges.size();
8657 skipped->ranges = new CXSourceRange[skipped->count];
8658 for (unsigned i = 0, ei = skipped->count; i != ei; ++i)
8659 skipped->ranges[i] = cxloc::translateSourceRange(Ctx, wantedRanges[i]);
8660
8661 return skipped;
8662}
8663
8664CXSourceRangeList *clang_getAllSkippedRanges(CXTranslationUnit TU) {
8665 CXSourceRangeList *skipped = new CXSourceRangeList;
8666 skipped->count = 0;
8667 skipped->ranges = nullptr;
8668
8669 if (isNotUsableTU(TU)) {
8670 LOG_BAD_TU(TU);
8671 return skipped;
8672 }
8673
8674 ASTUnit *astUnit = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU);
8675 PreprocessingRecord *ppRec = astUnit->getPreprocessor().getPreprocessingRecord();
8676 if (!ppRec)
8677 return skipped;
8678
8679 ASTContext &Ctx = astUnit->getASTContext();
8680
8681 const std::vector<SourceRange> &SkippedRanges = ppRec->getSkippedRanges();
8682
8683 skipped->count = SkippedRanges.size();
8684 skipped->ranges = new CXSourceRange[skipped->count];
8685 for (unsigned i = 0, ei = skipped->count; i != ei; ++i)
8686 skipped->ranges[i] = cxloc::translateSourceRange(Ctx, SkippedRanges[i]);
8687
8688 return skipped;
8689}
8690
8691void clang_disposeSourceRangeList(CXSourceRangeList *ranges) {
8692 if (ranges) {
8693 delete[] ranges->ranges;
8694 delete ranges;
8695 }
8696}
8697
8698void clang::PrintLibclangResourceUsage(CXTranslationUnit TU) {
8699 CXTUResourceUsage Usage = clang_getCXTUResourceUsage(TU);
8700 for (unsigned I = 0; I != Usage.numEntries; ++I)
8701 fprintf(stderr, " %s: %lu\n",
8702 clang_getTUResourceUsageName(Usage.entries[I].kind),
8703 Usage.entries[I].amount);
8704
8705 clang_disposeCXTUResourceUsage(Usage);
8706}

8712/// Default to using our desired 8 MB stack size on "safety" threads.
8713static unsigned SafetyStackThreadSize = DesiredStackSize;
8714
8715namespace clang {
8716
8717bool RunSafely(llvm::CrashRecoveryContext &CRC, llvm::function_ref<void()> Fn,
8718 unsigned Size) {
8719 if (!Size)
8720 Size = GetSafetyThreadStackSize();
8721 if (Size && !getenv("LIBCLANG_NOTHREADS"))
8722 return CRC.RunSafelyOnThread(Fn, Size);
8723 return CRC.RunSafely(Fn);
8724}
8725
8726unsigned GetSafetyThreadStackSize() {
8727 return SafetyStackThreadSize;
8728}
8729
8730void SetSafetyThreadStackSize(unsigned Value) {
8731 SafetyStackThreadSize = Value;
8732}
8733
8734}

8736void clang::setThreadBackgroundPriority() {
8737 if (getenv("LIBCLANG_BGPRIO_DISABLE"))
8738 return;
8739
8740#if LLVM_ENABLE_THREADS
8741 llvm::set_thread_priority(llvm::ThreadPriority::Background);
8742#endif
8743}
8744
8745void cxindex::printDiagsToStderr(ASTUnit *Unit) {
8746 if (!Unit)
8747 return;
8748
8749 for (ASTUnit::stored_diag_iterator D = Unit->stored_diag_begin(),
8750 DEnd = Unit->stored_diag_end();
8751 D != DEnd; ++D) {
8752 CXStoredDiagnostic Diag(*D, Unit->getLangOpts());
8753 CXString Msg = clang_formatDiagnostic(&Diag,
8754 clang_defaultDiagnosticDisplayOptions());
8755 fprintf(stderr, "%s\n", clang_getCString(Msg));
8756 clang_disposeString(Msg);
8757 }
8758#ifdef _WIN32
8759 // On Windows, force a flush, since there may be multiple copies of
8760 // stderr and stdout in the file system, all with different buffers
8761 // but writing to the same device.
8762 fflush(stderr);
8763#endif
8764}
8765
8766MacroInfo *cxindex::getMacroInfo(const IdentifierInfo &II,
8767 SourceLocation MacroDefLoc,
8768 CXTranslationUnit TU){
8769 if (MacroDefLoc.isInvalid() || !TU)
8770 return nullptr;
8771 if (!II.hadMacroDefinition())
8772 return nullptr;
8773
8774 ASTUnit *Unit = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU);
8775 Preprocessor &PP = Unit->getPreprocessor();
8776 MacroDirective *MD = PP.getLocalMacroDirectiveHistory(&II);
8777 if (MD) {
8778 for (MacroDirective::DefInfo
8779 Def = MD->getDefinition(); Def; Def = Def.getPreviousDefinition()) {
8780 if (MacroDefLoc == Def.getMacroInfo()->getDefinitionLoc())
8781 return Def.getMacroInfo();
8782 }
8783 }
8784
8785 return nullptr;
8786}
8787
8788const MacroInfo *cxindex::getMacroInfo(const MacroDefinitionRecord *MacroDef,
8789 CXTranslationUnit TU) {
8790 if (!MacroDef || !TU)
8791 return nullptr;
8792 const IdentifierInfo *II = MacroDef->getName();
8793 if (!II)
8794 return nullptr;
8795
8796 return getMacroInfo(*II, MacroDef->getLocation(), TU);
8797}
8798
8799MacroDefinitionRecord *
8800cxindex::checkForMacroInMacroDefinition(const MacroInfo *MI, const Token &Tok,
8801 CXTranslationUnit TU) {
8802 if (!MI || !TU)
8803 return nullptr;
8804 if (Tok.isNot(tok::raw_identifier))
8805 return nullptr;
8806
8807 if (MI->getNumTokens() == 0)
8808 return nullptr;
8809 SourceRange DefRange(MI->getReplacementToken(0).getLocation(),
8810 MI->getDefinitionEndLoc());
8811 ASTUnit *Unit = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU);
8812
8813 // Check that the token is inside the definition and not its argument list.
8814 SourceManager &SM = Unit->getSourceManager();
8815 if (SM.isBeforeInTranslationUnit(Tok.getLocation(), DefRange.getBegin()))
8816 return nullptr;
8817 if (SM.isBeforeInTranslationUnit(DefRange.getEnd(), Tok.getLocation()))
8818 return nullptr;
8819
8820 Preprocessor &PP = Unit->getPreprocessor();
8821 PreprocessingRecord *PPRec = PP.getPreprocessingRecord();
8822 if (!PPRec)
8823 return nullptr;
8824
8825 IdentifierInfo &II = PP.getIdentifierTable().get(Tok.getRawIdentifier());
8826 if (!II.hadMacroDefinition())
8827 return nullptr;
8828
8829 // Check that the identifier is not one of the macro arguments.
8830 if (std::find(MI->param_begin(), MI->param_end(), &II) != MI->param_end())
8831 return nullptr;
8832
8833 MacroDirective *InnerMD = PP.getLocalMacroDirectiveHistory(&II);
8834 if (!InnerMD)
8835 return nullptr;
8836
8837 return PPRec->findMacroDefinition(InnerMD->getMacroInfo());
8838}
8839
8840MacroDefinitionRecord *
8841cxindex::checkForMacroInMacroDefinition(const MacroInfo *MI, SourceLocation Loc,
8842 CXTranslationUnit TU) {
8843 if (Loc.isInvalid() || !MI || !TU)
8844 return nullptr;
8845
8846 if (MI->getNumTokens() == 0)
8847 return nullptr;
8848 ASTUnit *Unit = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU);
8849 Preprocessor &PP = Unit->getPreprocessor();
8850 if (!PP.getPreprocessingRecord())
8851 return nullptr;
8852 Loc = Unit->getSourceManager().getSpellingLoc(Loc);
8853 Token Tok;
8854 if (PP.getRawToken(Loc, Tok))
8855 return nullptr;
8856
8857 return checkForMacroInMacroDefinition(MI, Tok, TU);
8858}

8861 return cxstring::createDup(getClangFullVersion());
8862}

8864Logger &cxindex::Logger::operator<<(CXTranslationUnit TU) {
8865 if (TU) {
8866 if (ASTUnit *Unit = cxtu::getASTUnit(TU)) {
8867 LogOS << '<' << Unit->getMainFileName() << '>';
8868 if (Unit->isMainFileAST())
8869 LogOS << " (" << Unit->getASTFileName() << ')';
8870 return *this;
8871 }
8872 } else {
8873 LogOS << "<NULL TU>";
8874 }
8875 return *this;
8876}

8883Logger &cxindex::Logger::operator<<(CXCursor cursor) {
8884 CXString cursorName = clang_getCursorDisplayName(cursor);
8885 *this << cursorName << "@" << clang_getCursorLocation(cursor);
8886 clang_disposeString(cursorName);

8889
8890Logger &cxindex::Logger::operator<<(CXSourceLocation Loc) {
8891 CXFile File;
8892 unsigned Line, Column;
8893 clang_getFileLocation(Loc, &File, &Line, &Column, nullptr);
8894 CXString FileName = clang_getFileName(File);
8895 *this << llvm::format("(%s:%d:%d)", clang_getCString(FileName), Line, Column);
8896 clang_disposeString(FileName);
8897 return *this;
8898}
8899
8900Logger &cxindex::Logger::operator<<(CXSourceRange range) {
8901 CXSourceLocation BLoc = clang_getRangeStart(range);
8902 CXSourceLocation ELoc = clang_getRangeEnd(range);
8903
8904 CXFile BFile;
8905 unsigned BLine, BColumn;
8906 clang_getFileLocation(BLoc, &BFile, &BLine, &BColumn, nullptr);
8907
8908 CXFile EFile;
8909 unsigned ELine, EColumn;
8910 clang_getFileLocation(ELoc, &EFile, &ELine, &EColumn, nullptr);
8911
8912 CXString BFileName = clang_getFileName(BFile);
8913 if (BFile == EFile) {
8914 *this << llvm::format("[%s %d:%d-%d:%d]", clang_getCString(BFileName),
8915 BLine, BColumn, ELine, EColumn);
8916 } else {
8917 CXString EFileName = clang_getFileName(EFile);
8918 *this << llvm::format("[%s:%d:%d - ", clang_getCString(BFileName),
8919 BLine, BColumn)
8920 << llvm::format("%s:%d:%d]", clang_getCString(EFileName),
8921 ELine, EColumn);
8922 clang_disposeString(EFileName);
8923 }
8924 clang_disposeString(BFileName);
8925 return *this;
8926}
8927
8928Logger &cxindex::Logger::operator<<(CXString Str) {
8929 *this << clang_getCString(Str);
8930 return *this;
8931}
8932
8933Logger &cxindex::Logger::operator<<(const llvm::format_object_base &Fmt) {
8934 LogOS << Fmt;
8935 return *this;
8936}
8937
8938static llvm::ManagedStatic<llvm::sys::Mutex> LoggingMutex;
8939
8940cxindex::Logger::~Logger() {
8941 llvm::sys::ScopedLock L(*LoggingMutex);
8942
8943 static llvm::TimeRecord sBeginTR = llvm::TimeRecord::getCurrentTime();
8944
8945 raw_ostream &OS = llvm::errs();
8946 OS << "[libclang:" << Name << ':';
8947
8948#ifdef USE_DARWIN_THREADS
8949 // TODO: Portability.
8950 mach_port_t tid = pthread_mach_thread_np(pthread_self());
8951 OS << tid << ':';
8952#endif
8953
8954 llvm::TimeRecord TR = llvm::TimeRecord::getCurrentTime();
8955 OS << llvm::format("%7.4f] ", TR.getWallTime() - sBeginTR.getWallTime());
8956 OS << Msg << '\n';
8957
8958 if (Trace) {
8959 llvm::sys::PrintStackTrace(OS);
8960 OS << "--------------------------------------------------\n";
8961 }
8962}
